title: cauliflower gratin
directions: Cook cauliflower in boiling salted water for about 12 minutes, until fork-tender.
Drain and place in shallow baking dish. Combine soup and milk; stir in cheese.
Pour over cauliflower. Sprinkle with crumbs.
Bake at 350° for 20 minutes until hot and bubbly.
Garnish with bacon.

title: mexican corn bread
directions: Mix all together and cook as you would regular corn bread.

title: carpenter's fancy cookies
directions: Blend beaten egg whites and sugar.
Add rest of ingredients. Drop by teaspoon on ungreased cookie sheet.

title: caponata
directions: In large, heavy saucepan, combine olive oil, eggplant, green peppers, onions, garlic and tomatoes.
Cook 20 to 30 minutes until just tender.
Add sugar, capers, tomato paste, vinegar, salt, parsley, green olives, pepper and basil.
Cover and simmer for 15 minutes.
Add pine nuts.
Serve warm, not hot, at room temperature or cold.
May be refrigerated for up to 3 weeks.
Serves 10 to 12.

title: lime fruit fantasy
directions: Oil mold.
Dissolve gelatin in boiling water; add marshmallows and stir until melted.
Add pineapple juice and chill until partially set.
Remove from refrigerator and fold in whipped cream.
Blend in crushed pineapple, cottage cheese and nuts and fill salad mold.
Chill until set.
Unmold on bed of lettuce leaves, kale or red lettuce leaves.
Fill center with a small dish of thinned mayonnaise.

title: banana nut bread
directions: Cream Crisco and sugar.
Add eggs and bananas.
Add flour, soda and nuts last.
Bake in 350° oven for 1 hour.

title: oreo cookie dessert
directions: Roll cookies to make crumbs.
Melt margarine; mix with crumbs and spread in pan (9 x 13-inch).
Save some crumbs for top of dessert.
Mix cream cheese and 3 cups milk.
Add pudding mix; mix well and pour over crust.
Spread Cool Whip over pudding mixture; top with remaining crumbs.
Makes 18 to 20 servings.

title: peanut clusters
directions: Melt together the almond bark and chips in double boiler along with the baking chocolate.
Add the peanuts and drop by teaspoon on waxed paper.
Makes 150 to 175 clusters.

title: minestrone soup
directions: Cook first 5 ingredients until soft.
Stir in next 3 ingredients.
Add next 5 ingredients.
Bring to a boil.
Reduce heat and simmer 1 hour, then add last 3 ingredients.
Cook 20 to 30 minutes longer.
Makes a big pot of soup.

title: fruit punch
directions: Mix all of the ingredients together and enjoy.

title: cream of zucchini soup
directions: In a skillet, saute onion in butter.
In a big pot, combine chicken stock and zucchini.
Add to pot onion, butter and bouquet garni.
Simmer until zucchini is tender and remove bouquet garni. Puree soup in blender.
Add 1 1/2 cups light cream (half and half).
Add salt and pepper to taste.
Serve hot or cold.

title: spinach balls
directions: Cook and drain spinach.
Combine all ingredients.
Chill 2 hours.
Roll into balls.
Bake at 325° for 20 minutes.

title: soft molasses cookies
directions: Mix together margarine, sugar and molasses.
Beat in egg. Alternately add hot coffee and the combined dry ingredients.
Mix well.
Chill overnight.
Roll out about 1/4-inch thick.
Cut into any shape and bake at 375° for about 14 minutes.
This makes about 70 cookies.

title: stuffed peppers
directions: Clean peppers.
Combine all ingredients except Parmesan cheese.
Fill peppers.
Bake at 375° for 30 minutes.
Sprinkle Parmesan cheese over top.
Cook for an additional 10 to 15 minutes.

title: million dollar pie
directions: Mix milk and lemon juice. Add Cool Whip and heat. Add fruit, nuts, cherries and coconut.
Pour in graham cracker crust shell and chill.

title: banana oatmeal cookies
directions: These are yummy with chocolate chips and/or raisins, too!

title: rum cake
directions: Combine all ingredients except pecans and blend.
Sprinkle pecans in bottom of a floured tube pan.
Add butter and bake at 350° for 1 hour.

title: sticky buns
directions: Mix butter, brown sugar, cinnamon and milk until smooth. Butter a 9 x 13-inch pan.
Place frozen rolls in pan; pour mixture over all.
Sprinkle pudding on, then add nuts.
Cover; let set out overnight.
Bake at 350° for 30 minutes in the morning.
Turn upside down and lay on foil.

title: four-fruit compote
directions: Drain pineapple, reserving 3/4 cup juice.
In a saucepan, combine sugar and cornstarch.
Add pineapple juice, orange juice and lemon juice.
Cook and stir over medium heat until thickened and bubbly.
Cook and stir 1 minute longer.
Remove from the heat; set aside.
In a bowl, combine pineapple chunks, oranges, apples and bananas.
Pour warm sauce over the fruit; stir gently to coat.
Cover and refrigerate.
Yields 12 to 16 servings.

title: forgotten cookies
directions: Beat egg whites until foamy; gradually add sugar.
Beat until very stiff.
Add salt and vanilla.
Fold in chocolate chips and pecans.
Drop by teaspoonfuls on ungreased foil.
Place in oven that has been heated to 350°.
Turn off oven and leave overnight.

title: lasagna
directions: Brown hamburger and onion; stir in all the seasonings. Add Ragu sauce and simmer. Cook noodles according to instructions on box. When noodles are done, remove hamburger mixture from heat and add cottage cheese. Stir. In a casserole dish, layer noodles, hamburger sauce and Mozzarella cheese. Sprinkle Parmesan cheese over this. Repeat until all hamburger sauce is used, ending with cheese on the top. Bake in preheated 350° oven for 30 minutes.

title: layer cake or cupcake
directions: Cream butter and sugar.
Add eggs.
Then add milk, flour and vanilla.
Makes 3 layers.
Bake at 350° for 30 minutes.

title: dill pickles
directions: Wash and soak cucumbers in cold water.
Leave overnight. About noon the next day dry and pack in jars.
Put in stalks of dill, garlic and hot pepper.
To vinegar add water and salt. Bring to boiling point and pour over cucumbers; seal.
To make lids seal, put jars in a large container and cover with water. Heat to hot; don't boil.
Let stand 5 minutes.

title: creole pralines
directions: In large (3 1/2-quart) heavy saucepan, combine granulated sugar, soda, buttermilk and salt.
Cook over medium high heat about 5 minutes (210° on candy thermometer), stirring often and scraping bottom of saucepan.
Mixture will foam up.
Add butter or margarine and pecans.
Over medium heat, continue cooking, stirring constantly and scraping bottom and sides of pan until candy reaches soft ball stage (234° on candy thermometer).
Remove from heat and cool slightly, about 2 minutes.
Beat with spoon until thick and creamy.
Drop from tablespoon onto sheet of buttered aluminum foil or waxed paper.
Let cool.
Makes about 20 (2-inch diameter) pralines.

title: hershey's fudge
directions: Mix together chocolate chips, margarine and vanilla.
In a large saucepan, mix sugar and milk and bring to rolling boil. Boil for 6 minutes, stirring constantly.

title: squash pie
directions: Put into 9-inch unbaked pie crust and bake at 350° for 50 minutes.

title: belle's buttermilk pie
directions: Mix all ingredients well.
Pour into unbaked pie shell.
Bake at 350° for 45 minutes.
Freezes well.

title: sweet pickles
directions: Put cucumbers in a strong salt brine (enough salt to float an egg).
Do not cut cucumbers.
Soak for 8 days. Weight down cucumbers in brine so they will not touch air.
Pour off brine, wash and slice.
Soak in alum water (2 tablespoons per gallon of water) for 24 hours.
Pour water off and wash.
Pour 1 gallon apple cider vinegar on cucumbers.
Leave 24 hours.
Pour off vinegar and throw away.
Put in stone jar or plastic bucket in thirds or layers, 1/3 sugar, 1/3 cucumbers and 1/3 spice.
Repeat. Leave 3 or 4 weeks to be ready to eat.
Leave in jar or bucket and eat as needed.
Will keep all year.

title: pound cake
directions: Put all ingredients together, mix until smooth.
Bake in tube pan about 45 minutes at 350°.

title: white bread
directions: Heat 4 cups water (2 cups in each pan).
In one pan, put 3 tablespoons sugar, 2 tablespoons lard and 1 tablespoon salt.
In the other, put 1/2 cake of yeast or 2 packages of dry yeast.
Put both pans of mixtures in the flour and knead.
Let it raise for 3 hours.
Put in greased pans and let raise for an hour.
Put in oven for 45 minutes at 375°.
After taking out of oven, grease the bread with shortening.

title: strawberry cake
directions: *If you do not have enough juice, add enough water to make 1 cup.

title: refrigerator mashed potatoes
directions: Cook and mash potatoes.
Add remaining ingredients to mashed potatoes.
Place in greased casserole.
Makes 8 cups. Will keep 2 weeks in refrigerator.

title: stay-in-bed stew
directions: Place all ingredients in a large dish with a tight cover. Cook at 275° for 4 to 5 hours.

title: mama's chocolate pie
directions: Mix cocoa, sugar and cornstarch together.
Mix cream, water and egg yolks and add to mixture.
Add butter and vanilla.
Blend mixture together and cook in heavy saucepan until it thickens. Pour into cooked pie crust.
Save egg whites for meringue.

title: aunt sue's baked beef stew
directions: Put all ingredients in 9 x 13-inch pan (Pyrex or Corning) and cover with foil (over and under) so no steam escapes.
Bake at 300° for 4 hours.

title: easy fantasy fudge
directions: Mix margarine, sugar and cream in heavy pan; bring to full boil, stirring constantly.
Boil for 5 minutes, stirring constantly.
Remove from heat; stir in chips until melted.
Add other ingredients; mix well.
Pour into a 9 x13-inch greased pan. Cool at room temperature; cut into squares.
Makes 2 pounds.

title: deviled burgers
directions: Mix all ingredients and shape into 4 patties.
Pan fry, broil or cook on foil over outdoor grate until of desired doneness.

title: sweet pickled beets
directions: Wash beets, leaving root and short top on.
Cook until skin will peel off good when put in cold water.
Skin beets; cut off roots and tops.
If beets are big, slice to thickness you like. May need to cook again until tender.
When tender, put in canning jars.
Make a mixture of sugar, water and vinegar.
Bring to good boil.
Put 2 teaspoons pickling spice in quart jars with beets. Cover with syrup mixture, leaving 1/2 inch at top of jar.
Put on lids tightly.
Boil in boiling water to seal, 15 minutes.

title: green beans with bouillon
directions: Bring water to a boil. Add bouillon cubes and onion flakes. Add beans and boil until dry.

title: strawberry sheet cake
directions: Bake a strawberry cake in a 16 x 11-inch pan.
Poke holes in top and pour on jello which has been dissolved in boiling water. When cool, frost with Cool Whip and strawberries.

title: cheese dainties
directions: Mix ingredients with electric mixer and then by hand until well blended.
Shape a rounded teaspoonful into small balls. Place on ungreased baking sheet and press with a fork.
Brush tops with slightly beaten egg white.
Bake at 375° for 10 to 12 minutes.
Should make about 50.

title: open-face peach pie
directions: Line unbaked pie shell with drained peach halves.
Beat together egg, white sugar and evaporated milk.
Pour over peaches. Mix brown sugar, butter and flour.
Sprinkle on top of peaches. Bake 20 minutes in 375° oven, then 30 minutes longer in 350° oven. Yield: 6 servings.

title: wild rice chicken supreme
directions: Cook rice as directed. Saute onion in butter. Blend in flour, salt and pepper. Gradually stir in cream and broth. Cook until thickened. Mix sauce, chicken, pimiento, parsley and almonds into cooked rice. Bake in 2-quart casserole for 30 minutes at 425°. Serves 6 to 8.

title: apple crisp
directions: Put apples in bottom of large baking dish.
Combine sugar, cinnamon and nutmeg; sprinkle on top of apples.
Combine water and lemon juice; pour over apples.
Combine sugar, flour and butter. Crumble over apple mixture.
Bake at 350° for 30 minutes.

title: chicken and rice
directions: Boil chicken until tender.
Cook rice in chicken broth.
Mix together and simmer, adding onions, cream of mushroom and butter. Recipe can be cut in half.
Salt and pepper to taste.

title: ham glaze
directions: Combine all ingredients.
Spoon over ham 2 or 3 times during the last 20 minutes of baking time.
Makes about 1/2 cup of glaze.

title: zucchini quiche
directions: Mix together well.
Put in
greased
pan 9 x 13-inch at 350° for 25 minutes.
Bake uncovered.

title: grandma jeffrey's applesauce cake
directions: Heat oven to 350°.
Combine sugar and Crisco.
Hold. Heat applesauce and add baking soda.
It will fizz up.
Immediately add to sugar and Crisco mixture.
Blend well with mixer.
Add flour and then the rest of the ingredients.
Raisins added last. Place in a 350° oven and bake for 1 hour.
Use regular loaf pan. You can easily double this recipe.

title: spiced tea
directions: Mix all ingredients.
Store in dry airtight container.
To serve:
Mix heaping teaspoon with boiling water.

title: wesson oil chocolate cake
directions: Mix all ingredients until smooth.
Add 1 cup boiling water, this will make the mixture very thin.
Pour in a greased loaf pan and bake at 350° until done, approximately 30 minutes.

title: cool cucumbers
directions: Bring water, vinegar, sugar, salt and pepper to a boil over high heat.
Turn heat to medium and continue boiling 3 minutes. Pour liquid over cucumbers in large bowl and store in refrigerator.
Keeps for days.

title: orange baked chicken
directions: Spread chicken breasts open in a shallow baking dish, breast side up, not overlapping.
Sprinkle with onion and seasonings. In medium bowl, thoroughly blend flour with about 1/2 cup orange juice until smooth.
Stir in remaining juice; pour over chicken. Bake, uncovered, about 1 hour or until tender, basting occasionally with juice in pan.
Serve chicken over rice or noodles on warm platter.
Stir pan juices to blend and pour over chicken.
Yields 5 servings.

title: blueberry pudding cake
directions: Place blueberries or other fruit in the bottom of a well-greased 8-inch square pan. Pour lemon juice over fruit. Mix the shortening and 3/4 cup of sugar. Blend with milk, flour and baking powder. Spread over berries. Combine 1/4 cup sugar, cornstarch and salt. Sprinkle over batter. Pour boiling water over top.
Bake at 350° for 50 to 60 minutes.

title: cranberry chunk salad
directions: Mix all ingredients together.
Pour into mold and freeze. After salad is frozen, pour out upside down on plate and ice with Cool Whip.

title: peach fluff
directions: Mix 1 box of crushed vanilla wafers and 1 stick margarine. Make a crust for one long Pyrex dish.
Mix sugar and Fruit-Fresh and pour over peaches.
Dissolve Jell-O in boiling water.
Mix peach mixture, dissolved Jell-O, Cool Whip and Eagle Brand milk. Pour into crust.
Refrigerate before serving.

title: sky-high biscuits
directions: Heat
oven to 450°.
Cut shortening into flour and sugar until mixture resembles fine crumbs.
Beat egg and milk slightly;
stir into
flour
mixture
until
soft dough forms.
Turn dough	onto lightly floured board.
Knead 10 times, sprinkling with
flour
if dough is too sticky.
Roll or pat dough 1 inch thick.
Cut
with floured 2-inch biscuit cutter.
Place about 1 inch apart on ungreased cookie sheet.
Bake until golden brown, 10
to
12 minutes.
Immediately
remove
from
cookie
sheet. Yield:	15 biscuits.

title: fresh fruit pie
directions: Set oven to 400°.

Line pan with crust. Add the berries or fresh fruit and mix together the sugar, flour, salt and cream and pour over the berries. Bake for 35 to 40 minutes or until the crust is nicely browned and the filling is set.

title: lemon whippersnappers
directions: Grease cookie sheets.
Combine whipped topping, cake mix and egg in large bowl.
Mix well.
Drop by teaspoon into powdered sugar.
Roll to coat.
Place 1 1/2 inches apart on cookie sheet. Bake at 350° for 10 to 15 minutes until light golden brown. Remove and cool.
Makes about 4 dozen.

title: salsa
directions: Mix all ingredients together and cover. Refrigerate overnight to blend flavors.
If finer texture is desired, put in a blender for a few seconds.

title: squash casserole
directions: Mix ingredients and pour into greased casserole.
Top with grated cheese.
Bake at 350° for about 35 to 40 minutes.

title: hash brown quiche
directions: Blot shredded, thawed hash browns with paper towel.
Spread in buttered 9-inch pie plate, press to form solid crust.
Brush with butter.
Bake at 425° for 25 minutes.
Sprinkle with cheese, chilies and ham.
Beat half and half, eggs, salt and pepper together.
Pour over cheese mixture.
Bake at 350° for 30 to 40 minutes, or until knife inserted at center comes out clean.

title: copper pennies
directions: Boil carrots until done.
Mix remaining ingredients.
Drain carrots; add to sauce.
Cover and marinate overnight.
Serve cold.

title: meat loaf
directions: Mix all ingredients and press in an 8-inch square pan.
Bake about 45 or 50 minutes at 350°.

title: peach cream cheese dessert
directions: Grease an 8 x 8-inch pan.
Mix first 6 ingredients; put in pan.
Drain peaches (reserve 1/4 cup juice).
Lay peaches on batter.
Mix next 3 ingredients and spoon over peaches.
Top with cinnamon and sugar.
Bake at 350° for 35 to 40 minutes.

title: chicken  spectacular
directions: Bring broth to a boil and add rice.
Simmer, covered, 20 minutes. Saute onions and peppers. Add to rice.
Add green beans, mayonnaise, soup and chicken.
Add water chestnuts.
Season with salt, pepper and garlic powder to taste.
Bake in large casserole dish and bake at 350° for 40 minutes.
tags: cream of celery soup or cream of mushroom

title: bourbon fruit cake
directions: Combine candied fruit, raisins and pecans.
Dredge in 1/2 cup flour, stirring to coat evenly.
Set aside.

title: grandmother's hot cakes
directions: Beat egg and milk and put in dry ingredients.
Makes about 8 or 10 pancakes.

title: brownies
directions: Combine and
bring just to a boil sugar, shortening and water, stirring constantly.
Remove from heat; add and stir in chocolate chips and vanilla until smooth.
Beat in eggs one at a time. Blend
in sifted flour, salt and soda.
Stir in nuts. Bake in 9-inch
square
pan at 325° for approximately 25 minutes. Sprinkle with powdered sugar or frost.

title: apple cake
directions: Mix sugar, flour, cinnamon, nutmeg, oil and vanilla.
Stir in raisins, nuts and apples.
Pour in greased oblong pan.
Bake at 350° for 45 minutes to 1 hour.

title: japanese fruit pie
directions: Mix all ingredients.
Pour into two 9-inch unbaked pie shells. Bake at 350° for 45 minutes.

title: peanut butter swirl cake
directions: Cream peanut butter and butter.
Gradually add brown sugar, beating at medium speed of an electric mixer until blended.
Add eggs, one at a time; beat after each addition.
Combine flour, baking powder, soda and salt; add to creamed mixture alternately with milk, beginning and ending with flour mixture.
Mix well after each addition.
Stir in vanilla.
Pour batter into 2 greased and floured 8-inch round cake pans.
Bake at 350° for 28 to 30 minutes, or until a wooden pick inserted in center comes out clean.
Cool in pans 10 minutes.
Remove layers from pans; let cool completely on wire racks.

title: chicken delight
directions: Place chickens, skin side up, in a greased casserole.
Mix together the dressing, marmalade and soup mix.
Cover the chicken with this sauce.
Bake, uncovered, at 350° for 1 to 1 1/2 hours. Serve with rice.

title: honey mustard dressing
directions: Combine all ingredients in jar.
Shake to mix well and chill. Yields 14 calories per tablespoon.
No fat.

title: quickie rolls
directions: Mix together.
Shape into any form and let rise only once in a pan.
After rising, bake about 10-12 minutes at 400-450 degrees.

title: squash casserole
directions: Heat milk and oleo. Add cheese, bread crumbs and squash; mix well. Bake in greased dish at 350° for 30 to 40 minutes.

title: homemade sherbet
directions: Mix milk, sugar and Kool-Aid very well in a blender.
Pour into plastic bowls or tubs with lids and freeze.
May also freeze in individual paper cups.

title: toll house pie
directions: Preheat oven to 325°.
In a large bowl, beat eggs until foamy. Add
flour,
sugar
and
brown sugar;
beat until well blended. Blend
in
melted butter.
Stir in chocolate morsels and chopped walnuts.
Pour into pie shell.
Bake at 325° for 1 hour.
Remove from oven.
Serve warm with whipped cream or ice cream, if desired.
Makes
one
9-inch
pie.
Recipe
may
be doubled.
Bake 2 pies; freeze one for later use.

title: date bars
directions: Grease	a 13 x 9-inch pan.
Cook dates, sugar and water together until dates are soft.
Let cool.

title: lime punch
directions: Pour ale in large punch bowl.
Place whole gallon of ice cream in bowl.
Toss slightly.
Garnish with lime slices.
Break ice cream away from block as you serve.

title: pistachio salad
directions: Using dry pudding, mix in pineapple and oranges until dissolved.
Add rest of ingredients. Chill and serve.

title: german potato salad
directions: Boil potatoes al dente.
While still warm, slice thinly, pennywise.
Add olive oil to keep potatoes from sticking together. Add squeezed-out cucumber.
Add onion, vinegar, salt and pepper. Marinate at least 1/2 hour.
Add bacon and top with chives.
Serve at room temperature.
Serves 6.

title: cheddar cheese quick bread
directions: Stir together the flour, baking powder and salt.
Cut in the butter or margarine.
Stir in the dill weed, cheese and rolled oats.
Add the milk and eggs.
Mix just until moistened.
Pour into greased 5 x 9-inch loaf pan.
Bake in a 375° preheated oven for 1 hour.
Cool for 5 minutes in pan.
Remove from pan and cool for 40 minutes before cutting.

title: 15-day chunk pickles
directions: Cover about 50 pickles with salt brine strong enough to hold an egg.
Weight down and keep in brine 7 days.

title: kahlua
directions: Note: This must be made ahead.

title: lace cookies
directions: Line cookie sheet with aluminum foil.
Mix ingredients well. Drop by 1/2 teaspoonfuls 2-inches apart on the foil-lined sheet. Bake in 350° oven for 6 to 8 minutes or until light brown. Allow to cool on foil before peeling cookies off.
Makes 7 dozen cookies.

title: blueberry delight
directions: Combine flour and 2 tablespoons sugar; cut in butter (I melted butter).
Stir in 1/2 cup nuts.
Press mixture into a 13 x 9 x 2-inch baking pan.
Bake at 350° for 15 minutes.
Let cool completely.

title: skillet pasta italiano
directions: Cook rotini according to package directions.
Rinse with hot water; drain.

title: homemade ice cream
directions: Mix together all ingredients and beat 10 minutes in mixer. Fill ice cream freezer rest of the way with whole milk.

title: never fail pie crust
directions: Cut Crisco into flour and salt.
Combine egg and vinegar.
Add to mixture.
Add ice water and mix with fork.
Make two pies or four shells.
Bake shells at 475° for 8 to 10 minutes.

title: sour cream fudge
directions: Mix the first 3 ingredients in kettle, then add the sour cream. Stir well before cooking.
Cook until it forms soft ball in cold water.
Place on back of stove.
Add piece of butter and vanilla; stir until thick.
Add the nuts.
Pour into greased pan to cool.

title: dutch babies(eggs)
directions: Beat eggs, milk and flour until well mixed.
Pour egg mixture into a shallow, ovenproof baking dish in which butter has been melted.
Bake in a 425° oven for
20 to 25 minutes or until done.
Squeeze lemon juice over egg mixture.
Spread with sifted powdered sugar.
Serve with lemon wedges.
Delicious for brunch.

title: veggie dip
directions: Mix all ingredients.
Let stand at least 8 hours.
Serve with raw veggies.

title: meat balls # 2
directions: Mix all ingredients well.
Make into small balls.
Place in skillet with small amount of corn or canola oil.
Brown all around until well done.
Remove from oil and put them into a pot of warmed mild salsa; keep warm to serve.

title: cole slaw
directions: Put cabbage through processor, then put bell pepper and onion through processor and put on top of cabbage.
Do not mix.
Bring vinegar, sugar and salt to boil.
Pour over cabbage, etc.
Let stand 1 1/2 hours, then toss.
Put in bowl with lid and refrigerate.
May be kept for a week.
The longer it sits, the better it tastes.

title: easy corn bread
directions: Pour into greased muffin or cornstick pan or an iron skillet. Bake in preheated oven at 450° to 500° for 30 minutes, or until browned.

title: mrs. lyndon johnson's famous lemon cake
directions: Preheat oven to 325°.
Cream 3/4 cup butter with sugar until light and fluffy. In a separate bowl beat egg yolks until light and lemon colored.
Blend into sugar mixture.
Sift together flour, baking powder and salt; resift 3 times.
Add the sifted ingredients in thirds, alternating with the milk.
Beat the batter thoroughly after each addition.
Add vanilla, lemon rind and lemon juice and beat 2 minutes.
Bake in a greased Bundt pan for 1 hour or until a straw inserted in the center comes out clean.

title: morning glory muffins
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
Mix flour, sugar, soda, cinnamon and salt in large bowl.
Add eggs, oil and vanilla; mix just until moistened.
Stir in carrots, raisins, pecans, coconut and apple.

title: garden bloody mary
directions: In tall glass, fill with ice.
Add vodka, Worcestershire sauce, celery salt, salt, pickle and celery (olive, Brussels sprout and olive on drink pick).
Fill remaining glass with Bloody Mary mix.

title: raw apple cake
directions: Mix oil, eggs and sugar until creamy.
Add other ingredients and mix well.
Bake in well-greased and floured pan at 350° for 1 hour.
Frost with Cream Cheese Icing.

title: shrimp fra diavola
directions: In 12-inch skillet, heat olive oil over medium heat and cook shrimp, garlic powder (or fresh) and red pepper flakes 2 minutes or until shrimp are almost pink. Stir in pasta sauce and bring to a boil over high heat. Reduce heat to low and simmer, uncovered, 3 minutes or until shrimp turn pink. Serve over hot linguine. Serves 4.

title: taco salad
directions: Brown meat and drain; add taco seasoning.
In large bowl, chop lettuce.
Add tomatoes, cheese, chips and meat mixture.
Pour dressing over and mix well.
Refrigerate.

title: apple sour cream cake
directions: Combine nuts, cinnamon and sugar in small bowl; set aside. In large bowl, cream butter and sugar.
Add flour, sour cream, eggs and vanilla.
Prepare apples.
Grease a Bundt pan.
Spread half of batter in pan.
Add half of nut mixture, then apples, then nut mixture.
Spread rest of batter on top.
Bake at 350° for 45 minutes.
Top with Cinnamon Caramel Glaze Sauce.

title: broccoli-cheese quiche
directions: Cook broccoli in microwave for 5 minutes.
Mix broccoli with 2 eggs and 3/4 cup milk.

title: baked eggplant casserole
directions: Cut eggplant and peppers into 1-inch pieces.
Cook in water until soft.
Save 1 cup of cooking water.
Pour the eggplant water over bread; set aside.
Mix eggs, oil, salt, pepper, garlic and cheese.
Squeeze excess water from bread.
Mix all ingredients and place in casserole dish.
Cover; bake at 325° for 60 minutes.

title: cranberry sour cream salad
directions: Combine
gelatin
and hot water.
Let congeal slightly. Add cranberry
sauce, celery, nuts and sour cream.
Pour into mold and refrigerate.
Makes 8 servings.

title: winter jam
directions: Cook cranberries, apples and water until clear and tender. Add crushed pineapple and sugar.
Cook 2 minutes.
Add strawberry Jell-O.
Stir in Jell-O until dissolved.
Pour into jars.

title: punch
directions: Mix all together and serve.
Serves approximately 40 people.

title: sausage and egg casserole
directions: Crumble sausage into skillet, brown and drain.
Mix together remaining ingredients and pour into a 9 x 13-inch shallow baking dish.
Refrigerate overnight.
Bake for 30 minutes at 350° or until a knife inserted in center comes out clean.
Serve warm.

title: carrot brownies
directions: Mix flour with baking powder, salt and spices.
Melt butter in saucepan.
Add sugar and heat until dissolved.
Beat in eggs. Add flour mixture.
Mix well.
Stir in carrots and the cereal. Pour into greased 13 x 9-inch pan.
Bake at 350° fo 30 minutes. Cool and top with glaze.

title: sticky buns
directions: Separate each loaf into small chunks of dough.
Put into greased 9 x 13-inch pan.
Melt margarine and mix with other ingredients.
Pour over dough and let stand for 1 hour.
Bake at 350° for 30 minutes.
Invert immediately.

title: scalloped tomatoes
directions: Saute onion in butter until tender.
Add next 4 ingredients. Arrange layer of tomatoes in bottom of greased 1 1/2 quart casserole.
Top with layer of onion mixture.
Continue until all is used, tomatoes on top.
Combine 1/4 c. bread crumbs with melted butter.
Sprinkle on top of casserole.
Bake at 375° for 45 minutes.

title: tomato soup salad
directions: Soften gelatin in water.
Heat soup. Add gelatin, stirring well until it dissolves.
Remove from heat and add cream cheese. Beat with rotary beater until smooth. Cool.
Fold in lemon juice, mayonnaise and vegetables.
Pour into lightly oiled 1 1/2-quart mold. Chill 4 to 5 hours.
Serves about 12.

title: chocolate chocolate chocolate cake
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
Pour oil into a 13 x 9 x 2-inch pan. Tilt pan until bottom is covered with oil.
Put remaining ingredients into pan; stir with a fork until well blended, 3 minutes.
Scrape sides and spread batter evenly.
Bake for 35 to 40 minutes, until toothpick comes out clean.
Cooled cake may be sprinkled with powdered sugar.
Store loosely covered.

title: hawaiian tuna salad
directions: Cool rice.
Combine rice, tuna, pineapple, strawberries, celery, seasonings and lemon juice; mix lightly.
Store in airtight container in refrigerator.
Add yogurt and almonds just before serving.
Yield:
4 to 6 servings.

title: fat-free oatmeal raisin cookies
directions: Preheat oven to 375°.
Spray cookie sheet with nonstick cooking spray.
In a large bowl, combine dry ingredients.
Stir in egg whites, corn syrup and vanilla until well mixed.
Add raisins. (Batter will be stiff.)
Drop by rounded teaspoonfuls onto prepared cookie sheets.
Bake 8 to 10 minutes or until firm.
Do not overbake.
Remove; cool on wire rack.
Makes 2 1/2 dozen. Preparation time:
20 minutes.
Each cookie provides:
0 grams fat; 0 mg. cholesterol; 60 calories; 1 gram protein; 65 mg. sodium and 13 grams carbohydrates.

title: cornbread
directions: Bake at 350° for 1/2 hour to 45 minutes.

title: nut rolls
directions: Dissolve yeast in lukewarm milk.
Add sugar and let stand until it bubbles.
Measure flour into large bowl; make a well. Add yeast mixture, egg yolks and melted butter.
Mix well until bowl becomes clean.
Put in refrigerator for a few hours.
Divide dough into 4 portions.
Roll until thin.

title: texas sheet cake
directions: Bring to a full boil margarine, cocoa and water.
Combine flour, sugar, salt and soda.
To this, add sour cream and eggs. Bake on greased cookie sheet or jelly roll pan at 325° for 25 to 30 minutes.

title: peach salad
directions: Mix first three ingredients.
Stir in Cool Whip, then stir in pecans and cheese.
Freeze.

title: oyster crackers
directions: Put crackers in a large bowl with cover.
Add oil and shake well.
Add dill weed; shake.
Add dry dressing mix; shake.
Add lemon pepper and garlic powder and shake to coat well.
Pour crackers onto waxed paper to dry or bake on cookie sheet at 250° for 15 to 20 minutes.
Cool.
Store in airtight container.

title: an old easy pound cake
directions: Cream margarine and sugar until light and fluffy.
Add eggs and flour alternately, ending with flour.
Add vanilla and mix thoroughly.
Prepare cake pan with shortening and flour and bake at 300° for 1 hour or until done.

title: split pea soup
directions: Cover peas with water and soak overnight.
Drain and rinse. Cook all ingredients except for potatoes for 2 hours.
Add potatoes and cook for another 40 minutes.
Remove bones and puree in an electric blender.
Return to saucepan.
Use same recipe for fresh bean soup.

title: rocky road bars
directions: Melt butterscotch chips, chocolate chips and peanut butter in double boiler.
Remove from heat.
Cool and add marshmallows, nuts and vanilla.
Press into any size pan, depending on desired thickness of bars.
Place in refrigerator to set.
Cut into squares.

title: potato casserole
directions: Mix all ingredients together and bake it at 350° until potatoes are tender.

title: doughnuts
directions: Beat eggs until fluffy.
Cream in sugar and lard.
Beat until creamy; add milk, salt, soda and baking powder.
Mix well, then add flour until able to roll out.
Cut out with a glass and thimble.
Fry in hot lard until light brown.
Roll in sugar or confectioners sugar.
Makes about 6 to 8 dozen.

title: country sausage and potatoes
directions: Cook sausage and onions until done.
Drain.
Stir in potatoes, sauce mix, water and pepper.
Cover and simmer 10 minutes, stirring occasionally.
Stir in carrot strips, cover and simmer until carrots are crisp-tender and potatoes are tender (10 to 15 minutes).
Stir in broccoli and cheese.
Cover and cook until broccoli is heated through and cheese melts, 5 to 10 minutes.

title: chicken casserole
directions: Boil chicken in a small amount of water with celery and 1 onion.
Remove chicken from bones.
Save broth.
Cool in refrigerator overnight and remove fat from top of broth.
Saute in oil:
chopped pepper and 1 chopped onion.
Add tomatoes and garlic powder; cook 10 minutes.
Add salt, black pepper, curry powder, parsley and thyme.
Cook 5 minutes longer.
Brown 3 tablespoons flour in 3 tablespoons oil until flour is the color of a copper penny.
Add this and the chicken to sauce.
Add 1/2 to 1 cup broth to sauce.
Cook for 45 minutes or simmer slowly for a longer period of time.

title: taco soup
directions: Brown ground beef and onion.
Drain.
Add taco seasoning and 3 cups water.
Stir until mixed well.
Add remaining ingredients and simmer, covered, over medium heat, stirring often, for 30 to 45 minutes.
Serve over fritos or tortilla chips.
Good with hot water corn bread.

title: easy chimichanga
directions: Cook hamburger, onion and green chilies together.
Drain grease; add cream of mushroom soup and heat thoroughly.
Put 2 spoonfuls on flour tortilla.
Add 1 tablespoon picante sauce and 1 slice cheese.
Roll tightly and cook in 1 inch of grease until brown on both sides.

title: blueberry yum-yum
directions: Combine blueberries, 1 cup sugar and 1/4 cup water in saucepan and cook over low heat until berries are soft, about 15 minutes. Combine cornstarch and 3 tablespoons water in small mixing bowl and stir well.
Add cornstarch to blueberry mixture and cook, stirring constantly, until thickened.
Set aside to cool.
Combine flour, margarine and pecans in a small mixing bowl and mix well. Press dough evenly into 13 x 9-inch baking pan or dish.
Bake at 350° for 20 minutes and cool.

title: grated raw sweet potato pudding
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
Beat eggs; add sugar, milk, butter, vanilla and salt.
Add 2 cups potatoes.
Place in 2-quart baking dish.
Sprinkle reserved cup potato over top.
Bake for 25 minutes.
Serves 6.
Serve with ice cream of whipped cream.

title: ham salad
directions: Stir together until well mixed.

title: pineapple cheesecake squares
directions: Heat oven to 350°.
Bake crust.
Beat cream cheese in medium bowl until smooth and fluffy. Beat in 1/2 cup sugar and the eggs. Stir in 2/3 cup pineapple juice.
Pour cream cheese mixture over hot crust.
Bake just until center is set, about 20 minutes. Cool completely.

title: fruit compote
directions: Drain fruit well.
Retain 2 cups juice from oranges and pineapple.
Make pudding using juice instead of milk.
Pour over fruit while hot.
Refrigerate.
Will keep 7 to 10 days.

title: strawberry butter
directions: Mix butter and oleo well.
Add package of thawed strawberries. Blend; add 1 cup powdered sugar to consistency of frozen yogurt.

title: spinach-apple salad
directions: In a small bowl, combine vinegar, oil, salt, and sugar; mix well.
Add apple, onion, and raisins; toss lightly to coat.
Cover and let stand 10 minutes.
Just before serving, combine spinach and romaine in a large salad bowl; add dressing and toss.
Serves 4-6.

title: banana split salad
directions: Mix together the Cool Whip and sweetened condensed milk, until well blended.
Add cherry pie filling, pineapple, nuts and sliced bananas.
Chill until serving.

title: whoopie pies
directions: *Mix 1 teaspoon cider vinegar with regular milk.

title: mulled cider
directions: Simmer cider and lemon juice for 15 minutes.
Tie spices in bag and simmer in cider mixture until of desired taste.
Serve hot.
Serves 18.

title: chocolate oatmeal drop cookies
directions: Combine oats and cocoa in a large bowl.
In a saucepan, melt butter or oleo, sugar and milk.
Let simmer 1 minute.
Add peanut butter, vanilla and salt.
Blend.
Then add second mixture to oats and cocoa.
Mix well.
Drop onto wax paper by spoonfuls. Cool at room temperature.
They aren't pretty but they are delicious!!

title: plain pastry
directions: Mix and sift flour and salt.
Cut shortening into mix using pastry blender or fork.
Sprinkle water, a small amount at a time, over the mixture and toss together lightly.
Use only enough water to hold together.
Turn onto a piece of waxed paper.
Press together and place in refrigerator for about 15 minutes.
Roll and fit on pie plate.
Bake according to directions for kind of pie. Makes enough for double crust or two 9-inch shells.

title: "phillips crab house" crab imperial
directions: Mix all ingredients, except crab meat.
Add crab meat.
Turn lightly so as to not break the lumps.

title: praline kisses
directions: Beat egg whites (at room temperature) until foamy.
Gradually add sugar, 2 teaspoons at a time, beating until stiff peaks form and sugar dissolves.
Fold in vanilla and pecans.
Drop mixture by heaping tablespoonfuls 3 inches apart onto greased cookie sheet. Bake at 225° for 1 1/2 hours.
Turn oven off; cool cookies in oven at least 1 hour.
Do not open oven door!
Yields 3 1/2 dozen.

title: old-fashioned oatmeal cookies
directions: Heat raisins and water to boiling; reduce heat to medium or lower.
Simmer, uncovered, until raisins are plump, about 15 minutes.
Drain raisins, reserving liquid.
Add enough water to reserved liquid to measure 1/2 cup.
Mix sugar, shortening, vanilla and eggs in large bowl.
Mix in raisin liquid; stir in remaining ingredients.
Drop dough by rounded teaspoonfuls about 2-inches apart onto ungreased cookie sheet.
Bake at 400° for 8 to 10 minutes or until light brown.
Immediately remove from cookie sheet.
Makes about 6 1/2 dozen cookies.

title: refrigerator cucumber pickles
directions: Slice unpared cucumbers and the peeled onions as for table use, making them thin slices (coin shape).
Mix all other ingredients and bring to a boil.
Pour over slices.
Using glass jars for storage, cover jars and keep refrigerated.
Tastes like a bread and butter pickle.

title: togo sauce
directions: Stone grind to make a paste the anise, whole cloves, ginger root and garlic.
Add 1/2 of large onion.
Put cut up chickens in a pot.
Rub in spices with tablespoon of glutamate and salt.
Cover pot and cook 10 minutes, stirring and turning (save juice).
Now, brown chicken in hot oil.
Add tomatoes, bouillon cubes, tomato paste and pinch of glutamate.
Cook until it boils in the spoon. Add chicken juice, 2 liters water and hot peppers.
Add chopped onion.
Add 1 tablespoon flour with cold water, making paste.
Cook 5 to 10 minutes more.
Serve over rice.

title: tri-berry jam
directions: Spread one slice of bread first with peanut butter and then dark jelly.
Cut it and another slice in half, diagonally.
Cut oval shaped eyes and mouth in each of the plain halves and place them over the jelly.

title: fresh garden vegetable salad
directions: Marinate vegetables in salad dressing for 12 hours.
Grate 1 pound sharp Cheddar cheese over top before serving.

title: crab ball
directions: Drain crab meat.
Blend softened cream cheese, chives, garlic powder and salt.
Fold in crab meat.
Shape into ball.
Roll in pecans.

title: spinach con queso
directions: Over low heat, warm milk in a large heavy pan. When milk is warm to the touch, slowly stir in cheese. Wait for cheese to melt, stirring occasionally, add the remaining ingredients. Mix thoroughly and remove from heat. Mixture is best when reheated in the microwave. Makes about 1 qt.

title: white icing
directions: Heat corn syrup to boiling.
Beat egg whites until stiff, but not dry.
Add salt.
Slowly pour corn syrup over beaten egg whites.
Beat until mixture is fluffy and hangs in peaks.
Fold in vanilla.

title: cascade berry pie
directions: Boil cascade berries, flour and sugar together until thick using a heavy bottomed pot.
Place berry mixture in pie tin lined with bottom crust.
Top with 2nd pie crust and pierce with a fork in several places to vent steam while cooking.

title: chicken casserole
directions: Pat out crescent rolls on bottom of a baking pan and brown. Layer broccoli on top of rolls.
Mix cream cheese with chicken and spread on top of broccoli.
Sprinkle with cheese and then Ritz crackers on top.
Bake at 350° for about 30 or 40 minutes or until it is brown and bubbles.

title: chicken and rice casserole
directions: Mix all ingredients together and pour over cooked rice.
Bake at 425° for 20 minutes.

title: twice baked potatoes(makes 4 servings)
directions: Wash potatoes, pat dry and prick potatoes with fork in a few areas.
Bake potatoes at 400° for about 1 hour or until done. (Microwave, uncovered, for 10 minutes on High power, rearrange after 5 minutes and turn over; adjust for your microwave).
Cool slightly.

title: pastel dessert
directions: Combine
pudding
mix, gelatin and water in a saucepan. Cook and
stir
over medium heat until mixture comes to a full boil and
is
thickened	and clear.
Remove from heat.
Chill until slightly thickened.

title: zucchini lasagne
directions: Bring a large pot of salted water to a boil.
Cut zucchini lengthwise into 1/8-inch thick slices.
Parboil in 3 batches for 5 to 6 minutes.
Remove from pot; drain on paper towel.

title: pecan pie
directions: Cream flour, sugar, salt and margarine. Add eggs and beat at low speed until they are blended in. Add the Karo and beat at low speed. Last add vanilla. Stir in pecans last of all and pour into unbaked pie shell. Bake 50 to 60 minutes at 350°.

title: chinese-style beef and vegetables
directions: In small bowl, blend Italian dressing, soy sauce and ginger; reserve 2 tablespoons.
In large skillet, heat remaining dressing mixture and cook carrots, covered, over medium heat, stirring occasionally, 10 minutes.
Add mushrooms and zucchini and cook covered an additional 5 minutes.
Remove vegetables and keep warm. Add reserved dressing mixture to skillet, then add beef.
Cook uncovered over high heat, stirring constantly, 5 minutes or until beef is done.
Return vegetables to skillet and heat through.
To serve, arrange beef and vegetables over hot rice.

title: chess pie
directions: Mix sugar with slightly beaten eggs.
Add cornmeal, vinegar and vanilla.
Melt margarine and stir into mixture.
Pour into unbaked pie shell and bake at 350° for 40 to 50 minutes or until set.

title: beef jerky
directions: Mix and let stand for 10 minutes.
Cut beef into thin slices. Place beef in marinade and let stand for 10 minutes.
Stir often and make sure beef is coated.
Drain and put on trays in dehydrator.
Takes about 24 hours to dry.
Put in plastic bags and seal.

title: never-fail pie crust
directions: Blend dry ingredients with the lard.
Add egg and liquids. Mix. Take out as much as needed.
Roll out on heavily floured board.
Remaining dough may be stored in a covered bowl in the refrigerator until needed.

title: cheesecake cookies
directions: Preheat oven to 375°.
Place paper liners in miniature muffin tins.
Combine graham cracker crumbs, butter and 2 tablespoons sugar in medium bowl; mix thoroughly.
Press one rounded teaspoonful crumb mixture firmly into each liner.

title: tuna casserole
directions: Make macaroni and cheese to directions.
Add drained tuna and soup.
Heat until warm.

title: ma-mo's sunday chicken
directions: Melt 2 to 3 heaping tablespoons Crisco in deep frying pan. Place chicken pieces in.
Add salt and pepper.
Brown on each side.
Add onion and garlic.
Fry with chicken until onion and garlic are cooked or soft, then cover chicken with water.
Cook over medium heat until all or most of water is gone.
Chicken should be very tender.
If not, add more water and cook down again.

title: one-step pound cake
directions: Preheat oven to 325°.
Grease and flour a 9-inch fluted tube pan.
In mixer bowl, beat all ingredients for 3 minutes.
Pour into pan.
Bake 55 to 60 minutes until cake tests done.
Cool 15 minutes.
Remove cake from pan; cool.
Frost or put on powdered sugar.
Preparation time: 10 minutes; baking time: 55 to 60 minutes.

title: black walnut cake
directions: Combine butter and shortening until fluffy.

Add sugar, buttermilk, vanilla and egg yolks. Add coconut and nuts. Beat egg whites with cream of tartar until stiff. Fold into cake mix. Put in greased and floured cake pans. Bake at 350° for 30 minutes.

title: mediterranean pasta salad
directions: Prepare pasta as directed on package; drain.
Rinse with cold water; drain.
Toss pasta and remaining ingredients in large bowl. Cover.
Refrigerate for 1 hour or until ready to serve.
Makes 4 to 6 servings.

title: broccoli casserole
directions: Cook broccoli in salted water until tender, about 5 minutes, then drain. Mix all together and bake at 300° for 45 minutes.

title: fresh apple cake
directions: Mix oil, sugar and eggs thoroughly with mixer.
Stir in dry ingredients, sifted together, then fold in apples and nuts.
Bake in greased 9 x 13-inch baking dish for 1 hour at 325°.
Leave cake in dish and cover with the glaze.

title: orange glazed chicken
directions: Place chicken in glass dish.
Spread glaze over all.
Bake at 350° for 30 minutes.

title: cream cheese icing
directions: Cream oleo.
Add cream cheese and beat together.
Add vanilla and powdered sugar and beat.
Refrigerate 15 minutes.

title: six week muffins
directions: In large bowl, combine all dry ingredients.
Add all wet ingredients; mix well.
Store in tightly covered container in refrigerator.
Keeps about 6 weeks.
Use as desired.
Bake at 400° for 20 minutes.
Fill baking cups or muffin tins 2/3 full.

title: squash fritters
directions: Mix all ingredients and drop by tablespoons into oiled griddle or skillet.
Cook on both sides until lightly browned.
Serve at once.
Makes about 1 dozen fritters.

title: pineapple bake
directions: Mix sugar and cornstarch together. Add Cheddar cheese; mix well.
Add pineapple chunks and toss.
Place in casserole dish. Top with crumbled Ritz crackers.
Melt butter and pour over.
Bake at 350° until bubbly, approximately 30 minutes.

title: triple-rich pound cake
directions: Preheat oven to 325°.
Butter and flour a 9 x 5-inch loaf pan. Sprinkle the pecans over the bottom and sides of the pan.
With an electric mixer, cream together the butter and sugar until light and fluffy.
Add the eggs, one at a time, beating well after each addition.
Add the flour, cream, vanilla and lemon flavorings; mix until batter is smooth.

title: deviled eggs
directions: Boil 8 eggs; cool.
Peel and slice in half.
Put egg yolks into mixing bowl; mash with a fork.
In separate mixing bowl, mix together Miracle Whip, mustard, salt, sugar and pickle relish (drained).
Mix until smooth.
Add egg yolks and mix well.
Place mixture into each egg half.
Sprinkle with paprika and serve.

title: rhubarb salad
directions: Cook rhubarb, water and sugar until tender, about 20 minutes. Add jello to hot mixture; stir.
Add pineapple and nuts.
Chill.

title: holiday jam cake
directions: Cream the sugar and shortening.
Add eggs and mix well. Combine buttermilk and jam and add alternately with sifted dry ingredients.
Add nuts and fruit last and stir well.
Bake in three 9-inch layers for 30 or 40 minutes at 350°.

title: zucchini cake
directions: Mix together and bake in a Bundt pan at 325° for 1 1/2 hours.

title: oreo cake
directions: Crumble half the cookies on the bottom of a 9 x 13-inch cake pan.
Mix
both
boxes
of pudding and 3 cups of milk and set aside.
Mix together cream cheese, confectioners sugar and Cool Whip and
then
the
vanilla pudding.
Put on top of Oreo crust. Crumble other half of cookies on top and refrigerate.

title: fruit salad
directions: Mix all ingredients together in bowl and refrigerate 3 to 4 hours before serving.

title: sour cream chocolate praline upside down cake
directions: Heat oven to 350°. Grease and flour 3 round 9 1/2 in. pans. Heat brown sugar, butter and whipping cream over medium heat, stirring occasionally, until butter is melted. Divide among pans; spread evenly. Sprinkle with pecans. Beat remaining ingredients in large bowl with electric mixer on low speed 30 seconds. Beat on high speed 3 minutes, scraping bowl occasionally. Pour over pecans in pans; spread evenly. Bake 22 to 25 minutes or until cake springs back when touched in the center. Cool 5 minutes. Turn upside down onto wire racks; let pans remain over layers for a few minutes before removing. Cool completely. Prepare Whipped Cream Topping. Place one layer, pecan side up, on cake plate. Spread with 1/3 of the topping. Repeat with remaining layers. Store covered in refrigerator.

title: vidalia onion pie
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
Reduce to 325° to bake pie.
Cook onions in butter until lightly browned; spoon into pastry shell. Add milk and 1 1/4 cups sour cream.
Blend flour with 1/4 cup sour cream.
Combine with egg mixture; pour over onion mixture.
Bake in slow oven (325°) for 30 to 40 minutes or until firm in center. Garnish with crisp fried bacon.

title: breakfast sausage casserole
directions: Prepare the night before:
Butter a 9 x 13-inch Pyrex dish. Butter both sides of bread; line the dish. Brown the sausage; crumble and drain.
Spread sausage over bread.
Sprinkle cheese over sausage.
Beat eggs; mix with rest of ingredients.
Cover with plastic wrap; refrigerate overnight.

title: peanut pie
directions: Mix the first 3 ingredients well.
Fold in the Cool Whip. Pour into a graham cracker crust.
Refrigerate.

title: fruity kabobs
directions: To make a kabob, carefully push a skewer through the ingredients starting with a piece of apple, then a marshmallow, then banana, followed by another marshmallow.
Spread a dollop of peanut butter on top of the marshmallow.
Now skewer a piece of banana and another marshmallow (with more peanut butter) and finish with a piece of apple.
Repeat with other skewers.

title: brown pie
directions: Prepare brownie mix according to directions.
Bake in glass pie pan.
When cooled, spread peanut butter on top.
Chill 5 minutes, then spread chocolate frosting over peanut butter.
Place cookies on sides by dabbing frosting on cookies.
Put one in center.

title: party wieners
directions: Mix jelly, mustard and Worcestershire sauce in large pot. Heat until dissolved and mix well.
Add chopped wieners and simmer until wieners are done, stirring occasionally.

title: creole okra
directions: Saute okra, onion and green pepper in butter 5 minutes, stirring constantly. Stir in remaining ingredients; cook over low heat 10 to 15 minutes, stirring occasionally.

title: peanut butter cookies(no bake)
directions: Mix sugar and cocoa in pan.
Add butter and milk.
Stir over medium heat until mixture boils for 1 minute.
Add vanilla and stir.
Remove from heat and stir in the peanut butter.
Then stir in the oatmeal.
Drop by spoonfuls onto greased cookie sheets. Let dry.
Do not bake!

title: apple nut cake
directions: Sift flour, then measure.
Add soda and salt.
Sift 3 more times.
In another bowl, mix corn oil and sugar well.
Add beaten eggs to corn oil and sugar.
Sift flour in slowly.
Add nuts, apples and vanilla.
Pour into 9-inch pans.
Put in cold oven. Bake 45 minutes at 325°, no longer.

title: coffee cake
directions: Beat first 5 ingredients together well.

title: fried rice
directions: Heat bacon fat in frying pan. Fry ham until brown. Add mushrooms, celery, water chestnuts, bamboo shoots, and peas and cook 3 minutes. Add slightly beaten egg, cook. Stir in rice and green onions. Add soy sauce.
Any left over vegetables may be added.

title: marshmallow icing
directions: Boil sugar and water (I cook the sugar and water until it forms a hard ball when dropped into cold water.)
Add slowly to egg whites.
While still warm, add cream of tartar and vanilla. Beat until bowl is cool.

title: cheese ball
directions: Put cream cheese in bowl with mustard, mayo and horseradish. Mix all of this with electric mixer.
With spoon, add dried beef and roll in ball. Add walnuts or parsley on outside of cheese ball.

title: crispy dill sweet pickles
directions: Pour vinegar off pickles.
Cut pickles in chunks.
Boil sugar, water and vinegar until syrup.
Cool.
Pour over pickles. Refrigerate 2 weeks if you can wait that long.

title: chicken roll-ups
directions: Put chicken in rolls and roll up.
Place in Pam sprayed casserole dish.
Heat other ingredients until cheese is melted. Pour over rolls.
Bake at 350° for 20 to 30 minutes or until brown. Serves 8.

title: bean and corn salad
directions: Combine all ingredients in a large bowl, mixing well.
Chill for several hours before serving.
Yield: 16 to 20 servings! Enjoy!

title: oatmeal icebox cookies
directions: Cream oleo, sugar and brown sugar.
Add eggs and beat.
Add flour, baking soda, salt and vanilla and beat.
Add oatmeal and mix.
Add pecans and chips and mix.
Make into long rolls.
Wrap rolls in waxed paper.
Refrigerate or freeze.
Cut and bake at 350° for 12 to 15 minutes.
Makes 100 cookies.

title: vegetable ball
directions: Mix together and refrigerate two hours.
Take out and make ball.
Roll in chopped nuts.

title: 6 layer cookies
directions: In a 13 x 9-inch pan melt butter.
Add the last 5 ingredients in layers.
Bake at 325° for 25 minutes.
Cut into squares when cool.

title: fruit dip
directions: Mix together. Refrigerate. It is best when stands overnight.

title: sour cream banana cake
directions: Cream butter with sugar.
Add eggs, then bananas.
Add flour, baking powder with milk and soda and vanilla.
Bake at 350° until done.

title: mini-pizzas
directions: Split muffins in half.
Add desired sauce (any of the 3 works well), spread thinly.
Put ground beef on and top with Mozzarella cheese.
Bake at 400° until cheese melts and browns slightly.

title: cheese and sausage balls
directions: Mix all ingredients together.
If too dry, add 1 tablespoon of water.
Form into balls, one-inch in diameter (not too smooth or uniform).
These can be made ahead and frozen before baking.
Bake at 350° for 20 to 25 minutes.

title: hash brown casserole
directions: Mix all ingredients together.
Put in deep 9 x 13-inch or 10 x 15-inch pan.
Melt 1 stick butter.
Mix with 2 cups corn flake crumbs.
Sprinkle on top.
Bake until hot through.

title: brownies
directions: Melt the butter and chocolate chips in a microwave-safe dish. Add sugar, eggs and water.
Mix in flour and soda.
Pour in a 9 x 13-inch pan and bake at 325° for 30 to 35 minutes or until done. Sprinkle with powdered sugar after they have cooled.

title: keri's slaw
directions: Mix together cabbage and Ramen noodles.
Meanwhile, mix noodle seasoning, oil, vinegar and water together.
Add to cabbage mixture.
Add peanuts before serving.

title: chicken casserole
directions: Melt margarine in bottom of 9 x 13-inch pan.
Place chicken breasts in pan.
Sprinkle with salt, pepper, garlic salt and Accent.

title: chicken and rice
directions: Lay chicken on top dry rice and add 1 package of Lipton onion soup mix.
Be sure to follow directions on soup package and soup cans.
Add proper amount of water.
Put soups plus water on top of chicken in order listed.
Bake at 425° for 1 1/2 hours.

title: stroganoff steak
directions: Cube the steak and cook with onion in margarine until brown. Stir in rest of ingredients.
Cover and cook 45 minutes.
Serve over rice or noodles.

title: chow mein noodle candy haystacks
directions: Melt morsels over low heat in thick skillet. Pour over noodles and peanuts and mix well. Drop by spoonful onto wax paper.

title: fruit delight
directions: In a large bowl, add fruit cocktail, chocolate chips, 3/4 bag of coconut and whole container of Cool Whip.
Mix well.
Spoon onto dish.
Sprinkle remaining coconut over top.

title: blueberry crisp
directions: Heat oven to 375°.
Arrange blueberries, sugar, lemon and juice in 8 x 10-inch dish or pan.
Combine next 5 ingredients until crumbly and sprinkle over berries.
Bake 35 to 40 minutes until brown and bubbly.

title: peppered steak
directions: Cut steak in bite size pieces.
Flour pieces; put in pan and let brown.
Add water, then add bell pepper and onion, then add mushrooms.
Cook about 5 to 10 minutes after steak browns.

title: chocolate syrup
directions: Simmer 5 minutes.
This is delicious over ice cream cakes.

title: skillet apples
directions: Melt margarine in a skillet.
Add sugar, cinnamon, cornstarch and water.
Stir until well mixed.
Add apples and cook for 15 minutes, covered.

title: rumaki(makes 18 appetizers)
directions: Prepare rumaki; cut livers into chunks.
Wrap each bacon piece around a water chestnut and piece of liver.
Secure with toothpick.

title: green tomato pie
directions: Mix all ingredients together except butter and pour into pie shell. Dot with butter and cover with top crust. Cut small holes with knife to vent. Bake at 350° for 1 hour.

title: honey dijon chicken(fat:  3 grams per serving)
directions: Combine honey, mustard, curry powder and soy sauce.
Place chicken in a food storage bag with zipper-type closure.
Pour in marinade.
Marinate in refrigerator overnight.
In a 9 x 13-inch baking pan, place chicken breasts.
Pour marinade over chicken. Cover and bake in a 350° oven for 1 hour.
Remove cover and bake 15 minutes, uncovered.
Serves 4.

title: pasta dinner salad
directions: Cook macaroni until done; drain and chill.
Slice carrots; cube ham and tomatoes.
Chop onion and broccoli.
Mix with chilled macaroni.
Mix olive oil and Catalina dressing and toss with macaroni mixture.
Chill thoroughly for at least 3 hours.

title: old fashioned teacakes(over 50 years old)
directions: Cream shortening and sugar together until fluffy.
Beat eggs. Add to sugar mixture; mix well.
Dissolve soda in vinegar.
Add to mixture.
Sift flour, baking powder and salt.
Add to mixture. Dough will be stiff.

title: fruit pizza
directions: Line bottom of two 12-inch round pizza pans with foil. Combine 1/2 cake mix with water, eggs, margarine and brown sugar; mix thoroughly.
Add remaining 1/2 mix.
Fold in nuts.
Divide batter between pans.
Bake at 350° for 15 to 20 minutes.
Remove from pans after cooling slightly and peel foil from cake.
Top with the Cool Whip.
Arrange fruit in circular pattern: strawberry halves, pineapple spears, kiwi slices and sliced bananas.
Refrigerate.

title: pita bread filling
directions: Mix and put in pita bread.
You can put Ranch dressing on top.

title: aunt belle's cheesecake
directions: Mix Jell-O and boiling water, slightly thicken.
Melt oleo and mix with cracker crumbs.
Press into 9 x 13-inch glass dish.
Whip chilled milk; set aside.
Beat cream cheese, vanilla and sugar. Beat slightly thickened Jell-O into cream cheese mixture, then fold into whipped cream.
Refrigerate overnight or a minimum of 3 hours.

title: quick cherry cobbler
directions: Chop frozen pie in small pieces and place in glass baking dish.
Add sugar and butter.
Bake at recommended setting and time on pie box.
Serve warm with whipped topping.

title: chocolate zucchini bread
directions: Combine sugar and oil in mixer bowl; beat until thick.
Beat in eggs, buttermilk and vanilla.
Add flour, cocoa, baking powder and baking soda; mix well.
Stir in zucchini and chocolate chips.

title: holy cow cake
directions: Cool cake mix according to directions.
While cake is still hot, poke holes in cake and pour Eagle Brand milk and ice cream topping over cake.
Cool completely in refrigerator.
After cooled, top with Cool Whip and sprinkle on candy bars.
Keep in refrigerator.

title: one-pot dinner
directions: Brown ground beef in skillet; drain off fat and put beef in crock-pot.
Brown bacon and onions; drain off fat.
Add bacon, onions and all other ingredients to crock-pot.
Stir well.
Cover and cook on low for 9 hours.
Liquid smoke is optional.

title: overnight casserole
directions: Mix all ingredients except chopped boiled eggs.
Place chopped, hard boiled eggs in an 8 x 12 inch casserole.
Fold mixture over eggs.
Let stand overnight in the fridge.

title: oatmeal hot cake
directions: Measure oats.
Let stand
in
boiling water 15 minutes. Combine sugar, shortening, salt,
egg, soda and baking powder. Mix well on low speed mixer.
Add
vanilla
and nuts.
Bake at 350° until done.

title: strawberry cake
directions: Place all ingredients in bowl; beat 3 minutes on medium speed. Place in greased 9 x 13-inch layer pan or 2 (9-inch) pans.

title: slow cooker spaghetti sauce
directions: Combine meat in large skillet with onion and garlic.
Break up meat with a fork and cook until it loses red color.
Drain excess grease.
Transfer to slow cooker; add remaining ingredients. Cover and cook on low for 6 to 8 hours.
Serve hot with spaghetti/macaroni.
Serves 6.
Freezes well.

title: banana nut cake
directions: Beat all
ingredients
on
high for 3 minutes.	Bake at 350°. Bake until golden brown.

title: creamed spinach
directions: Over medium low heat, melt 3 Tbsp. butter in a saucepan. Stir in flour and salt until creamed together. Stir in milk a little at a time. Increase heat to medium. Constantly stir with a whisk until mixture becomes thick and smooth. Remove from heat and set aside. Saute onions in 2 Tbsp. butter until transparent. Add spinach and water to pan; lower the heat and cover. Stir several times until the spinach is almost completely cooked. When spinach is almost done, stir in prepared sauce and sour cream. Stir well and simmer until completely blended.

title: sweet potato custard
directions: Preheat oven to 300°.
Coat 5 cups of a standard muffin tin with nonstick baking spray.
Put all ingredients into food processor and puree.
Stir in raisins and spoon into muffin tins. Bake for 45 minutes.
Unmold and serve when cool enough to eat.

title: quick fixing casserole
directions: Spray casserole dish with Pam.
Layer uncooked ground meat, pressed in casserole dish.
Cover with sliced onion.
Top with mushroom soup; add frozen peas or corn.
Spread Tater Tots over mixture.
Sprinkle with paprika.
Bake for 1 1/2 hours at 350°.

title: polka dot cookies
directions: Cream together sugar, butter and cream cheese until light and fluffy.
Beat in eggs and vanilla.
Blend in flour and salt.
Stir in chocolate and raisins.

title: spiced rice, beef
directions: Cook rice according to package.
Brown ground beef in a small skillet.
Combine all ingredients except cheese in a 2-quart casserole.
Sprinkle cheese over top.
Bake at 350° for 30 minutes.

title: crab dip
directions: Blend softened cream cheese with milk. Drain crab meat well. Add crab meat, onion, horseradish, salt and pepper to cream cheese mixture. Top with sliced almonds. Bake 15 minutes at 375°.

title: broccoli and rice
directions: Mix together.
Bake at 350° for 1 hour 15 minutes.

title: banana split brownie pizza
directions: Preheat oven to 375°.
Prepare brownie mix according to package directions.
Grease a 13-inch pizza pan.
Pour brownie mix in it and spread evenly.
Bake 15 to 20 minutes or until set. Cool to room temperature.
Mix cream cheese and 2/3 cup sugar until smooth.
Sprinkle 2 tablespoons sugar over strawberries. Spread cream cheese mixture over brownie "crust".
Top with fruit and nuts.
Melt chocolate and butter together, stirring until smooth.
Drizzle over pizza.
Chill.
Cut into wedges with pizza cutter.
You can add coconut, if desired.

title: taco dip
directions: In a small bowl, combine cream cheese, sour cream, dressing mix, lemon juice and hot pepper sauce.
Blend well and refrigerate for several hours.
Just before serving, spread mixture on large serving plate.
Top with lettuce, olives, chiles, onions, tomato and cheese.
Serve with tortilla chips.
Makes 10 to 12 servings.

title: toasted chili nuts
directions: In saucepan, combine butter, Worcestershire sauce, chili powder, onion salt and red pepper.
Heat and stir until butter melts.
Spread nuts in 9 x 9-inch pan.
Toss with butter mixture. Bake at 350° for 12 to 15 minutes, stirring occasionally.
Spread on foil; cool.
Store in airtight container.
Makes 2 cups.

title: praline biscuits
directions: Heat oven to 450°.
Place 2 teaspoons butter, 2 teaspoons brown sugar and 3 nut halves in each cup of muffin pan.
Sprinkle with cinnamon.
Heat in oven until butter is melted.

title: veggie pizza
directions: Flatten out on cookie sheet.
Bake at 225° until brown.

title: oatmeal fruit drop cookies(low calorie)
directions: Melt margarine.
Beat in eggs and vanilla.
Sift together the flour, baking powder, sweetener and salt.
Mix in dried fruit, nuts and oatmeal.
Add liquid mixture and stir until blended. Drop by teaspoonful onto greased cookie sheet.
Bake at 350° for 12 to 15 minutes, until golden.
Yields 60 cookies, 29 calories each.

title: mexican fiesta dip
directions: Combine beans and Manwich sandwich sauce in saucepan.
Stir over low heat until well blended.
Add green chilies.
Bring to a boil, stirring constantly.
Reduce heat and stir in cooked meat and Jack cheese.
Continue stirring until cheese melts.
Serve as hot dip with tortilla chips.

title: zucchini drop cookies
directions: Cream above ingredients together.
Add 1 cup chopped nuts and 1 cup raisins, if desired.
Drop by spoonful on greased cookie sheet.
Bake 12 to 15 minutes at 375°.
Makes approximately 3 dozen cookies.

title: terry's oatmeal munchies
directions: Preheat oven to 325°.
Cover baking sheets with foil and coat with a nonstick vegetable spray.
In a medium bowl, combine oats, flour, salt and baking powder.
Mix well with a wire whisk and set aside.
In a large bowl, combine sugar and butter and mix at medium speed to a grainy paste.
Add egg and vanilla.
Beat until smooth.
Add flour mixture and blend until just combined.
Drop teaspoons of dough onto the prepared baking sheet 2 1/2 inches apart.
Bake for 10 to 12 minutes or until edges begin to turn golden brown.
Cool, then peel off cookies with fingers.

title: caramel popcorn
directions: Stir all ingredients except vanilla
until boiling; cook without stirring for 5 minutes, then stir in baking soda and vanilla.
Pour over popcorn.
Spread on cookie sheet.
Bake in oven at 300° for 15 minutes.
Stir and cook 5 to 10 minutes more. Store in airtight container.

title: cheese ball
directions: Let cheeses and margarine soften about 10 hours.
Mix ingredients together, except nuts.
Roll into a ball.
Let harden, then roll into nuts.
Refrigerate at least 5 hours.

title: jimmy carter peanut butter pie
directions: Cream butter, peanut butter and cream cheese.
Add sugar and mix well.
Fold in Cool Whip.
When thoroughly mixed, pour into baked pie shell.
Chill for 1 hour.

title: banana bread
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
Grease bottom only of 9 x 5-inch or 8 x 4-inch loaf pan. In large bowl blend first 6 ingredients; beat 1 minute at medium speed.
Stir in remaining ingredients just until dry ingredients are moistened.
Pour batter into prepared pan. Bake at 350° for 50 to 60 minutes.
Cool 5 minutes; remove from pan.

title: broccoli and cheddar cheese with ritz crackers
directions: Cook broccoli; drain.
Place in casserole dish.
Crumble Ritz crackers on top of broccoli and melted butter.
Place shredded cheese on top.
Place in oven until cheese melts.

title: cream cabbage
directions: A raisin is a grape that's had too many worries.

title: sausage casserole
directions: Wash rice and put in casserole dish.
Brown sausage; drain. Mix soups, rice and sausage together.
Add salt to taste.
Bake, covered, for 1 hour at 350°.

title: mexican cornbread
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
Cream butter and sugar.
Add eggs. Beat well.
Blend in corn, peppers, chillies and cheeses.
Sift flour, baking powder, salt and corn meal; blend into mixture. Stir in jalapeno.
Pour into greased 9 x 13-inch or 8 x 10-inch pan.
Lower heat to 300°.
Bake 1 hour.

title: enchiladas
directions: Combine soups with meat.
Add green chillies to taste as well as pepper and salt.
Layer meat mixture with corn tortillas in a 9-inch square baking dish.
Top with grated cheese.
Bake in a 350° oven for 30 to 45 minutes.

title: fried pie crust
directions: Combine butter, coconut, flour and brown sugar in a saucepan. Cook until a brown color. Press mixture into a 9 inch pie plate. Cool before filling.

title: shrimp and broccoli soup
directions: Melt butter; add flour.
Cook until thickens.
Add McKenzie blend and saute.
Add broccoli, chicken broth and water.
Cook 20 to 30 minutes.
Add milk, shrimp and seasoning to taste.
Cook 10 to 15 minutes.
Great holiday soup!!

title: chicken-corn-chowder
directions: Place the chicken wings, water and salt in soup kettle.
Bring to boil, reduce heat to simmer and cook covered for 1 1/2 hours. Strain soup and allow chicken wings to cool.
Remove the meat from the bone. Discard bone and skin.
Return the meat to the broth and again place over the heat.
Add corn and black pepper. Cook for 15 minutes. Stir in chopped parsley just before serving. Serve hot with oyster crackers. Serves 6.

title: chili relleno dip
directions: Mix all ingredients. Refrigerate a few hours. Serve with tortilla chips.

title: sugar cookie
directions: Cream the butter, sugar, eggs and vanilla.
Mix dry ingredients together; add to first mixture.
Chill dough.
Roll out on 10x sugar.
Bake at 400° for 6 minutes.
Use an ungreased cookie sheet.

title: caramel frosting
directions: Mix ingredients.
Cook over low heat (like candy) until forms ball in water and it forms a golden brown in color.
Remove from heat.
Add vanilla; stir until it cools.
Spread on cake.

title: apricot brie
directions: Grease a round 8-inch pan.
Place a sheet of phyllo in pan overhanging one side by 4 inches.
Butter phyllo.
Repeat with other sheet.
Hang this one 4-inches over the other side.
Repeat until you have 2 layers on each side.

title: taco salad
directions: Brown hamburger and put on plate (10 or 12-inch).
Mix next 3 ingredients and spread on hamburger, then layer next 5 ingredients.
Serve with chips.
Serves 6 to 8 people.

title: dago dish
directions: Cook macaroni according to directions on package.
Drain well. Brown meat in skillet. Add onion soup mix and mix well. Add the cooked and drained macaroni and the crushed tomatoes.
Put mixture in casserole dish.
Sprinkle with grated cheese.
(You can use other kinds of cheese if you prefer.)
Place in a 350° oven and cook about 20 minutes until hot through and cheese is melted.

title: devonshire salad(very easy)
directions: Mix all above ingredients together. Chill several hours before serving. Serve on a lettuce leaf. Very easy.

title: bleu cheese dressing
directions: Blend in blender all ingredients except the last 4 ounces Blue cheese.
Blend until smooth.
Mix in by hand the additional 4 ounces crumbled Bleu cheese. Store
in refrigerator.
Makes 4 cups.

title: gramma's sweet potato pie
directions: Mix brown sugar with flour, then mix all ingredients together well and pour into unbaked crust.
Dot butter on top before baking.
Bake at 350° for 1 hour.

title: 3-day sweet pickles
directions: (Put spices in a cloth so can remove from the liquid.)

title: scalloped oysters
directions: Alternate corn, crackers and oysters in layers; add salt and pepper to taste.
Beat eggs; add milk and half and half together. Pour over each layer.
Dot with butter.
Bake at 350° for 35 to 40 minutes.
Serves 10.

title: greek salad
directions: Mix all together and chill overnight.

title: escalloped okra
directions: Combine onions, salt, pepper, butter and cooked okra.
Layer in casserole with cheese, egg and bread crumbs.
Top with buttered bread crumbs.
Bake at 350° for 30 minutes.
Makes 4 servings.

title: smothered liver and onions
directions: Salt, pepper and flour liver.
Place in heated shortening and brown on both sides.
Add sliced onion and hot water.
Simmer for 1 hour or until tender.

title: old-fashioned mincemeat
directions: Mix spices and salt with sugar.
Add to other ingredients. Cook until apples are tender and clear.
Use beef broth or apple juice or both for cooking liquid.

title: crescent rolls
directions: Dissolve yeast in water.
Stir remaining ingredients, except half of flour, into yeast.
Add rest of flour and mix until smooth. Scrape dough from side of bowl; cover with cloth.
Let rise in warm place until double, about 1 1/2 hours.
Divide in half.
Roll about 1/4-inch thick into a circle.
Spread with soft butter.
Cut into 16 pie shaped pieces.
Beginning at rounded edge, roll up.
Place on pan, point down.
Repeat with other half.
Cover; let rise until double, 1 hour.
Brush with butter.
Bake in 400° oven for 12 to 15 minutes.

title: bran muffins
directions: Combine dry ingredients first, then add remaining.
Mix well. Bake at 350° for 20 minutes.
Makes 1 dozen.

title: roast beef seasoning
directions: Mix well and store in covered jar.
Use 2 tablespoons per roast the last hour or so of cooking.

title: punch bowl cake
directions: Bake cake mix in 9 x 13-inch pan and cut in squares.
Mix pudding as usual.
Layer ingredients in the order stated in a punch bowl.
About 3 layers will fill a punch bowl.

title: tea biscuits(bakery style)
directions: Mix sugar, flours, baking powder and salt.
Mix oil, milk and vanilla, then add to dry ingredients.
Beat well.
Add raisins. Put in muffin tins.
Bake at 350° for 25 minutes.

title: martha wilson's broccoli casserole
directions: Cook broccoli and drain it.
Mix mayonnaise, soup, onion, eggs and broccoli.
Place on casserole dish, put cheese on top then bread crumbs and bake at 350° for 45 minutes.

title: sausage or ham casserole
directions: Cover bottom of baking dish with cubed bread.
Spread over cubed bread, 1 pound cooked and drained sausage or ham.
Sprinkle with chopped onion and green pepper.
Add lots of grated cheese and eggs, whipped with milk.
Cover well and refrigerate overnight. Cook at 350° for 35 minutes.

title: fruit salad
directions: Drain juice from pineapple and oranges and save.
Add enough water to the juice to make 3 cups liquid.
Mix liquid with pie filling and cook until it has a glazed look.
Do not boil.
Cool completely.

title: tuna salad
directions: Combine all these ingredients in a large mixing bowl.
Cook and drain a 7 ounce package of salad noodles or spaghetti rings and stir with salad.
Salt and pepper to taste.
Chill and serve on lettuce leaf.
Sprinkle with paprika.

title: dump cake
directions: Place cherries in 13 x 9-inch pan.
Pour on pineapple.
Cover with dry cake mix.
Cover this with melted butter.
Bake at 350° for 45 minutes.

title: skroodles
directions: Brown meat and drain.
Simmer mushrooms and onions in oleo; add to beef.
Pour sauce over meat; set aside to cool.
Combine cheese and sour cream.
Cook noodles.
In a casserole dish, layer 1/2 noodles, 1/2 sauce, all of cheese mix, then the rest of the noodles and sauce.
Cover and chill 2 hours or overnight.
Bake at 350° for 1 hour.

title: working girl's cobbler
directions: Melt margarine in oblong casserole dish.
In a separate bowl, mix flour, sugar, baking powder and milk.
Pour over the margarine without stirring.
Add fruit without stirring.
Sprinkle 2 tablespoons sugar over top and bake at 325° for 1 hour.
A tasty brown crust forms on top.

title: frosted grapes
directions: Wash grapes and place on a towel.
Pat with towel and set grapes aside to completely dry.
In a bowl, beat the egg whites until they are just frothy.
With a pastry brush, brush the grapes lightly but thoroughly with the beaten whites.
Arrange the grapes on racks and sift the sugar over them, turning them to coat them evenly.
Chill the grapes until the sugar is set, and arrange them carefully in a serving bowl or on a lovely tray.

title: cheese ball
directions: Mix by hand all ingredients except dried beef.
Form into a ball.
Chop dried beef fine in blender or Oscar.
Roll cheese ball into beef, covering the whole thing.
Best if refrigerated overnight before serving.

title: copper pennies
directions: Mix together all ingredients, except carrots.
Pour mixture over carrots.
(Do not stir.)
Let set overnight.

title: mock turkey
directions: Mix all ingredients together and put into greased baking dish. Cover and bake at 350° for 90 minutes.

title: peanut butter and marshmellow eggs
directions: Melt paraffin wax; add chocolate and Hershey bar.
Soften butter until creamy.
Add peanut butter; mix until creamy.
Add marshmellow and sugar.
Mix with hands and shape.
Dip formed eggs into chocolate.
Place on cookie sheet; freeze overnight.
Makes about 42 eggs.

title: chicken livers with burgundy sauce
directions: Dredge livers in flour.
Lightly brown on both sides in bacon fat.
Add 1 cup chicken broth.
Simmer 10 minutes.
Add onion, mushrooms and wine and continue to simmer for 30 minutes.
Serve over buttered noodles or rice.
Sprinkle with Parmesan cheese. Serves 6.

title: cottage cheese filling
directions: Mix all ingredients well.

title: mrs. gilpin's fruit cake
directions: Dredge fruit in 1 cup of flour.
Add 1 cup wine or whiskey. Bake in slow oven.

title: lasagna
directions: Melt 4 tablespoons butter in saucepan.
Add onion, salad dressing mix and tomatoes.
Simmer, stirring, until liquid evaporates.
Combine beef, bread crumbs, milk, eggs, 1/2 of Parmesan cheese, 1/2 of parsley, 1 1/2 teaspoons salt and pepper. Mix well and brown in remaining butter.
Add to tomatoes mixture. Add tomato paste, water, sugar and remaining ingredients.
Simmer 45 minutes.

title: black-eyed pea salad
directions: Mix all ingredients together; toss lightly and serve.

title: pistachio pie
directions: Blend instant pudding, Cool Whip and crushed pineapple.
Pour into chocolate crust.
Top with walnuts and/or shaved chocolate. Freeze.
Thaw about 2 hours before serving.

title: butterscotch nut bars
directions: Mix all ingredients except the butterscotch morsels and nuts. Press
dough
into a 10 1/2 x 15 1/2-inch pan. Sprinkle butterscotch
morsels
and chopped nuts over the top.
Bake at 350° for 20 to 25 minutes. Cool and cut into 2-inch squares.

title: cold spicy szechuan noodles
directions: Cook noodles according to package directions; drain and rinse under cold water.
Press rest of ingredients except sesame seeds and scallions in a blender, food processor or mixing bowl.
Blend well.
Add sesame seeds to the sauce and pour over the cold noodles.
Sprinkle with the scallions and serve immediately or refrigerate.

title: molasses cake
directions: Mix all ingredients, first the sugar, butter and molasses. Add coffee and eggs, then spices, raisins, currants and flour. Can use all raisins; I like to substitute craisins for the currants. Bake at 350° about 50 minutes or 325° about an hour and 10 minutes. Test center. Bake in 8 x 12-inch dish or pan. This makes a large cake and will keep or freeze well. Good sliced and served with butter. Serves 40. Can freeze. Can do ahead.

title: bill's sugarless cookies
directions: Mix all ingredients together.
Drop by teaspoon on ungreased cookie sheet.
Flatten with a glass.
Bake at 350° for about 6 minutes until golden brown.
May add 2 or 3 chocolate chips to each cookie, but they are good without the chips.

title: cinnamon cherry crisp
directions: Butter baking pan.
Arrange cherry pie filling in bottom of pan.
Drizzle with lemon juice.
In a bowl, mix flour, sugar and cinnamon.
With a fork, blend in the egg to make a crumbly mixture.
Sprinkle the mixture over the cherries.
Drizzle with melted butter.
Bake at 375° for 35 to 40 minutes or until top is crisp and cherries are bubbly.
Serve warm or cooled with vanilla ice cream.
