title: chow chow
directions: Wash, drain and prepare vegetables.
Sprinkle with salt. Cover and let stand overnight.
Turn into a colander, drain and rinse well with cold water.

title: baked beans
directions: Combine all ingredients, except bacon.
Place in casserole dish.
Put bacon strips on top.
Bake for 1 hour in a 350° oven.

title: hello dolly squares
directions: Melt margarine and add to graham cracker crumbs to form a crust in 9-inch square pan.
In this order, add layers of coconut, chocolate chips and pecans.
Pour Eagle Brand milk over ingredients.
Bake at 350° for 30 minutes.
Let cool for 1 hour before cutting.

title: broccoli rice dish
directions: Cook rice.
Add soup and cheese to hot rice.
Saute onions and celery in oleo.
Pour boiling water over broccoli and drain. Combine all in casserole and bake at 325° for 45 minutes.
If you like, top with can of French fried onion rings the last 10 to 15 minutes.

title: my mothers' chocolate icing
directions: Bubble boil 1 minute. Take off heat and beat. Add vanilla flavoring and pecans. Spread over 3 layer cake (Duncan Hines Butter Recipe).

title: life savers soup(low-calorie soup)
directions: Mix all ingredients in stock pot.
Allow to simmer for hearty taste.

title: scalloped potatoes
directions: Spray baking pan.
Put potatoes in first.
Slice butter into pats on top.
Add milk.
Sprinkle flour, salt, pepper and parsley evenly over potatoes and milk.
Bake at 450° about 1 hour or until creamy.

title: radish salad
directions: Clean radishes, then slice very thinly.
Put in a bowl and sprinkle with salt.
Cover and leave for 10 minutes, then pour off liquid from bowl.
Rinse and pat dry with paper towels.
Mix together vinegar, oil, parsley and capers.
Add the radishes and toss well together.
Cut the cheese into thin strips and stir into the salad.
Chill for 20 minutes before serving with Melba toast. Serves 4.

title: blueberry cake
directions: Cream the first 3 ingredients and mix well.
Add the vanilla, flour and baking powder.
Grease a 13 x 9-inch pan.
Spread 1/2 of batter in pan.
Spread the blueberry pie filling or any other filling.
Spoon remaining batter on top.
Bake at 350° for 45 minutes.

title: cheese ball
directions: Mix cheese, garlic, salt, onions and all ham except about 2 slices (dice all ham).
Mix well and shape in form of a ball.
Put the remainder of ham on ball.

title: peanut butter kisses cookies
directions: Cream the sugars, oleo and peanut butter.
Beat in eggs, milk and vanilla.
Put dry ingredients together and add to sugar mixture.
Shape into balls (about the size of a walnut).
Roll in granulated sugar and place on ungreased cookie sheet lined with foil.
Bake at 350° for 10 to 12 minutes.
Remove from oven, place a chocolate kiss on cookie and press down.
Makes 7 dozen cookies.

title: walnut filling for layer cake
directions: Mix all ingredients together well.
Cook in double boiler until thick.
Frost with chocolate frosting.
We like a boughten frosting.

title: crab meat-stuffed mushrooms
directions: Preheat oven to 375°.
Remove stems from mushrooms; brush caps with melted butter.
Arrange in greased baking dish.
Combine crab meat, 2 tablespoons crumbs, egg, mayonnaise, lemon juice and 2 teaspoons melted butter in a bowl. Fill each mushroom cap with some of the crab mixture.
Garnish each mushroom with 3 small dices of green pepper (optional).
Combine 2 teaspoons butter and remaining bread crumbs; sprinkle over crab stuffing.
Bake 15 minutes; serve hot.

title: summer salad
directions: Mix together as in order given.

title: mexican dip
directions: In bottom of pan, spread beans.
Mix together sour cream, mayonnaise and taco seasoning.
Spread over beans.
Next, put a layer of tomatoes, onion and cheese.

title: chicharrones de pollo
directions: Cut parts into morsels and discard wing tips.
Season well with adobo.
Mix rest of ingredients, except corn oil, and pour over chicken.

title: peanut butter candy roll
directions: You will also need wax paper.
Mix first 3 ingredients together.
Get 3 equal size sheets of wax paper.
Separate ingredients that are already mixed together into 3 separate portions.
Put on each piece of wax paper.
Using a rolling pin, roll out on wax paper.
Spread peanut butter all over.
Take 1 corner and roll it over and over, etc., then wrap it up in the wax paper.
Put in refrigerator.

title: apricot fruit salad
directions: Combine all ingredients and chill.

title: fried corn
directions: Remove husks and silks from corn. Cut corn from cobs, scraping cobs to remove all milk.
Heat butter and bacon drippings in a skillet until hot.
Add corn, water, salt and pepper.
Cook, uncovered, over medium heat until mixture comes to a boil.
Cover, reduce heat and simmer 10 to 12 minutes or until liquid is absorbed, stirring frequently.
Yields 10 to 12 servings.

title: chile rellenos casserole
directions: Beat eggs; add flour and milk.
Beat well.
Add grated cheese, chopped chiles and salt; stir well.
Pour into a 2-quart casserole.
Bake at 350° for 45 to 50 minutes or until set in the middle.
Test with a knife as you do for custard to make sure it is done and knife comes out clean.

title: great pumpkin!
directions: Slice pound cake.
Mix bourbon and sugar and brush on cake. Cube cake.

title: chocolate raspberry truffles
directions: In a saucepan, bring cream to a boil over moderate heat. Remove from heat.
Add chocolate, stir until melted and smooth. Add butter bit by bit, stir until smooth.
Stir in jam and Chambord.
Chill in bowl for about 4 hours.
After chilled, roll into small balls (1/2 to 1 inch diameter) and roll in cocoa powder.
Chill on waxed paper for about 1 hour.

title: bavarian style sauerkraut with pork chops
directions: Rinse sauerkraut with warm water; drain.
Cook onions and bacon in butter until onion is soft. Add drained kraut, caraway seed and sugar.
Cover.
Cook 1/2 hour.
Add bouillon and wine. Simmer 1/2 hour longer until kraut is cooked.
Pork chops can be put on top after being browned in a skillet.
Salt and pepper. Place under a broiler to brown bread crumbs.

title: bacon wrapped water chestnuts
directions: Wrap the water chestnuts with the bacon strips and secure with a toothpick.
Bake 1/2 hour at 350°.
Drain the grease.
Mix the remaining ingredients and spoon over the water chestnuts.
Return to the oven and bake an additional 1/2 hour at 350°.

title: angel biscuits
directions: Roll dough on floured board.
Cut with doughnut cutter or glass.
Bake at 400° for 12 minutes.

title: saucette potato patties
directions: Blend entire contents of saucette can.
Heat in microwave or on stove, adding canned milk, margarine and water as wished.
If you want more saucette taste use less milk and no water.
If you wish to stretch the recipe, add more water and milk.
Stir in potato flakes until mixture is stiff.
Shape patties and brown lightly.

title: souper burgers
directions: Brown ground beef and drain fat.
Add one can cream of onion soup and approximately half can of water.
Mix well and simmer 10 minutes.
Great hot lunch in little time, served on buns.
tags: cream of onion soup or substitute French onion soup but must add flour

title: granola
directions: Mix together oatmeal, almonds, coconut, sunflower seeds, sesame seed and optional ingredients thoroughly if used.
Blend together olive oil, honey, cinnamon and nutmeg; pour over first mixture. Mix well.
Bake in 2 large pans (I use sheet cake pans) until lightly golden at approximately 300°, for about 30 minutes, stirring every 10 minutes.
Serve warm or cool.
May add raisins or other dried fruit after it has cooled.
Store in large jar or cans in refrigerator if it won't be eaten in one week or so.

title: butterball cookies
directions: Sift flour; measure.
Sift again with sugar and salt into mixing bowl.
Add butter and vanilla.
Blend with pastry blender. Add 2 cups of nuts.
Shape half of the dough into 1/2-inch balls. Roll in nuts or flatten the balls; press pecan in top.
Bake in a 350° oven for 15 to 20 minutes.
Roll remaining dough into logs; bake.
Roll in powdered sugar.
Makes 4 dozen.

title: strawberry yogurt cake
directions: Beat cake mix (dry), water, oil, egg whites and 1 container yogurt in a large bowl on low speed for 30 seconds.
Beat on medium speed for 2 minutes.
Pour into a greased 13 x 9 x 2-inch pan.
Bake at 350° for 35 to 40 minutes or until cake springs back.
Cool completely.
Fold (one) container yogurt and 2 drops red food coloring into whipped topping.
Spread over top of cake. Garnish with fresh strawberries, if desired.
Refrigerate any remaining cake.

title: potato rolls
directions: Mix and let dissolve the warm water and yeast.
Add sugar, salt, shortening, eggs and mashed potatoes.
Mix until stirred together, then add flour.
Knead the bread.
Put into a greased bowl.
Cover with damp cloth and chill for 2+ hours.
Roll out and shape.
Let it raise twice its size.
Bake at 400° for 12 to 15 minutes.

title: dim sum pork
directions: Make sauce by combining first 8 ingredients, bringing them to a boil and then adding a cornstarch and water mixture to thicken. (Thicken to the point where sauce will cling to pork, but not too thick.)
Saute pork in pan of melted butter until 1/2 done.
Now add vegetables and finish cooking.
When pork and vegetables are done, add sauce and toss, then serve over a bed of rice.

title: mississippi mud cake
directions: Cream sugar, margarine and cocoa.
Add remaining ingredients and mix well.
Bake in 9 x 13-inch greased pan in a 350° oven for 25 to 35 minutes.
When done and while hot, spread 1 pint marshmallow cream on top.
When cold, ice with 1 box powdered sugar, 1/3 cup Milnot and 1/3 cup cocoa which has been blended well.
Sprinkle nuts on top of icing.

title: cake mix cookies
directions: Combine cake mix, butter, milk and egg; beat on low speed until very stiff dough forms; mix in coconut, chips and nuts (optional). Drop by rounded teaspoonfuls 2 inches apart onto lightly greased cookie sheets.
Bake at 375° for 10 to 13 minutes until lightly brown.
Let stand few minutes before removing from baking sheet. Makes 5 dozen.

title: celery casserole
directions: Cook celery about 20 to 25 minutes in chestnut water on low. Combine cooked celery, water chestnuts, soup and pimentos.
Turn into buttered 4-quart casserole.
Top with croutons.
Bake at 350° for 30 minutes.

title: sweet cherry salad
directions: Drain cherries and reserve liquid.
Cut cherries in half and set aside.
Add enough water to measure 2 1/2 cups.
Bring liquid to a boil; remove from heat.
Add gelatin and stir until gelatin dissolves.
Stir in Port wine.
Chill until the consistency of unbeaten egg white.
Fold in cherries and pecans.
Spoon mixture into a lightly oiled 6-cup mold.
Cover and chill until firm. Unmold onto a lettuce-lined plate; serve with mayonnaise.

title: jalapeno cornbread
directions: Mix all ingredients together and bake in a skillet.
Bake at 350° for about 35 minutes or until done.

title: greek salad
directions: Tear lettuce into bite size pieces.
Place lettuce, romaine, radishes, cucumber and green onions in large plastic bag.
Shake oil, vinegar, salt and oregano in tightly covered jar; refrigerate.
Before serving, shake dressing, then add olives to vegetables in bag.
Close tightly and shake until ingredients are well coated.
Pour salad into large bowl; top with cheese.
Add anchovies, if desired.

title: breakfast casserole
directions: Press rolls into a buttered 9 x 12-inch baking dish and seal edges.
Brown sausage. Drain well. Sprinkle sausage and cheese over rolls. Combine remaining ingredients. Beat well.
Pour over sausage and cheese. Bake at 425° for 15 minutes or until set.
Cut into squares and serve.

title: macaroni and beef
directions: Brown ground beef.
Cook macaroni until tender.
Drain ground beef and macaroni.
In the same pot, add Ragu and ground beef. Cook for about 5 minutes.
Add macaroni to sauce and ground beef. In baking dish layer macaroni and beef with cheese.
Bake at 350 for 30 minutes.
Serve with garlic bread and salad.

title: pumpkin pound cake
directions: Combine first 4 ingredients and beat well.
Add remaining ingredients and mix thoroughly.
Pour into greased and floured tube pan.
Bake 30 minutes at 350°; reduce heat to 325° and bake about 45 to 50 minutes more or until done.
Cool 10 minutes in pan before removing.
Freezes well.

title: easy white salad
directions: Drain pineapple well of all juice in large bowl.
Combine pineapple, walnuts, milk and Cool Whip.
Add lemon juice and mix well.
Refrigerate.

title: strawberry banana milk shake
directions: Place milk, banana and strawberries in a blender.
Cover and mix at high speed for 10 seconds.
Add ice cream.
Mix at high speed until smooth.

title: vanishing oatmeal raisin cookies
directions: Heat oven to 350°. Beat together butter and sugars until creamy. Add eggs and vanilla; beat well. Add combined flour, baking soda, cinnamon and salt. Mix well. Stir in oats and raisins. Drop by rounded tablespoonfuls onto ungreased cookie sheet. Bake 10 to 12 minutes or until golden brown. Cool 1 minute on a cookie sheet. Makes about 4 dozen. Cookie bars use 13 x 9 metal pan. Bake 30 to 35 minutes.

title: lemon broiled fish
directions: In small bowl combine butter and lemon juice.
In medium bowl combine bread crumbs, parsley, 1/4 cup of butter and lemon juice mixture.
Add paprika to remaining butter and lemon juice mixture. Dip fish into mixture of butter, lemon juice and paprika.
Broil fish until they flake with fork.
Top with crumb mixture.
Return to broiler and heat thoroughly.
Refrigerate leftovers.
Makes four servings.

title: orange jello salad
directions: Heat pineapple.
Add Jell-O and stir until dissolved.
Chill until it starts to set, then add cottage cheese, Cool Whip and mandarin oranges.

title: rhubarb custard pie
directions: Beat eggs.
Add sugar, flour, salt and melted butter.
Beat mixture thoroughly.
Add milk.
Put rhubarb, cut in little pieces, in pastry lined pie pan.
Pour custard mixture over rhubarb.
Bake in 350° oven for 15 minutes.
Reduce heat and bake until custard is set, about 40 to 45 minutes.

title: creamy crunchy chicken and rice bake
directions: Combine process cheese spread and rice; mix well.
Add chicken, peas and half of onions; mix lightly.
Pour into 1 1/2-quart casserole.
Bake at 350° for 15 minutes.
Top with remaining onions.
Continue baking 5 minutes or until onions are lightly browned.
Makes 4 to 6 servings.

title: beef stew bourbonnais
directions: Cut vegetables diagonally.
Cut beef into cubes and brown slightly.
Add garlic and onion and saute.
Use salt and pepper. Stir in soup (undiluted), wine and water.
Cover and simmer 30 minutes.
Add herbs and ketchup.
Arrange vegetables on top of meat and gravy.
Cover.
Simmer 1 1/2 hours or until meat and vegetables are tender.
Add more water if needed.
Half cup lemon juice may be substituted for wine.
Increase water from 1/4 cup to 3/4 cup.

title: strawberry salad
directions: Mix gelatin with boiling water and juice saved from pineapple plus enough water to make 1 cup.
Add pineapple and refrigerate overnight.
Add sour cream, cream cheese, 1/2 cup of sugar and 1/2 teaspoon of vanilla and beat at medium speed.
Cover gelatin with mixture and sprinkle with nuts.

title: cranberry jello mold
directions: Mix Jell-O in boiling water until dissolved.
Sit until almost set.
Mix sour cream and cranberry sauce with mixer.
Combine with Jell-O and pour into glass bowl or mold.
Serves 8 to 10.

title: sand tarts
directions: Work
butter and part of sugar together, then remainder of sugar
and	the
eggs should be added.
Use enough flour to make stiff
(very
stiff).
Roll
and cut with cookie cutter. Wet the top with beaten egg, sprinkle nutmeg and sugar on top. Bake at 350°
for 10 minutes.
Will stay for months in cookie tin.

title: cranberry salad
directions: Run cranberries through a food chopper.
Make jello; let set, then add sugar, cranberries, marshmallows and walnuts.
Pour in mold and serve with whipped cream mixed with homemade salad dressing, if desired.

title: low fat casserole
directions: Chop onion and cook with ground beef.
Put chopped cabbage into casserole bowl.
Spoon beef mixture on top then pour soup and water mixture and rice over this.
Bake at 350° for 1 hour covered.

title: pop's favorite salad
directions: Mix Cool Whip and oranges with cottage cheese.
Sprinkle dry Jell-O over this.
Mix well.
Keep refrigerated.

title: corned beef casserole
directions: Cook noodles in boiling salt water; drain.
Add corned beef, soup, milk and onions.
Pour into 2-quart casserole (greased) and top with buttered crumbs.
Bake in a 350° oven for 45 minutes.

title: fruit dip
directions: Mix all ingredients with electric mixer.
Serve.

title: elvis presley's fried peanut butter sandwich
directions: Mash banana with a fork.
Spread the bread with peanut butter and banana.
Melt the butter in skillet over medium heat.
Fry the sandwich, browning both sides.

title: lemon pie
directions: In a double boiler pan combine sugar, cornstarch and salt.
Add milk and heat until mixture boils and thickens.
In small bowl combine lemon juice and egg yolks.
Add 1/3 cup of hot milk to eggs and lemon juice.
Add to hot stove mixture and cook until thick custard.
Add butter.
Pour custard into baked 9-inch pie crust and top with 2 egg whites, beaten to peaks.
Add 2 tablespoons sugar and put on pie custard and bake at 350° until meringue browns, about 10 to 20 minutes.

title: peanut butter cups
directions: Cream together peanut butter, butter and sugars.
Add beaten egg and vanilla.
Stir in and mix well the flour, baking soda and salt.
Roll into 1-inch balls.
Put into ungreased miniature muffin pans.
Bake at 350° for 10 to 12 minutes.
While warm, press into each cookie a mini Reese's peanut butter cup.
Cool completely and remove from pans.
Yields approximately 48.

title: orange nut bread
directions: Sift the flour and salt into a large bowl; stir in orange rind and sugar.
Beat egg, orange juice, milk and butter together in a small bowl.
Stir in the nuts.
Pour liquids onto flour mixture and stir until blended.
Pour into two 8 x 4-inch greased loaf pans.
Bake at 350° for 40 to 50 minutes until skewer comes out clean.
Cool on wire racks.

title: joan's scalloped corn
directions: Melt oleo.
Stir all together.
Bake at 325° for 50 minutes covered and 10 minutes uncovered.
Bits of onion and/or red or green pepper (chopped) may be added, if desired.

title: sock it to me cake
directions: Mix together and bake just like any other cake.

title: lois' fried chicken
directions: Boil chicken pieces approximately 15 minutes.
Remove from water; salt and pepper to taste.
Melt shortening in skillet.
Add flour to melted shortening, mixing well.
Add fryer.
The flour will coat the chicken.
Fry to golden brown.
Save broth from chicken for future use.

title: easy crock-pot roast beef
directions: Place tinfoil on a broiling pan (you need enough so you can wrap the beef).
Place beef on tinfoil and bring foil up so you make a bowl. Dump in soup and soup mix.
Fold tinfoil closed.

title: oatmeal bread
directions: Mix boiling water, oatmeal, shortening, molasses and salt all together. Then dissolve 3 pkg yeast in 1/4 cup warm water and beat in 2 eggs and add to mixture. Next add in flour a little at a time.

title: window cleaner
directions: Put into spray bottle to use.
Will leave no streaks and windows stay bright and shiny.
You may add a few drops of food coloring to identify it.

title: cream cheese icing
directions: Mix the first 4 ingredients.
Add pecans and coconut.

title: lucy marse's hot roll recipe
directions: Mix warm water, yeast and sugar thoroughly.
Add to that mixture the cooking oil and self-rising flour.
If the dough is not as stiff as biscuit dough, add a little more flour.

title: creamy tacos
directions: Cook ground beef and salt.
Drain off excess liquid.
Then add soups, Ro-Tel, beans, cheese and seasoning.
Cook about 15 minutes over medium heat.
Pour over chips or use as dip (Doritos or Fritos).

title: jesse's corn cheese bread
directions: Saute onion in butter (just until tender, do not brown).
Mix together muffin mix, milk, corn, salt and Tabasco.
Spread in a greased 8 x 8-inch baking dish.
Top with a layer of onion and then a layer of sour cream.
Sprinkle with grated cheese.
Bake in a 425° oven for 20 to 25 minutes.

title: buried treasure pie
directions: Beat cream cheese with sugar and 2 tablespoons milk in a bowl until smooth.
Spread evenly in bottom of pie crust.
Arrange strawberries on cream cheese mixture.

title: mexican dip
directions: Layer ingredients in 1-quart dish in the order that they are listed.
Microwave on High power for 5 minutes or until cream cheese is melted.
Stir and serve with tortilla chips.

title: chicken barbecue sauce
directions: Beat eggs; add salt, pepper and poultry seasoning.
Add oil and vinegar.
May be refrigerated.
May use small amount to marinate chicken 2 hours to overnight.
Use remaining to baste as you grill.

title: squash 'n apples
directions: Use a 9 x 13-inch glass baking dish.
Make a layer of cut-up squash and a layer of unpeeled apple rings.
Dot with plenty of margarine.
Then mix brown sugar, flour and salt.
Mix and crumble over the squash and apples.
Cover pan tightly with foil and bake at 350° for 1 hour.

title: muffin surprise
directions: Preheat oven to 425°.
Grease muffin pan.
Sift flour, baking powder and salt into large bowl.
Stir in oat bran and brown sugar; set aside.
In small bowl, combine milk, oil, eggs and vanilla. Stir mixture into dry ingredients just until moistened.
Cut cream cheese into 12 equal pieces.
Spoon about 1/2 of batter into muffin cups, filling 1/2 full.
Spoon 1 tablespoon of jam on top of batter.
Top with 1 piece of cream cheese.
Spoon remaining batter over jam and cheese, filling each cup 2/3 full.
Bake 14 to 16 minutes or until brown.

title: spiced pecans
directions: Combine all ingredients in a saucepan and cook over medium flame with a candy thermometer to thread stage (232°).
Remove from flame and add 1 teaspoon vanilla and 2 1/2 cups pecan halves. Stir until pecans are well coated and mixture is creamy.
Pour onto a greased cookie sheet.
Separate pecans as they cool.

title: barbecue pork chops
directions: Mix all in a bowl.
Pour over pork chops.
Bake at 350° for 1 hour or until done.

title: tapioca pudding(baby pearl tapioca)
directions: Add tapioca to boiling water, stirring frequently.
Cook 10 to 15 minutes, then taste for softness.
Add dry jello and sugar; stir to dissolve.
Will be thin, but will absorb liquid while cooling.
Stir several times while cooling.
Chill.
Just before serving, add fruit (and juice if too thick) and whipped cream.

title: orange pie
directions: Mix all ingredients together, thoroughly, and pour into graham cracker crust. Refrigerate. This recipe makes 3 pies. (Can be frozen up to 6 months.)

title: bacon wrapped chicken
directions: Preheat oven to 325°.
Pound chicken breasts until flat.
Put a slice of cream cheese and 1 teaspoon chives in middle of each breast; roll up.
Wrap each rolled breast with 1 slice of bacon and secure with toothpick.
Combine soup, mayonnaise, milk, lemon juice, pepper and salt.
Mix until smooth.
Place wrapped chicken pieces in a 9 x 13-inch baking dish.
Cover chicken with sauce mixture.
Bake at 325° for 1 hour.

title: 24 hour salad
directions: Line bowl with lettuce and layer the onions, peppers, celery, peas and bacon.
Mix together the sour cream, mayonnaise and sugar; spoon in, covering the other ingredients.
Spread side-to-side to seal in flavor and sprinkle top with Parmesan cheese.
Cover and refrigerate.

title: bachelor's roast
directions: Place roast in pan.
Top with catsup, then pour on cola. Cover with foil and cook at 350° for 3 to 4 hours.

title: fish cakes
directions: Flake fish with fork.
Add potatoes, egg, parsley and seasoning.
Mix well.
Divide into 8 round cakes.
Coat in seasoned flour, then in egg, then in bread crumbs.
Heat fat and fry fish cakes 2 to 3 minutes each side until golden brown.
Drain on paper towels.
Garnish with lemon and parsley.

title: peanut brittle pie
directions: Beat egg yolks with brown sugar. Add to scalded milk. Cook until it's thick. Dissolve gelatin in cup of water. Add to mixture while hot. Cook until starting to set and add beaten egg whites which have 2 tablespoons of sugar. Add cup of whipping cream, crushed peanut brittle and vanilla. Pour into the baked pie shell and serve with whipped cream with brittle in it.

title: easy chocolate fudge
directions: Combine morsels and sweetened milk in heavy saucepan.
Warm over lowest possible heat, stirring until smooth.
Remove from heat.
Stir in nuts and vanilla.
Spread evenly into foiled 8 or 9-inch square pan.
Chill for 2 hours or until firm.
Lift from pan and remove foil.

title: maple syrup icing
directions: Boil syrup until it forms a thread.
Beat egg whites until stiff, adding syrup slowly until icing is cold and thick.
Add baking powder during last part of beating.
Sufficient for icing and filling for 9-inch layer cake.
Delicious!!

title: hot rotel dip
directions: Cook the ground meat or sausage, then drain off the grease. Then cook Velveeta cheese, Ro-Tel and picante sauce together on slow simmer until cheese melts.
Then mix in the meat.

title: dried apple stack cake
directions: Mix the first 6 ingredients together.
Sift together the flour and ginger and mix all together to make a stiff dough.
Divide in 10 equal parts.
Pat out in thin layers in 8-inch well greased pans.
Bake at 450° for 8 to 10 minutes until brown.
Cool and fill between layers with cooked, sweetened and mashed dried apples which have been seasoned to taste with cinnamon and apple pie spice.

title: crispy oatmeal cookies
directions: Combine oats, flour, brown sugar, butter and salt into large mixing bowl.
Blend until butter is thoroughly worked into mixture.
Stir together water and baking soda.
Stir soda mixture into oat mixture.
Add nuts, if used, blending well.
Shape into balls the size of walnuts or smaller if dainty tea-type cookies are desired.
Flatten with the bottom of a glass dipped in water, then dipped into sugar.
Bake at 375°
for 8 minutes until golden and crispy.
Cool on racks.
Makes 30 (3-inch) cookies.

title: roast eye of round
directions: Coat roast with coarse black pepper.
Cook 6 to 7 minutes per pound at 500°.
Turn oven off and do not open for 2 hours.

title: breakfast pizza
directions: Cook sausage until brown; drain off fat.
Unroll crescent dough and place in a 9 x 13-inch ungreased pan.
Press over bottom to form crust.
Seal perforations.
Spoon sausage over crust. Sprinkle with potatoes, then with cheese.

title: salisbury steak
directions: Combine beef, onion, egg, milk, bread crumbs, salt and pepper. Form 4 or 5 small patties.
Roll in flour and brown in oil.
Place in baking dish.
Cover with soup.
Bake 45 minutes at 350°.

title: german pizza
directions: Brown beef and onion; drain off grease.
Reduce heat.
Set aside.
In a large pot or electric skillet, melt butter.
Spread potatoes over butter; top with beef.
Combine eggs and milk; pour over all of it.
Cover and cook for 30 minutes.
Add cheese; cover until cheese melts.
Cut into squares and serve.

title: linda's chicken perlan(a version of recipe by regina ashby)
directions: In a large cast-iron pan, coated with cooking spray, saute onions and bell peppers.
In a frying pan, cook the bacon and brown the pieces of sausage. Add cooked bacon and sausage to pot with onions and bell peppers.
Add 2 Cornish hens and enough water to cover.
Cook covered on medium until hens are done (about 2 to 2 1/2 hours).
Remove hens and debone.
Return hens to pot, add rice and more water if needed, let cook about 45 minutes to an hour, stirring occasionally until rice is done.
Remove lid, stir and continue cooking until liquid is absorbed to your liking; careful not to absorb too much.
Great for a winter meal.

title: turkey caliente
directions: In casserole, put layer of turkey sprinkled with chili pepper, layer of soup mixture combined with broth and tomatoes. Next, a layer of tortilla strips, chopped onion, etc.
Cook for 30 minutes at 350°.
Uncover and cook for 15 minutes more.
Serves 8.

title: marinated duck breast
directions: In a dish, place skinned duck breasts.
Season with salt and pepper.
Place sliced apples and onion in dish and pour orange juice over breasts.
Cover and marinate overnight.

title: fruit cake
directions: Cream together the shortening and sugar.
Beat in eggs and sifted dry ingredients alternately with coffee, jelly and molasses.
Blend in fruits.
Line two 9 x 5 x 3-inch loaf pans with heavy wrapping paper and grease.
Fill pans almost full. Bake 2 1/2 hours at 300°.
Cover with paper last hour until tester comes out clean.
Cool.
Wrap in wax paper.
Store in airtight container.

title: cheeseburger pie
directions: Fry hamburger meat until done.
Drain off excess fat.
Add onions to the meat and cook until onions turn clear.
Set meat mixture aside.
When you open the crescent rolls, do not separate into crescent shapes but leave as rectangles.
Line the bottom of a lightly greased 9 x 13-inch baking pan with a layer of crescent rolls.
Add the hamburger and onion mix.
Top with a layer of the Velveeta cheese and finish with another layer of crescent rolls until all the top is covered.
Put in 375° oven and bake until crescent rolls turn golden brown. Cut into cubes to suit your plate.
Great served with salad and baked beans.

title: hot chocolate
directions: Mix all ingredients.
Put 1/4 cup mixture into cup and fill with boiling water.

title: beet pickles
directions: Boil beets; skin.
Place in mixture and bring to a boil. Place into jars and seal.

title: pimento cheese spread
directions: Mix dry ingredients.
Add water, vinegar and beaten egg.
Mix well and cook until thickened, stirring constantly.
Add butter and pimento and cook gently about 3 minutes.
Add 1 to 2 pounds of favorite cheese.

title: all-in-one brunch
directions: Combine and put in a buttered baking dish.
Refrigerate overnight.
Bake, uncovered, at 350° for 45 minutes.
May be frozen after cooking.

title: million dollar pecan pie bars
directions: Beat at medium speed for 2 minutes.
Pour over partially baked crust and sprinkle with finely chopped pecans.
Return to oven and bake 35 minutes until filling is set.
Cool and cut into squares. Makes 3 dozen.

title: apple pie
directions: Mix sugar and spices together.
In bottom of crust, line apples in thick layer.
Spread generously with sugar/spice mixture.
Repeat.
Fill crust very full, as apples cook down.
Dot oleo on top and put top crust on.
Cut vent holes in top and seal to bottom crust.
Bake in 400° oven for 40 to 60 minutes.
If edges begin to get too brown, cover with foil.

title: poppy seed sandwiches
directions: Take rolls out of pan and slice in half.
Mix margarine, mustard, Worcestershire sauce, grated onions and poppy seed well. Spread mixture on both sides of rolls.
Then lay ham and cheese on rolls.
Place top of rolls over ham and cheese.
Then spread mixture on top of rolls.
Bake at 350° for about 15 minutes.
Makes 72 sandwiches.

title: caramel pie
directions: Put one cup sugar in large iron skillet and let melt to a dark golden brown syrup, stirring constantly.
Add boiling water and cook until lumps are gone.
Mix rest of ingredients together and stir into syrup.
Cook until thick.
Cool before putting into baked pie crusts.
Makes 2 pies.

title: meat balls
directions: Mix the ingredients.
Roll into balls.
Put in oven and bake until brown.

title: swiss fruit bread
directions: Soak dried fruit in juice several hours.
In a large mixer bowl, stir flour, yeast and spices.
Heat milk, butter, sugar and salt to warm (to 120°).
Add to dry mixture.
Add eggs and shredded orange peel.
Beat with mixer on low speed.
Beat 3 minutes on high speed.
Stir in fruit mixture, walnuts and 2 to 2 1/2 cups flour to make soft dough.
Knead 8 to 10 minutes.
Use dough hook.
Shape in ball.
Place in greased bowl.
Let rise until double.
Shape in 2 loaves.
Let rise 60 minutes.
Bake in a 375° oven for 35 minutes.

title: rose hip jam
directions: Simmer rose hips in water in a covered saucepan.
Put cooked pulp in blender and blend until smooth.
Add sugar and allspice. Simmer, stirring constantly, until thick.
Mixture will thicken more after cooled.
Pour into jars.
Seal with paraffin.

title: bavarian apple torte("winner of endicott's apple festival bake off")
directions: Cream margarine, sugar, and vanilla.
blend in flour.
Pat dough into bottom and about 1 1/2 inches up the sides of a greased 9 inch spring form pan.

title: rum batter
directions: Melt together the butter, sugars, cinnamon and nutmeg.
Let ice cream melt and mix together.
Put in jars and refrigerate. Can be stored up to 3 months.
Delicious.

title: chicken piccata
directions: Pound chicken breasts paper thin; coat in flour.
Place in heated skillet, coated with butter.
Brown breasts and set aside. Discard contents of skillet.
Place breasts, lemon juice, capers and wine in skillet.
Cook until done (3 to 4 minutes).
Remove. Serve with steamed vegetables (broccoli, cauliflower, carrots and red bell peppers).
Add tarragon and wild rice.
Top chicken with artichoke hearts and twist of lemon peel.

title: mom's spanish chicken
directions: Boil chicken; skim fat off.
Add salt, pepper, and bay leaves.
Reduce heat and cook for 1 hour and 15 minutes.
Save broth.
Saute onion and bell pepper in olive oil.
Add tomatoes, Rotel, and rice.
Debone chicken and add to mix.
Cook additional 30 minutes over medium low heat.
Serving idea:
Serve wrapped up in warm tortilla.
Serves many people!

title: vanilla rolled cookies
directions: Cream margarine and sugar.
Add eggs and blend thoroughly. Add vanilla.
Combine dry ingredients and add to creamed mixture. Mix thoroughly and chill 2 hours or overnight.
Roll out as thin as possible on lightly floured board.
Cut with cookie cutters and place on greased baking sheet.
Sprinkle with sugar or frost after baking.
Bake at 400° for 6 to 8 minutes.

title: taco casserole
directions: Brown
ground beef and onion;
drain.
Add taco seasoning and taco sauce.
Crumble 2 cups of corn chips in casserole dish; add meat mixture on top of chips.
Put drained beans on top of
meat; cover
with
foil.
Bake
minutes
at 350°. Remove foil;
add rest
of
crumbled chips.
Top with cheese. Return
to
oven
and bake,
uncovered,
until
cheese melts. Garnish with shredded lettuce and sour cream, if so desired.

title: pineapple delight
directions: Melt margarine.
Beat egg in large bowl, then add sugar, beating until creamy.
Add hot margarine.
Stir until creamy. Fold in Cool Whip and pineapple until well blended.

title: frogmore stew
directions: Fill large kettle or Dutch oven with 2 gallons water.
Add sausage, lemons, onion, crab boil, salt and pepper.
Bring to a boil; simmer 45 minutes.
Add butter.
When butter has melted, add corn; cook for 5 minutes.
Add shrimp and cook for about 8 minutes or until shrimp are pink.
Drain liquid and serve on large platter.
Let each guest take some sausage and corn, then peel their own shrimp.
Serves 8 to 10.
Make once a month.

title: date pecan bars
directions: Cream margarine and sugar. Add eggs. Combine baking soda and water; add to mixture. Add salt and vanilla; mix well.
Add dates, cherries and pecans. Stir in flour. Spread onto cookie sheet. Bake at 300° for 25 to 30 minutes; cool. Cut into bars.

title: pound cake
directions: Cream shortening and sugar.
Add one egg at a time.
Add milk and flour to which baking powder has been added.
Add vanilla and lemon extract last.
Use a stem pan, greased and floured.
Place in cold oven.
Turn to 350° and bake 1 hour and 15 minutes.
Do not open oven.

title: macaroni loaf
directions: Cook macaroni; drain and rinse in cold water.
Add other ingredients.
Bake in well-greased pan for 45 to 60 minutes.
Turn out on platter; serve plain or with tomato or mushroom sauce.

title: elephant stew
directions: Cut the elephant into small bite size pieces. (Reserve trunk; you will need something in which to store the pieces.) This will take about 6 months.
Add enough brown gravy to cover. Cook over kerosene fire about 3 months at 600°.
This will serve 3,867 people. If more are expected, 2 rabbits may be added. Do this only if necessary as most people do not care to find hare in their stew.

title: chicken casserole no. 4
directions: Cook
chicken
in
water until tender.
Cool and remove skin. Slice
thin
and refrigerate.
Cook broccoli and cut in bite size pieces.
In double boiler, blend milk, cream cheese, salt and garlic salt; stir in 3/4 cup Parmesan cheese.
Place broccoli
and sliced
chicken
in
layers; top with remaining cheese.
Bake
for
minutes.
Garnish with onion rings and bake 10 additional minutes.

title: quick chili con carne
directions: Saute ground beef and onion on medium heat 15 minutes.
Add the rest of the ingredients except the beans; mix well and cover. Simmer 15 to 20 minutes.
Add kidney beans and simmer 15 minutes longer.

title: apple nut torte cake
directions: Beat eggs hard.
Add sugar.
Beat well.
Add oil and vanilla and beat.
Add dry ingredients.
Add one can of drained pie apples (sliced and packed in water).
Add 1/2 cup walnuts.
Bake 1 hour at 350° in 9 x 13-inch pan.
Serve with Cool Whip on top.

title: brownies
directions: Beat eggs. Add sugar, beating well.
Add oil, cocoa and vanilla. Add flour and mix well. Stir in nuts.
Pour batter in greased 8 x 8 x 2-inch pan. Bake in preheated oven for 25 minutes at 325°.

title: stuffed mushrooms
directions: Preheat oven to 400°.
Soak in mixing bowl.
Chop stems and add to crumbs, garlic, parsley, salt, pepper, eggs and Ricotta cheese. Blend well and stuff mushrooms.
Place on greased baking dish.
Put some oil and Parmesan cheese on mushrooms.
Bake 20 minutes.

title: cornbread broccoli casserole
directions: Mix all ingredients together and bake at 350° until brown.

title: broccoli and cauliflower salad
directions: Mix all of the ingredients together.

title: porcupines
directions: Mix all ingredients (except tomatoes) together.
Shape into balls.
Place in baking dish previously sprayed with nonstick spray.
Cover with tomatoes and bake in 350° oven until done, about 1 hour.

title: macaroni supper casserole
directions: Heat oven to 400°.
Combine all ingredients, using 1 cup cheese.
Pour into 1 1/2-quart casserole dish.
Sprinkle with remaining cheese.
Bake 20 minutes.
Makes 6 servings.

title: orange pork chops
directions: Trim fat from pork chops.
Brown in oil.
Sprinkle with salt and pepper.
Add orange juice, sugar, cinnamon and cloves.
Cover and simmer 45 minutes.
Add cornstarch dissolved in a little orange juice.
Heat until bubbling and clear.
Serves 4.

title: low calorie mini pizza
directions: Brown meat, drain and put meat back in skillet and add seasonings and cheese.
Stir until melted.
Put on bread and top with halved olives.
Bake at 400° for 10 minutes.
The pizzas can be frozen and baked later.

title: red lobster rolls
directions: Prepare Bisquick rolls as directed.
Add grated cheese and garlic to Bisquick mixture.
Bake at 350° until golden brown. When just out of oven, pour melted butter over top.

title: layered taco dip
directions: Use platter with 1-inch sides.
Spread refried beans on platter.
Mash avocados in blender with lemon juice.
Spread on beans.
Mix sour cream, mayonnaise and taco seasoning together in bowl; spread on top of avocados.
Sprinkle tomatoes, chilies and olives over sour cream.
Top with shredded Cheddar.
Refrigerate; can be made a day ahead.

title: canyon casserole
directions: Heat oven to 400.
Grease 8 inch square glass baking dish. Brown ground beef in a large skillet over medium-high heat until thoroughly cooked, stirring frequently.
Drain.
Add tomatoes, corn, water, and taco seasoning mix.
Mix well.
Bring to a boil, stirring occasionally.
Pour into the greased baking dish.
In a small bowl, combine corn meal mix, milk, oil, and egg.
Blend well.
Stir in cheese.
Pour batter over ground beef mixture in baking dish.
Bake at 400 for 30 to 35 minutes or until the topping is golden brown.

title: old fashion candy
directions: Boil milk, sugar and butter 8 minutes. Add other ingredients and beat. Pour into dish and cool.

title: chicken and spaghetti casserole
directions: Cook chicken and take meat off bones.
Cook spaghetti.
Brown onion.
Add tomatoes.
Add Worcestershire sauce, salt, pepper and bay leaf.
Add chicken broth.
Cook down about 10 minutes. Thicken a little with flour and broth.
Let this simmer about 30 minutes.
Add chicken and heat through.
Then add mushrooms and olives, if desired.
Butter baking dish.
Cover bottom with spaghetti which has been cooked.
Add alternately layers of chicken, spaghetti and grated cheese.
Dot with butter.
Bake at 350° about 20 or 30 minutes.

title: super slimmer soup
directions: Bring to a boil.
Simmer 30 minutes to 1 hour.
Great warmed up.
Equals unlimited vegetables.

title: sugar-free lime jello salad
directions: Mix Jell-O according to directions on box.
Let set until thickened, but not set firm.
Add the rest of the ingredients.

title: fried cabbage
directions: Fry bacon slices.
Remove from grease and crumble bacon. Alternate layers of cabbage, onion, green pepper and crumbled bacon until skillet is full.
(Put this in bacon grease.)
Cook covered until cabbage is wilted and pepper and onion are done. Stir occasionally.

title: southern-fried chicken strips
directions: Combine milk and yogurt.
Add chicken strips, toss to mix. Combine dry ingredients on piece of wax paper.
Put 1/4 inch oil into skillet and heat to 325°.
Add evenly coated chicken, avoiding overcrowding skillet.
Cook until browned on bottom. Turn to brown other side.
Remove from oil to drain.
Serve immediately.

title: chicken adobo(filipino)
directions: Add salt, minced garlic, pepper and bay leaf to the chicken. Put in a kettle and add vinegar and water.
Cover and cook until chicken is tender and liquid has practically evaporated.
(You may add 2 tablespoons soy sauce after liquid has evaporated and mix).

title: hamburg pie
directions: Can also add corn or mixed vegetables if desired.

title: mom's fish bisque
directions: Saute onion and celery in margarine.
Add remaining ingredients.
Cook to a boil.
Lower flame; cover and simmer for 30 minutes.
Add fish fillets, cut into chunks.
Cook until fish is white and flaky.

title: fresh tomato basil tart
directions: Spread pie crust in 10-inch tart pan.
Preheat oven to 400°. Evenly brush mustard over the bottom of pastry.
Top the mustard with all the Mozzarella slices, covering the bottom.
Starting at the outer edge of shell, make a layered overlapping row of tomato slices.
Make a second row and continue until top is covered. Sprinkle herbs and garlic evenly over top.
Season to taste with salt and pepper.
Drizzle oil evenly on top.
Put tart on baking sheet and bake at 400° for 40 minutes.

title: rum sausages
directions: Heat together with a lump of butter until butter is melted the rum, soy sauce and brown sugar.
Do not boil.
Add sausages, cut into thirds.
Soak for at least 1 hour before serving warm.

title: million dollar pie
directions: Combine first 5 ingredients, then fold in whipping cream.
Put in a vanilla wafer crust.

title: elephant stew
directions: Cut elephant into bite sized pieces, this should take about 5 days.
Add enough brown gravy to cover.
Cook over a kerosene fire for about 4 days.
Add vegetables and simmer for a 1/2 day. Serves about 1,800 people.
If more are expected, add rabbits, finely chopped.
Stir well, as most people do not like to find a hare in their stew.

title: chicken casserole
directions: Heat soup, milk and 1 cup cheese.
Mix all ingredients, except 1/2 cup cheese, in casserole.
Sprinkle cheese on top.
Bake for 30 minutes at 300°.

title: brownies
directions: Mix
ingredients together.
Add pecans to mixture last. Bake at 350° for 35 minutes in pan greased with oil.
Cut into squares when cool.

title: eggplant parmigiana
directions: Saute onion and garlic in margarine until golden brown.
Stir in tomatoes, tomato juice, sugar, salt, oregano, basil and pepper. Bring to a boil.
Reduce heat and simmer, uncovered, 10 minutes. Wash eggplant; cut crosswise into 1/2-inch thick slices.
Combine flour and seasonings.
Use to coat eggplant.
Saute eggplant slices in 2 tablespoons hot oil or microwave 8 minutes.

title: fruit roll
directions: Mix all ingredients well and shape into two rolls.
Wrap in foil and chill.
Cut in slices to serve.

title: cranberry salad
directions: Mix jello according to directions. Add other ingredients and chill overnight.

title: oatmeal cake
directions: Cook oatmeal and water until done; let cool. Mix remaining ingredients and oatmeal.
Bake at 350° for 30 to 35 minutes in loaf pan.

title: sour cream raisin bars
directions: Cook the raisins in small amount of water for 10 minutes. Drain and cool.

title: hush puppies
directions: Combine all ingredients and add enough sweet milk to make a stiff batter that will drop from a spoon.

title: crab delightful rice
directions: To the cooked rice, add dill, seasoning salt, black pepper, garlic powder and margarine.
Put seasoned rice into 9 x 13-inch glass baking pan.
Top with imitation crab.
Sprinkle with paprika.
Top with loosely wrapped Saran Wrap.
Heat in microwave about 10 minutes or until crab is heated through.
Rotate pan once during heating.

title: spaghetti sauce
directions: Brown hamburger meat in skillet with 1 tablespoon oil.
Add chopped onion, bell pepper and simmer for 10 minutes.
Drain grease off meat and put in pot.
Add remaining ingredients; let sauce boil, then cook slowly for 3 hours (stir frequently).

title: mulled cider
directions: Place cider and spices in saucepan.
Bring just to a boil; strain.
Serve hot or cooled.
Makes about 4 cups or 6 servings.

title: diabetic pecan pie
directions: Mix all ingredients.
Pour into unbaked crust.
Bake at 350° until done.

title: cool and cream cucumber salad
directions: In medium-sized bowl, combine all ingredients except cucumbers; mix thoroughly.
Toss cucumber slices in dressing and marinate 3 to 4 hours in refrigerator.

title: baked zucchini
directions: Peeled or unpeeled, cut zucchini into 1/4-inch slices and parboil in salted water for 5 minutes.
Drain and place in casserole in layers of zucchini, crumbs and cheese.
Bake 20 minutes at 325° to 350°.

title: key lime pie
directions: Combine condensed milk, cream cheese, vanilla and lime juice and blend to a creamy texture.
Pour into pie shells and chill for one hour.
Garnish with sliced limes around outside of pie shell. Can also grate lime to sprinkle color over top.
May also add a dollop or two of whipped cream to sweeten tartness.
Makes 2 pies. Keep refrigerated.

title: hummingbird cake
directions: Mix all ingredients together and bake in Bundt pan at 350° for 1 hour.

title: shrimp creol
directions: Saute onions, celery, parsley, and bell pepper until tender. Add water, tomatoes, tomato sauce, and garlic.
Simmer 5 minutes, add worcestershire sauce, smoked hot sauce and salt.
Cook mixture 30 minutes.
Add shrimp and cook 30 minutes more or until shrimp is done and mixture is thick.
Serve over rice.

title: southern sweet potato pecan bread
directions: Sift dry ingredients together.
Cream the sugar and eggs and add to dry ingredients.
Add vegetable oil and milk and blend. Add sweet potatoes, nuts and raisins and blend.
Bake in loaf pan that has been greased on bottom only for 1 hour and 8 to 10 minutes in a 325° oven.
Cool 15 minutes.
Take from pan and cool before slicing.

title: strawberry pie
directions: Mix together first 3 ingredients and cool (15 minutes) then add jello.
Cool and add strawberries.
Pour into baked pie shell and chill 2 to 3 hours.
Top with whipped cream.

title: robin's tuna burgers
directions: Split and butter 6 hamburger buns.
Fill bun with tuna mixture and replace the top of the bun.
Wrap in foil and place on a cookie sheet. Bake at 350° for 15 minutes. Very good.

title: potato soup
directions: Brown bacon and onion; drain.
Crumble bacon.
Cook potatoes in small amount of water until tender.
Mix all ingredients, except cheese.
Cook until heated thoroughly.
Do not boil.
Add cheese and cook until melted.
Season to taste.
You can add more milk if needed.

title: lasagna
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
Brown hamburger, adding oregano and garlic to taste.
Drain.
Add tomato sauce and tomato paste. Stir and simmer. Boil egg noodles until limp. Drain noodles.
Add chopped onion, cottage cheese and sour cream.
Mix well.
In a 13 x 9-inch baking dish, layer half the meat sauce, then the noodles and top with remaining meat sauce.
Sprinkle Mozzarella cheese on top and bake at 350° for 30 minutes.

title: waffles
directions: Spray waffle iron.
Mix ingredients in order.
Pour mixture on waffle iron.
Cook until golden brown.

title: chicken rice dressing
directions: Mix all ingredients in large bowl until well blended.
Heat oven to 325°.
Put rice mixture in baking dish and heat 30 to 40 minutes or until heated throughout.

title: surprise cupcakes
directions: Make cake according to directions.
Fill cupcake pans 2/3 full with batter.
Cream cheese with egg, sugar and salt.
Stir in chocolate chips.
Drop one rounded teaspoonful of cheese mixture into cake mixture in each cupcake.
Bake 15 to 20 minutes at 350°. Makes 30 to 36 cupcakes.

title: auntie dear's cream pie
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.

Combine sugar, flour and salt in a large bowl. Add corn syrup and blend thoroughly. Beat the eggs lightly and add then to the sugar mixture. Stir to blend. Add the evaporated milk and stir until well blended. Add the vanilla and pecans; mix well. Pour the filling into the crust and bake for 1 hour or until the filling is set and browned. However, do not overcook because the filling becomes grainy.

title: meat loaf
directions: Mix all ingredients thoroughly.
Put in loaf pan and pour over top one 8-ounce can tomato sauce.
Bake 1 hour at 350°.

title: zucchini with pecans
directions: Coat skillet with cooking spray.
Saute zucchini in oil until crisp-tender.
Add remaining ingredients, tossing gently.
Yield: 2 servings.

title: fruit cobbler
directions: Put berries or fruit in an 8 x 12 x 2-inch baking dish. Sprinkle lemon juice over the fruit.
Cream together the butter, salt and sugar.
Beat at high speed until thoroughly mixed.
Sift together the flour and baking powder and alternate with the milk to
the creamed mixture.
After all flour and milk have been added, beat until firm.
The dough will be thick and fluffy and will require about three minutes at high speed beating with an electric mixer.

title: corn casserole
directions: Beat eggs and add milk, margarine, cheese, salt, pepper and onion.
Mix in cream-style corn.
Bake for 40 to 45 minutes at 350°.

title: raisin bread pudding
directions: Preheat oven to 300°.
Remove any very dark crust from bread. Break bread into small cubes.
Combine 1 1/2 cups sugar, the milk, melted margarine, eggs and cinnamon.
Pour over cubed bread in a large bowl.
Transfer to a buttered 13 x 9-inch pan and bake 40 minutes at 300°.

title: chicken and broccoli casserole
directions: Grease square baking pan.
Preheat oven to 350°.
Cook broccoli in a skillet over low heat until it breaks apart.
Layer broccoli in bottom of pan.
Next, layer diced chicken.
Spread prepared stuffing on top of this.
Top with two cans of mushroom soup. Spread Velveeta and Cheddar cheese on top.
Bake at 350° for 20 to 30 minutes.

title: carrot cake
directions: Combine sugar and oil; beat in eggs.
Sift dry ingredients together; add to mixture.
Bake at 350° for 30 minutes or until shrinks from pan.

title: cherries jubilee
directions: Mix
flour, margarine and nuts and put in 13
x
9-inch pan. Bake 30 minutes at 325°.
Cool completely.	Beat
cream cheese, powdered sugar and vanilla for 2 minutes.
Fold in 1/2 of large Cool Whip.	Spread on crust and then put
pie filling on and cover with remainder of Cool Whip.

title: gram's quick fix meal
directions: Cook macaroni (no salt) per package directions.
Place meat in large skillet over low heat; cover and cook until red disappears and drain off liquid.
Add remaining ingredients, except macaroni, and let simmer for short time until flavor is blended, stirring a few times.
Add drained macaroni and mix well.
If mixture is too thick, add small amount of milk.
Serve hot.

title: smoked oyster dip
directions: Combine ingredients and mix well.
Serve with assorted crackers or chips.

title: blueberry buckle
directions: Cream margarine and sugar.
Add egg and beat well.
Add dry ingredients alternately with milk, beating after each addition. Pour into greased 9-inch square pan.
Sprinkle over with blueberries that have been washed and allowed to dry.

title: vegetable casserole
directions: Place cooked vegetables in a 1-quart casserole dish. Mix together rest of ingredients except the crumbs and pour over vegetables. Mix gently. Cover with Ritz crackers or seasoned bread crumbs and dot with butter.
Bake at 350° for 35 minutes.

title: lo-cal crispy chicken
directions: Dip the chicken breasts in skim milk and roll in corn flakes. Sprinkle with salt, pepper and sesame seed.
Bake at 400° for 15 to 20 minutes in a nonstick pan.
Serves 4.

title: deep dish turkey pie
directions: Cook celery in oleo.
Add dash of onion powder.
Stir in remaining ingredients, except Bisquick and water.
Bring to boil. Place in deep casserole.
Mix Bisquick and water.
Roll to fit top of dish.
Slit top; bake at 400° for 15 minutes.

title: sunday roast
directions: In roast pan, put roast in the middle.
Add chopped vegetables, then cover with cream of mushroom soup.
Set oven on 350°.
Cover and bake for 3 to 3 1/2 hours.

title: chicken elegante
directions: Place
contents of seasoning packet, water and 2 tablespoons margarine
in
large bowl. Add stuffing;
stir to moisten.	Let stand
until
water
is
absorbed.	Cook
and
stir chicken
in remaining margarine until lightly browned, about 5 minutes.
Place chicken
in
baking dish; top each piece with stuffing.
Mix gravy, mushrooms and wine.	Pour over stuffing. Cover and bake at 350° for 30 minutes.

title: black forest cherry jubilee
directions: Prepare cake mix by package directions; cook in sheet cake pan.
Cut cake into small pieces.
Alternate layers in trifle bowl or punch bowl, starting with cake, pudding, cherries and Dream Whip, until reaching top of bowl.
Finish with 1 layer of Dream Whip; garnish with cherries.

title: snickerdoodles
directions: Mix margarine, sugar and eggs thoroughly.
Sift together the flour, cream of tartar, baking soda and salt.
Stir into margarine mixture.
Roll into small balls.
Roll balls in a mixture of 2 tablespoons sugar and 1 teaspoon cinnamon.
Place 2 inches apart on ungreased cookie sheet.
Bake until lightly browned, but still soft.
Cookies puff up at first, then flatten out.
Bake 8 to 10 minutes in preheated 400° oven.

title: sopaipillas
directions: Combine dry ingredients.
Cut in shortening.
Dissolve yeast in warm water and scalded milk (be sure milk has cooled down before putting into yeast).
Make well in dry ingredients.
Add liquid to dry ingredients and work into the dry ingredients.
Work into dough.
Knead dough for 15 or 20 minutes.
Set aside for approximately 10 minutes.
Roll dough to 1/4-inch thick or less. Cut into squares or triangles and deep fry in melted shortening. If too hot, they will puff and become hollow shortly after adding to fat.
Drain on paper towel.
May take a little more flour to knead better.

title: glazed carrots
directions: Cook 3 to 4 carrots; cut crosswise in 1-inch pieces.
Add butter, brown sugar (packed) and grated lemon rind and juice to taste.
Heat slow, stirring occasionally, until nicely glazed, about 15 minutes.
Makes 2 to 3 servings.

title: pink punch
directions: In saucepan, bring water and sugar to boil for 5 minutes.
Add pineapple juice and lemon juice.
Pour into ice cube trays and freeze.
Mix frozen juice with pop, colada mix and strawberry pop. Blend well.

title: good brownies
directions: Mix sugar, cocoa and flour. Add melted margarine, eggs and vanilla. Add pecans and
chocolate chips. Pour in a greased oblong baking pan and bake at 350 degrees until done.

title: orange cake
directions: Drain mandarin oranges and put them in with the cake mix. Make according to box directions.
Use liquid from oranges and water to make amount of liquid needed.
Bake in a 9 x 13-inch pan. Cool.

title: oatmeal cookies
directions: Beat together 1/2 cup shortening, 1 1/4 cups sugar, 1/2 cup molasses and two eggs.
Sift together and add 1 3/4 cups sifted flour, salt, soda and cinnamon.
Stir in two cups of oatmeal and 1 1/2 cups raisins.
Drop by teaspoonful, 2 inches apart.
Bake for 12 to 15 minutes in oven at 375°.

title: pepper jelly and pecan spread
directions: Mix cheese, onions, mayo and pecans.
Roll into desired shape.
Refrigerate for 2 hours or until firm or ready to serve. Pour pepper jelly of choice on top and serve with snack crackers.

title: old fashioned sweet dough pie crust
directions: Sift together flour, salt and baking powder; set aside.
Cream sugar, Crisco and eggs together.
Combine with flour mixture alternately with milk, mixed with vanilla.
Roll 1/2 to 1-inch thick.
Spoon figs or other preserves on 1/2 dough.
Fold over and flute edges.
Bake at 350° until golden brown.

title: broiled lemon chicken sandwiches with garlic mayonnaise
directions: Place garlic in small saucepan.
Cover with water and bring to a boil.
Reduce heat.
Cook for 25 minutes.
Drain; slip skins off. Mash and mix with mayonnaise, lemon zest and pepper.
Refrigerate until ready to use.
Preheat broil or ready outdoor grill.
Cut breasts in half lengthwise, removing center cartilage.
Fan out the little fillet on the underside of each breast and lay flat on baking sheet.

title: chili soup
directions: Cook and stir meat, onion and salt until meat is brown.
Stir in remaining ingredients.
Heat to boil.

title: chocolate biscuits
directions: Mix ingredients with enough water to make biscuits as usual. Bake at 350° until brown.

title: chicken-n-rice and then some!
directions: Boil chicken with water and seasoning salt.
When the meat falls off the bone, it's done.
Remove from broth to cool.
Add rice to broth and let boil for 10 minutes.
Separate meat into small pieces and return it to the pot.
Cook on low for 10 minutes longer.
Remove from heat; let stand 5 minutes before serving.

title: sauce
directions: Mix together and cook for 1 minute.
This is very good over cake or ice cream.

title: rhubarb upside-down cake
directions: Beat egg yolks until thick.
Add 1/2 cup sugar and beat.
Add boiling water, then fold in remaining cup of sugar.
Add flour, salt and baking powder.
Beat well and fold in egg whites.
Place cut up rhubarb in buttered pan.
Pour batter over rhubarb and bake at 350° for 45 minutes.

title: egg salad
directions: Mix all ingredients; add a little more mayonnaise, if desired. Chill.
For a great lunch sandwich, spread egg salad on whole wheat bread.

title: taco pizza
directions: Lay crescent rolls on cookie sheet, in a flat crust.
Bake at 375° for 10 minutes.
Cool.
Combine remaining ingredients and spread over cooled crust.
Sprinkle with chopped tomatoes, peppers, black olives, sweet onion, shredded carrots, Cheddar cheese, etc. Cover with plastic wrap and refrigerate overnight.
Cut into squares and serve.

title: beverly's pumpkin bread
directions: Mix all ingredients in a mammoth bowl.
Bake at 350° for 1 hour and 15 minutes.
Makes 2 loaves.

title: florida's lightest orange cake
directions: With electric mixer, beat whites at medium speed until foamy. Gradually beat in 1/2 cup sugar, beating after each addition until stiff peaks form. Set aside.

title: cinnamon rolls
directions: Combine 1 1/2 cups flour and yeast.
Heat milk, sugar, 1/4 cup butter and salt until warm (120° to 130°), stirring constantly. Add to flour; add eggs.
Beat on low for 30 seconds.
Beat on high for 3 minutes.
Stir in and knead in rest of the flour (5 minutes total).
Place dough in greased bowl; turn once.
Cover; let rise until double (1 to 1 1/2 hours).
Punch down; divide in half.
Let rest, covered, for 10 minutes.
On floured surface, roll half dough to 12 x 8-inch rectangle.
Spread with 3 tablespoons softened butter.
Combine brown sugar and cinnamon; sprinkle half over rectangle.
Roll up from a short side.
Make a second roll. Slice each roll into 8 pieces.
Arrange in greased 13 x 9-inch pan.
Cover and let rise about 30 minutes (or refrigerate and bake in morning).
Bake at 350° for 25 to 30 minutes.
Mix powdered sugar, vanilla and milk together and glaze.

title: meat loaf
directions: Mix 1/2 cup mushroom soup, onion soup mix, beef, crumbs and egg.
Firmly shape into loaf.
Bake at 350° for 1 hour and 15 minutes.
Spoon off fat, reserve 1 to 2 tablespoons of drippings.

title: sweet potato casserole
directions: Mix all of the ingredients completely and place in a greased oblong baking dish.

title: boiled raisin cake
directions: Boil sugar, water, lard, raisins and spices for 5 minutes. When cool, add remaining ingredients.
Beat well and pour into a well-greased and floured 9 x 13-inch pan.
Bake at 350° for 40 minutes.

title: homemade ice cream
directions: Beat egg whites.
Add together all else except regular milk. Fold in egg whites. Add regular milk to finish filling freezer.

title: refrigerator cole slaw
directions: Shred cabbage and onion. Put salad oil, vinegar, sugar, mustard and celery seed in small saucepan; bring to boil to dissolve the sugar. While hot, pour mixture over the cabbage. DO NOT STIR for 24 hours. Place in the refrigerator when cool. After 24 hours, stir and keep refrigerated. Will keep for weeks.

title: linguini with shrimp
directions: Bring water to a boil.
Add pasta when you begin to stir-fry vegetables.
In a wok or large, heavy skillet, stir-fry onion, bell peppers, chiles and oregano with olive oil or chicken broth over medium-high heat until tender to bite (about 5 minutes).
Add pea pods and continue to stir-fry about 2 minutes more.
Add shrimp and remove from heat.
Cook pasta until tender to bite (6 to 8 minutes); drain.
Mix into skillet of vegetables and add Parmesan.
Serve with additional Parmesan.
tags: sprinkling of crushed dried hot red chiles

title: instant rice pudding
directions: Combine all ingredients except eggs, and vanilla.
Bring to boil, stirring constantly.
Reduce heat; boil 15 minutes.
Slowly pour hot mixture into eggs, a little at a time, beating vigorously.
Add vanilla, sprinkle with nutmeg.
Let cool.

title: cream of carrot soup
directions: In a large saucepan, melt the butter over moderate heat.
Add the onion and saute until translucent, about 5 minutes.
Add the carrots and stock and simmer until the carrots are tender.
Puree the soup in a food processor or blender until smooth.
Return the soup to the saucepan and stir in the orange juice concentrate and cream.
Cook just until heated through and season with salt to taste.
Serve hot or cold with parsley or mint.
Serves 4 to 6.

title: shrimp scampi
directions: Heat oil in large skillet over medium heat.
Add diced red pepper and cook 3 to 4 minutes.
Add shrimp, garlic and salt. Cook turning shrimp once for 5 minutes.
Remove from heat and stir in parsley, butter and lemon juice.

title: fruit salad
directions: Mix together; chill before serving.
Add any fruit if you would like to a have a larger salad assortment.

title: old fashioned brownies
directions: Melt oleo; mix the remaining ingredients in with the oleo. Pour into a greased and floured 13 x 9-inch pan.
Bake at 350° for 30 to 35 minutes.

title: creole fried oysters
directions: In a deep bowl, mix well, the egg, ketchup, Worcestershire, tabasco, black pepper, red pepper, and garlic powder.
Soak oysters in sauce for 1 hour and refrigerate.
Roll oysters in cornmeal and fry in oil until golden brown.
Yield:
4 servings.

title: velvet waffles
directions: Sift flour.
Measure.
Resift 3 times with baking powder, salt and

title: lazy day cobbler
directions: Mix sugar, flour and milk in bowl.
Melt butter and pour in a 13 x 9-inch cake pan.
Pour mixture of sugar, flour and milk. Next pour in fruit.
Do not stir. Bake at 350° for 45 minutes.

title: rice casserole
directions: In a saucepan put oil, water, Savorex and broth in mushroom soup and bring to a boil.
Stir to dissolve Savorex.
Pour over rest of ingredients in baking dish and mix well.
Cover and bake at 350° for 1 hour.

title: kentucky burgoo
directions: In a pot, combine 2 tablespoons bacon fat, beef and veal. Cook until browned.
Add chicken, water and salt.
Cover; cook slowly until tender.
Remove meat and chicken.
Discard bones and cut meat and chicken into fairly large pieces.
Return chicken and meat to broth.
In a frying pan, combine remaining fat and onions. Cook until tender; add to broth.
Add garlic, potatoes, celery, tomatoes, carrots, green pepper, beans, red pepper, onion with cloves, bay leaf, brown sugar and pepper.
Cook slowly, stirring occasionally for 2 hours.
Add okra and corn; cook for 15 minutes. In a bowl, combine butter and flour. Blend into burgoo. Sprinkle with parsley.
Serves 10.

title: fudge
directions: Mix chips and milk.
Heat until chips are melted.
Add vanilla.
Line 8 x 8-inch pan with wax paper.
Chill until firm.

title: coconut kisses
directions: Beat egg whites with dash of salt and vanilla to soft peaks; gradually add sugar and beat until stiff.
Stir in cereal, coconut and nuts.
Drop from teaspoon onto well-greased cookie sheet. Bake at 350° for 18 to 20 minutes.
Remove cookies immediately.

title: apple crisp
directions: Butter an
8 x 8-inch pan.
Mix together in pan first 4 ingredients.
Mix
together flour, oats, sugar, salt and soda; cut into flour mixture 6 tablespoons butter.
Crumble consistency, sprinkle over apples.
Scatter 1/4 cup nuts on top and press lightly.
Bake at 350° for 1 hour.

title: apple crisp
directions: Heat oven to 375°.
Grease square cake pan.
Place apples in pan.
Mix remaining ingredients thoroughly.
Sprinkle over apples. Bake 25 to 30 minutes.

title: vegetable dip
directions: Mix in bowl.
Chill 2 hours.
Serve with raw carrot sticks, cauliflower, broccoli or any raw vegetable.

title: sweet potato pie
directions: Mix all ingredients and cook on top of stove until thick. Pour into cooked pie shell.
Top with meringue.

title: little meat loaves
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
In a large bowl, combine the eggs, cracker crumbs, milk, cheese, onion, 1 tsp. Worcestershire sauce, italian seasoning, garlic salt, ground beef and sausage.
Mix together well and form into individual loaves.
Place loaves in 9 x 13-inch baking dish.

title: kentucky pound cake
directions: Beat egg whites first and set aside.
Mix flour, sugar, oil and pineapple together.
Add egg yolks, cinnamon and hot water. Fold in egg whites and nuts.
Pour into greased and floured tube pan.
Bake 1 hour and 10 minutes at 325°.

title: angel surprise
directions: In small mixing bowl, gradually blend milk into cream cheese, beating until smooth.
Add pudding mix and beat at low speed until smooth and slightly thickened, about 2 minutes.

title: chicken fettuccine
directions: Spray a large nonstick frying pan with nonfat cooking spray. Saute the onion and garlic in chicken broth.
Add chicken and saute about 7 minutes or until the chicken is cooked.
Add the zucchini and mushrooms.
Saute until tender.
Add the fettuccine and milk.
Sprinkle the cheese on top and mix well.
Yields 6 to 8 servings.
Calories 220 (8% calories from fat), fat 2 g, protein 23 g, cholesterol 44 mg, carbohydrate 26 g, fiber 2
and sodium 257 mg.

title: punch
directions: Mix all but the ginger ale.
Just before serving add the ginger ale.

title: frito salad
directions: Mix all ingredients thoroughly and use as a dip for Fritos.

title: cherry supreme(8 servings)
directions: Tear angel food cake into small pieces; set aside.
In a large bowl, beat powdered sugar and cream cheese until smooth.
Prepare the Dream Whip in accordance with package directions.
Mix the Dream Whip, cream cheese mixture and cake pieces.
Press into a square cake pan (8 x 8-inch or 9 x 9-inch).
Top with cherry pie filling.
Chill before serving.

title: no bake cookies
directions: Combine sugar, cocoa, oleo and milk.
Bring to boil and boil for one minute.
Take off heat and add peanut butter and vanilla. Stir, then add oatmeal.
Stir well and drop from teaspoon onto waxed paper.

title: mexican meat loaf
directions: Cook and drain hamburger.
Mix and add all other ingredients to hamburger except chips and cheese.
Place chips in bottom of baking pan.
Pour hamburger mixture over chips and cover with grated cheese.
Bake in a 350° to 375° oven for about 15 minutes or until cheese melts and is bubbly. Good served with salad, corn and extra chips.

title: miller's special sausage
directions: Grind all together and stuff casings or make patties.
Cut and prick casings with a fork and roast in oven, then process.
Put grease in cans that fries out while roasting.

title: super spud casserole
directions: Place hash browns (partially thawed) in casserole dish.
I break mine into pieces.
Mix all other ingredients together and pour over the potatoes.
Sprinkle with Parmesan cheese.
Bake at 350° for 45 minutes.

title: crab bites
directions: Combine all ingredients.
Put on slices of toast rounds. Broil for 3 minutes at 350°.

title: blueberry delight
directions: Layer as follows.
Do not grease dish.

title: persimmon pudding
directions: Cream butter and sugar together.
Add the persimmon pulp and egg.
Then add the dry ingredients, flour, soda, baking powder, salt and cinnamon.
Add raisins, nuts and vanilla and cook 30 minutes at 375°.

title: quick and easy nachos
directions: In saucepan or microwave oven, heat refried beans.
In pan, fry hamburger and add taco seasoning according to directions on taco seasoning package.

title: crusty herbed cauliflower
directions: Cut cauliflower into medium-sized flowerets.
Cook in steamer basket over simmering water in covered saucepan for 15 to 18 minutes, or until tender.
Remove.

title: potato celery
directions: Combine potatoes, celery, onions, chicken stock, salt and pepper.
Cover and cook until tender, about 15 minutes.
Mix cornstarch with milk and add to vegetables.
Heat to just short of boiling.
Ladle into individual serving bowls.
Top each with a pat of butter and a sprinkling of grated cheese.
Makes 6 servings.

title: stuffed mushrooms
directions: Wash mushrooms thoroughly first.
Take out the stems and dice up.
Dice onion, celery and shrimp.

title: 7 layer salad
directions: Cut vegetables in small pieces.
Layer in order.
Mix Hellmann's and sugar.
Cover vegetables completely including edges of pan to seal mixture.
Top with cheese, eggs and bacon bits. Great with ham!!

title: creole lima beans
directions: Fry bacon.
Remove and brown onions.
Add bacon, onion and remaining ingredients to drained limas.
Simmer 10 minutes.
Serves 6.

title: crispy baked chicken
directions: Heat oven to 425°.
Heat margarine in 9 x 13 x 2-inch pan until melted.
Mix potatoes, cheese, salt and pepper.
Dip chicken into egg; roll in potato mixture.
Place skin side up in pan. (Chicken can be skinned.)
Bake uncovered about 50 minutes or until thickest pieces are done and coating is golden brown and crisp.
Makes 6 servings.

title: taco meat
directions: Brown meat and drain.
Mix all ingredients together and simmer on low for 25 to 30 minutes.
Put 1 to 2 tablespoons cooked meat into heated taco shell.
Top with cheese, onion, lettuce, taco sauce and tomatoes, whatever you like on your tacos.

title: easy whole wheat bread
directions: Using solid shortening generously grease two 9 x 5-inch or 8 x 4-inch loaf pans.
Lightly spoon flour into measuring cup.
Level off and combine dry ingredients in large mixing bowl.
Heat 2 1/4 cups milk and 1/4 cup cooking oil until very warm (120° to 130°). Add 1 egg and warm liquid to flour mixture.
Beat 1/2 minute at low speed, 3 minutes at medium speed.
By hand, gradually stir in 1 cup whole wheat flour and 3 to 4 cups unbleached all-purpose flour to form soft dough.
Knead on floured surface until smooth and elastic.
Place dough in greased bowl turning to grease all sides of dough.
Let rise until double, about 1 hour.
Punch down and shape into 2 loaves.
Let rise again 30 to 45 minutes.
Bake at 350° for 40 to 45 minutes.

title: danish meatballs
directions: Mix all ingredients except butter.
Blend well.
Bake 24 small balls.
Chill 4 hours and then fry in butter.
Serve hot.

title: chicken salad
directions: Cook chicken and cut in bite-size pieces.
Mix together with lettuce and onion.
Toast Sesame seeds and almonds and mix with chicken mixture.

title: buttermilk salad
directions: Bring jello and pineapple to a boil.
Let cool.
Beat with a mixer.
When very cool, add buttermilk.
Mix, then add Cool Whip and nuts.
Congeal.

title: chicken bundles
directions: Pound chicken breasts flat.
Marinate in barbecue sauce. Spread mushrooms and onions on chicken; wrap and fold over filling.
Wrap 2 bacon slices around chicken.
Secure bacon to chicken with toothpicks.
Broil until done.

title: hash brown casserole
directions: Defrost patties and mix with salt, pepper, soup, sour cream and diced onion.
Pat into 9 x 13-inch pan.
Poke holes with end of wooden spoon.
Pour stick of melted butter or margarine over top.
Sprinkle Durkee fried onions.
Bake at 350° for 35 to 40 minutes.

title: cheddar bagel nachos
directions: Place bagel chips on small plate.
Spread one to two teaspoons of pizza sauce on bagel chips, then sprinkle with cheese.
Microwave on HIGH for 45 seconds.

title: new year's pretzel
directions: Mix dry milk, sugar, salt and water.
Stir in mixing bowl. Stir in yeast until it dissolves.
Add eggs and shortening and stir in.
Add flour, cup by cup, beating in with mixer at high speed, until about half the flour is used.
Mix in remaining flour.
Knead until smooth.
Let rise until double.
Punch down and let rise again.
(If in haste, skip second rising).
Take half of dough and roll it to form a long strip and shape into a pretzel, twisting once at the center.
Repeat with remaining half. Bake about 20 minutes at 350°.
Remove from oven and brush with margarine.
Frost while still warm with thin powdered sugar and water frosting.
Sprinkle with chopped nuts or decorate with candied cherries, etc.

title: ice cream icing
directions: Beat egg white and 1 cup of sugar for 1 minute, then combine all ingredients and beat well until light and fluffy.
(Add 1/2 cup cocoa for chocolate or add peanut butter to taste.)

title: no-fuss meatballs
directions: In a skillet, cook meatballs in soy sauce until heated through on a slow fire. Combine chili sauce, jelly and mustard. Mix well. Pour into skillet with meatballs. Cook, stirring constantly, until jelly is melted and mixture comes to a boil. Reduce heat, cover and simmer for 1 to 2 minutes.

title: lemon dessert
directions: In a large bowl mix together the flour, nuts and margarine. Put into oblong pan.
Bake 15 minutes in 350° oven; cool.
Mix in the same bowl the powdered sugar, cream cheese and 1 cup of Cool Whip.
Put this on top of cooled crumb mixture.
Mix in the same bowl the pudding mix and milk.
Put this on top of cream cheese and let set.
Top with rest of Cool Whip; chill and serve cold.

title: sweet and sour wieners
directions: Mix jelly and mustard in a crock-pot; let jelly melt, then put sausage or wieners or both in the crock-pot and cook on high for about 2 to 3 hours.

title: italian stuffed shells
directions: Cook shells according to package directions.
In a large bowl, combine the Ricotta, Mozzarella, eggs, parsley, salt and pepper. Set aside.
In a 9 x 13-inch baking dish, pour in half of spaghetti sauce.
Spoon the cheese mixture into the cooked shells and place into dish, open side up.
Cover with remaining sauce and sprinkle with Parmesan.
Bake at 350° for 30 minutes.

title: crustless coconut pie
directions: Mix all ingredients together.
Bake at 350° for 45 minutes or until brown and set.

title: baked rigatoni with sausage
directions: Preheat oven to 350°F.
In large saucepan, over medium heat, brown sausage;
pour off fat.
Add garlic;
cook and stir until tender.
Stir in spaghetti sauce and oregano.
Cover;
simmer 20 minutes.
Remove from heat;
stir in 1 1/2 cups cheese and cooked rigatoni.
Turn into a greased 13x9-inch baking dish;
cover. Bake 35 minutes or until hot and bubbly.
Uncover;
top with remaining 1 1/2 cups cheese and parsley.
Bake 8 to 10 minutes longer or until cheese melts.
Refrigerate leftovers.

title: fast pizza
directions: Split muffins.
Spread with sauce, then add cheese and toppings.
Place in broiler for 3 to 5 minutes.
Can be done in microwave.

title: mulled cider
directions: Combine ingredients in slow cooking pot.
Cover and heat on low for 2 to 5 hours.
Serve from pot.
Makes 10 to 12 servings.

title: peanut butter fudge
directions: Boil the sugar, milk and butter slowly for 8 minutes, until it makes soft ball stage.
Remove from fire.
Stir in the peanut butter and marshmallow cream.
Stir until smooth, then add the vanilla and flour.
Pour quickly into 9 x 13-inch pan.
Set, then cut.

title: hot fudge for chocolate sundae
directions: Melt chocolate.
Add remaining ingredients except vanilla. Boil for 5 minutes; add vanilla.

title: beet salad
directions: Drain beets reserving liquid in saucepan.
Add vinegar, sugar, mustard, garlic and bay leaf.
Bring to boil.
Remove from heat. Place beets, onion and parsley in non-metallic container.
Pour hot liquid over mixture.
Cover and chill.

title: chile relleno casserole
directions: Grate and mix cheeses together.
Layer chiles and cheese in baking dish.
Beat eggs and combine with milk, salt, pepper and flour.
Pour over chiles and cheeses.
Bake at 350° for 45 minutes until mixture bubbles.
Serves 8 to 10.

title: pork chops and cabbage
directions: Brown chops in oil.
Remove from oil and set aside.
Combine onion, soup, milk, salt and pepper in pan and blend well.
Spray 2 quart casserole dish with Pam.
Place alternating layers of potatoes and cabbage.
Sprinkle each with flour.
Pour soup mixture over top.
Place pork chops on top and cover.
Bake at 350° for 1 hour 15 minutes.

title: light rolls
directions: Mix together lukewarm water, sugar and salt.
Add yeast that has been softened in warm water.
(It must be only warm.
Hot water will kill the yeast.)
Stir mixture.
Add eggs and shortening.
Mix first with spoon, then by hand.
Add potatoes and flour.
Knead until smooth.
Place in refrigerator.
About 2 hours before baking, make into rolls. Let rise until doubled in size. Bake in 400° oven for 12 to 15 minutes.

title: queen elizabeth cake
directions: Pour water over soda and dates.
Let stand while mixing remaining ingredients.
Add date mixture to batter, stirring well, and pour into a 9 x 13-inch baking dish.
Bake at 350° for 35 minutes.

title: strawberry pie
directions: Cook cornstarch, sugar and 7-Up until clear.
Cool.
Add red food coloring.
Add strawberries.
Pour into baked pie shell. Chill about 2 hours.
Garnish with whipped cream.

title: midwest cream cake
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
Grease and flour a 13 x 9 x 2-inch baking pan or two (8-inch) round pans.
In a large bowl, cream together sugar and butter; add sour cream, eggs and vanilla.
Sift together flour and baking powder and add to creamed mixture; beat well.
Pour into prepared pans.
Bake for 30 to 35 minutes or until cake tests done.

title: shake and bake
directions: Stir together and store in refrigerator.
Use for chicken and pork chops.

title: black bean brownies
directions: Beat margarine, sugar, cocoa and coffee.
Add eggs, one at a time.
Beat in bean puree.
Stir in nuts.
Pour into 9 x 13-inch greased pan.
Bake at 350°
for 45 minutes for moist, fudgy brownies.
