If you like drier brownies, bake 5 to 10 minutes longer.
Cool completely in pan.
Cut into 1 1/2 x 2-inch bars. Serves 16.

title: mini buns
directions: Roll out dough and divide into two sections.
Ignore the diagonal perforations.
Cut each section into four thin rectangles, making sixteen strips.
Roll each strip up like a jelly roll and fit into tiny muffin cups (greased, if not Teflon). Brush with melted butter.
Bake at 375° about ten minutes.
Makes 16 Mini Buns.

title: onion-roasted potatoes
directions: Preheat oven to 450°.

title: banana pudding
directions: Mix first 4 ingredients well in a sauce pan over high heat, stirring constantly. Bring to a boil until thicken. In a round dish, layer graham crackers then bananas. Pour 1/2 of the mixture over bananas. Layer graham crackers and bananas again and pour over remaining mixture.

title: pineapple cake
directions: Cream butter and shortening with sugar.
Add vanilla and eggs, beating in eggs one at a time.
Mix well after each addition.
Add flour that has been sifted with baking powder and salt. Alternately add milk with the dry ingredients beginning with flour.
Blend well.
Blend in pineapple and mix well.
Pour batter into 3 greased and floured pans, 9-inch size.
Bake in preheated 350° oven for 30 minutes or until cake tests done.
Frost.

title: chicken curry
directions: Melt butter over low heat.
Saute onion and curry in butter. Blend in flour and seasonings; cook over low heat until mixture is smooth and bubbly.
Remove from heat.
Stir in broth and milk. Bring to a boil for 1 minute, stirring constantly.
Add chicken and lemon juice.
Heat.
Serve over rice and garnish.
Serves 4.

title: aunt evelyn's sweet lime pickles
directions: Mix.
Add cucumbers and heat until sugar dissolves.
Soak overnight, then boil 40 minutes.
Pack and seal.

title: fresh vegetable gumbo
directions: Drain all oil out of skillet, leaving just the pan drippings. Cut the heat on medium-high; add the flour and stir to combine well.
Slowly add the water, stirring constantly, until thickened. Add salt and pepper to taste.
Cut heat on low until served.
If gravy is too thick, add a little more water and stir well.
You won't get lumps in your gravy if you stir the flour in first with the drippings and then add the water and stir constantly.

title: liver pate
directions: Mash liverwurst with fork.
Add bacon, mayonnaise, Worcestershire sauce, Tabasco sauce, garlic powder, horseradish sauce, onion and 1 (8 ounce) package cream cheese.
Blend well and pack into 1 or 2 bowls lined with plastic wrap.
Chill until firm. Whip the other 8 ounce package softened cream cheese until fluffy and frost pates.

title: go to the shelf enchiladas
directions: Drain pork; discard all but 1 tablespoon of fat. Discard juice.
Saute chopped onion in fat.
Add smashed garlic.
Cook until tender.
Add meat; lower heat.
Mix in large bowl the sour cream, chilies, pimentos and spices.
Add meat mixture when fully heated.
Stir well.
Place 1/4 cup mixture in center of taco shell.
Fold end over to center, making like burrito shape.
Place in baking pan.
Can use toothpicks to hold together.
Pour enchilada sauce over top.
Sprinkle with cheese.
Bake at 350° for 20 minutes or until hot.

title: luscious dessert
directions: Mix well and press in bottom of a 9 x 14-inch baking dish. Bake about 10 or 15 minutes at 350°.
(Take out when it is a light brown.)

title: homemade chili for hot dogs
directions: Chop onion and brown in grease from hamburger meat, but brown meat first.
Add meat to onion.
Season with salt, pepper and chili powder.
Add 2 cans tomato sauce plus 2 cans of water.
Cook slowly over low heat for 2 to 3 hours.

title: potluck green salad
directions: Mix and chill.
Serve on lettuce with Ritz crackers or cheese balls.

title: lamb shanks
directions: Place all ingredients in crock-pot and cook on low heat 6 to 8 hours.
Serve with Major Grey chutney and rice.

title: cranberry sauce cake
directions: In mixing bowl, combine flour, sugar, mayonnaise, cranberry sauce, orange juice, orange peel, baking soda, salt and extract. Mix well.
Fold in walnuts.
Use a 10-inch tube pan.
Cut waxed paper to fit pan.
Spray pan, then line pan with paper and spray over paper.
Pour batter in pan.
Bake at 350° for 60 to 70 minutes or until tests done.
Cool 10 minutes in pan before removing to wire rack.

title: orange eggs
directions: Slice orange in half, clean out pulp and eat.
Break eggs into orange shell and place in coals until egg is finished.
Eat egg directly from shell.
Eggs really draw the orange flavor from the shell when cooking, quite a unique taste.

title: carrots with grapes and dill
directions: Cook carrots in large pot of boiling water for 8 to 10 minutes, until crisp-tender.
Drain.
Refrigerate in plastic bags if cooking early.
Bring to room temperature before proceeding. Heat butter in a large saucepan.
Add carrots and stir over medium heat until butter melts.
Stir in grapes and salt.
Cook 2 minutes or until hot.
Sprinkle with dill.
Makes 9 cups (12 servings).

title: marinated steak
directions: Combine all ingredients in bowl and mix well.
Transfer to a glass marinator dish.
Add steak.
Marinate up to 2 days in refrigerator.

title: yam yam sweet potatoes
directions: Mix and pour into butter dish.

title: chocolate pie
directions: Mix ingredients.
Pour in pie shells. Bake at 350° for 45 minutes.

title: fruit salad
directions: Drain fruit cocktail and crushed pineapple.
Mix pudding with juices.
Add fruit and pineapple to pudding.
Mix; stir in remaining ingredients.
Keep refrigerated.

title: bun bars(10 x 15-inch jelly roll pan)
directions: Melt chips and peanut butter together until blended.
Put 1/2 mixture in a greased 10 x 15-inch jelly roll pan.
Place in freezer to set up.
Stir peanuts into remaining chips-peanut butter mixture; set aside.
Melt margarine.
Add evaporated milk and dry pudding mix.
Boil 1 minute.
Remove from heat.
Add confectioners sugar and extract.
Let cool slightly.
Pour over first layer and return to freezer to set up.
Then pour remaining chip mixture over top.
Chill for 1/2 hour.
Cut into small squares.
Keep bars refrigerated or frozen.

title: pumpkin bread
directions: Sift flour, nutmeg, cinnamon, baking soda, soda, salt, sugar and cloves together.
Add oil, pumpkin, eggs and water.
Mix well. Then add dates and nuts.
Pour into 2 well oiled and floured pans (loaf).
Bake 1 1/2 hours in 325° oven.

title: orange julius
directions: Mix all together in a blender.
If orange juice is frozen, use only 9 cubes.

title: apple cake
directions: Beat oil, eggs and lemon juice together.
Add apples; set aside.
Combine sugar, flour, salt, soda, cinnamon and cloves; mix well.
Fold apple mixture into dry ingredients until dry ingredients are absorbed by apple mixture.
Pour into a 9 x 13-inch greased pan; bake at 350° for 40 minutes.
Serves 8 to 10.

title: macaroni and cheese casserole
directions: Combine ingredients.
Pour into baking dish and bake until thoroughly heated and pepper is soft.
If too dry, add a little cream or milk.

title: yogurt pie
directions: Fold together yogurt and Cool Whip. Spoon into crust. Freeze 4 hours or longer. Move to refrigerator 30 minutes before serving.

title: pineapple pie
directions: Mix cream cheese, lemon juice and sugar. Add pineapple, Cool Whip, milk and nuts. Fold together and put in baked pastry or graham cracker crusts. Makes 2.

title: black bean dip
directions: Pressure cook the beans and water for 1 hour.
While the beans are cooking, saute the onions and oil in a small skillet.
When the onions are soft and slightly browned, turn the flame to low and add the garlic powder and cumin.
Stir a few minutes and remove from heat.
When the beans are done, drain and save the liquid.
Mash the beans and add onions, 3/4 cup bean broth, vinegar, salt and hot sauce.
Mash well!
Top with cheese, guacamole, sour cream, etc.

title: zucchini bread
directions: Mix flour, salt, sugar, baking powder, soda and cinnamon together.
Beat eggs, oil, zucchini, orange rind and vanilla. Add to flour mixture. Add pecans and raisins.
Pour into well-greased loaf pan. Bake at 350° until done.
When cool, mix orange juice and confectioners sugar and pour over bread.

title: quick-and-easy refrigerator rolls
directions: In a large bowl, stir ingredients together in the order given. Cover and refrigerate dough at least 12 hours.
(Dough may be kept in refrigerator several days.)

title: cinnamon nut cake
directions: In a mixing bowl, combine the cake mix, eggs, water and oil. Beat on medium speed for 2 minutes.
Combine walnuts, sugar and cinnamon.
Sprinkle a third of the nut mixture into a greased 10-inch fluted tube pan.
Top with half of the batter and another third of the nut mixture.
Repeat layers.
Bake at 350° for 35 to 40 minutes or until a toothpick inserted near the center comes out clean.
Cool for 10 minutes before removing from pan to a wire rack to cool completely.
Yield: 12 to 14 servings.

title: mrs. o's cookies
directions: Stir together cream cheese and butter.
Blend in flour, kneading to form dough. Place in a bowl in refrigerator overnight or longer.

title: hominy casserole
directions: Heat hominy; do not boil.
Then drain and add Cheez Whiz, sour cream, pimentos and chiles.
Mix well; heat thoroughly, but do not boil.
Pour into your favorite casserole dish and serve!!
This is an excellent side dish.

title: tabooleh
directions: Soak burghul in water for 1/2 hour.
Chop everything very fine.
Drain burghul.
Mix together with juice and oil.

title: corn casserole
directions: Melt butter in a 9 x 12-inch dish.
Mix other ingredients and pour into dish.
Bake at 350° for 40 to 45 minutes.

title: chicken and rice supper
directions: Heat margarine or butter in a square pan until melted.
Stir in flour, salt and pepper.
Mix well, then add milk and broth; stir until it gets thick.
Combine all of the ingredients and pour into a 9 x 13-inch greased pan.
Bake, uncovered, at 350° for 30 minutes.

title: summer fruit salad
directions: Wash, dry and break spinach leaves and lettuce leaves into small pieces.
Arrange on salad plates with fruit slices on top. Top with toasted almonds.
May use fruit dressing or dressing of your choice.

title: johnny rossetti
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
Cook pasta according to directions. Brown hamburger until all pink is gone.
Stir in onions and cook until onions are cooked through.
Drain.
Using a large pot (approximately 8 quarts), put hamburger mixture in pot, over low heat.
Add can of soup, cream corn, and both cans of tomatoes.
Do not drain corn or tomatoes, and do not add water to soup!

title: chocolate sauce
directions: Combine
and
bring to a boil.	Cool and serve over ice cream or plain cake.
Serves 4.

title: fruit pizza pie
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
Cream butter and powdered sugar.
Add 1 cup flour to make a soft dough.
Pat evenly into pizza pan and bake for 15 minutes.
Remove from oven and spread pie filling over crust.
Combine cheese, flour, brown sugar and cinnamon.
Sprinkle over pie filling and return to oven and bake 30 minutes.
Serve warm.

title: applesauce cake
directions: Cream shortening and sugar.
Add egg, floured raisins, nuts and applesauce.
Add dry ingredients and vanilla.
Beat thoroughly.
Pour into greased and floured loaf pan and bake at 300° for 1 1/2 hours.
Candied fruit may also be used.

title: cranberry salad
directions: Cook cranberries in enough water to soften. Add sugar; cook, stirring constantly. When cool, add jello. Only use 1/2 as much water as called for. Mix and let jell.

title: shrimp dip
directions: Mix all ingredients together; chill and serve with cocktail rye bread.

title: broccoli cheese soup
directions: Saute onion in butter (but don't brown onion).
Add flour to butter mixture to form consistent batter.
Add remaining ingredients (except broccoli) and cook until well blended and thickened.
Add broccoli.

title: chicken pot pie ii
directions: Mix all ingredients together and put in a greased 9-inch or 10-inch pie pan.
Cover with pie crust (top only).
Brush with milk and put a slit on top.
Bake at 375° for 1 hour.

title: cream cheese pound cake
directions: Cream together cream cheese, butter and sugar.
Add eggs one at a time.
Add flour slowly while beating mixture.
Add salt and baking powder, then lemon and vanilla; mix well.
Pour into greased and floured tube pan.
Bake for 2 1/2 hours at 275°, or until cake tests done.
Cool in pan.

title: cheeseburger pie
directions: Use 8-inch pie shell, mix together all ingredients and fill pie shell.
Bake at 350° for 35 to 40 minutes.
Take out and cover top with 1 cup of shredded American cheese, bake 10 more minutes. Let stand 10 minutes then serve.

title: mexican corn bread
directions: Combine cornmeal, salt and baking soda.
Add shortening, sour cream, corn and eggs. Spoon 1/2 of batter in greased 9 x 13-inch pan.
Sprinkle with cheese and chilies.
Cover with remaining batter.
Bake at 375° for 35 to 40 minutes.

title: princess bars
directions: To prepare base of bars mix together 1-1/3 c. flour, margarine and brown sugar; easiest way is to use your fingers.
Press into a greased 9 inch square pan.
Spread with your favorite jam or pineapple filling, 1/4 to 1/2 inch thick.
To prepare pineapple filling, mix together 1/2 c. sugar, cornstarch, undrained crushed pineapple, and lemon juice.
To prepare topping, melt margarine in a saucepan.
Remove from heat and add sugar, flour, cinnamon and nuts.
Sprinkle topping over filling and bake at 350° for 35 minutes, or until top is lightly browned.

title: stir-fry sauce mix
directions: In 1-quart jar combine first 5 ingredients.
Add soy sauce and vinegar; shake until blended.
Add broth, sherry and water.
Shake well.
Store, covered, in refrigerator up to 2 weeks.
Shake before using.
Mix may be frozen in tightly covered containers in 1-cup portions; thaw and shake before using.
Makes 4 cups.

title: easy mushroom crescents snacks
directions: Brown mushrooms in margarine or butter.
Stir in garlic powder, onions, lemon juice and Worcestershire sauce until liquid evaporates.
Set aside.

title: mabel's salad
directions: Mix cabbage and pineapple.
Add light mayonnaise to desired moistness.

title: zucchini casserole
directions: Steam zucchini.
Combine sour cream, butter, cheese, salt and paprika.
Stir over low heat until cheese melts.
Stir in beaten egg.
Pour over zucchini and chopped chives.
Sprinkle with bread crumbs and grated cheese.
Bake at 375° for 30 minutes.

title: lettuce toss with hot bacon dressing
directions: Fry bacon until crisp.
Drain, reserving 1 tablespoon of fat. Tear lettuce into bowl.
Add tomato and onion.
Sprinkle greens with seasonings.
Combine 1 tablespoon of bacon fat and vinegar. Bring to boil.
Pour over salad, tossing lightly to mix.
Crumble bacon over top of salad.
Serve immediately.
Serves 6.

title: microwaved oats cereal
directions: Combine all ingredients in a large microwave-safe bowl. Cereal expands rapidly when it cooks.
Cover with plastic wrap, vent.

title: coconut pecan cake
directions: Blend cake mix, pudding, water, eggs and oil in a large bowl at
medium
speed for 4 minutes.
Stir
in
coconut
and pecans. Pour into three greased
and
floured
9-inch
pans. Bake at 350° for 35 minutes.
Cool
in
pans
for
15 minutes. Remove cake from pans and cool on
racks.
Ice
between layers and top with frosting (recipe follows)

title: instant hot chocolate mix
directions: Mix all ingredients.
Add 1/3 cup to 1 cup boiling water.

title: cheese straws
directions: Cream together cheese and butter.
Sift in flour 1 cup at a time.
Add salt and pepper.
Press through cookie press into straw shapes.
Bake at 400° until they begin to brown slightly.
Remove with spatula onto wax paper and cool.

title: swedish pie
directions: Cream eggs, sugars, salt and vanilla.
Sift flour with baking powder; add to creamed mixture.
Fold in apples and nuts.
Mix well.

title: 4-bean salad
directions: Mix together the sugar, vinegar, salad oil, salt and pepper. Combine vegies and dressing; mix.
Toss several times, or turn in bowl with tight lid.
Chill overnight or longer.
Turn daily until eaten.

title: sweet potato casserole
directions: Mix first 6 ingredients together with mixer.
Pour in casserole dish.

title: muffins
directions: Pour into greased muffin tins and bake at 400°.
Store in refrigerator and use as needed.

title: hamburger deluxe
directions: Mix all ingredients together.
Divide into 8 parts.
Form patties.
Place 1 slice cheese on patty and top with another patty. Brown and cook on grill or frypan.
Cut rolls in half.
Butter sides.
Sprinkle with little garlic powder and heat in oven.
Put cooked patties in.
Enjoy!

title: shakertown scalloped oysters
directions: Pick over oysters and drain.
Grease a baking dish and cover with a third of the cracker crumbs.
Cover with half the oysters and season.
Add half the oyster liquor and cream mixture.
Repeat. Cover the top with remaining crumbs.
Pour melted butter over all. Bake at 400° for about 30 minutes.
Serves 6.

title: smoked salmon ball
directions: Drain and flake salmon, removing skin and bones.
Combine salmon with next 7 ingredients.
Chill several hours.
Shape salmon mixture into 1 large or 2 small balls.
Coat with either chopped pecans or the parsley.
Chill well.
Serve with crackers. Serves 10.
Approximate time to prepare:
20 minutes
(Needs 2 to 3 hours to chill.)

title: noodles and kraut
directions: Cook noodles in salt water, add bacon drippings.
Add kraut and beef hot dogs.
Mix well.
Eat warm.

title: okra gumbo
directions: In large deep frying pan, saute onions in 3 tablespoons cooking oil.
Put in stewed tomatoes.
Slightly boil okra, about 5 minutes; drain.
Then put okra in tomatoes and let cook for awhile, about 20 minutes.
Good.

title: chicken enchilada casserole
directions: Cook, skin, debone and cut up chicken.
Make a sauce of soup, sour cream, chilies and oregano.
Add chicken broth if sauce is too thick.
Put chicken and sauce in a large bowl.
Add torn up tortillas and a portion of the cheese; stir.
Put all in a large casserole dish.
Sprinkle with remaining cheese and sliced black olives.
Bake at 350° for 1 hour.

title: olive nut sandwich spread
directions: Soften cream cheese to room temperature, then mash with fork. Chop pecans fine until you have 1/2 cup.
Chop salad olives until you have 1 cup.
Cream mayonnaise with cream cheese.
Add olives, nuts, olive juice and a dash of pepper.
Mix well and seal in a jar.
Refrigerate 24 to 48 hours before using.
Keeps well in refrigerator for several weeks.

title: mulligan stew
directions: Fry floured meat until brown, drain and discard fat.

title: butter dips
directions: Mix flour, sugar, baking powder and salt.
(I like to use 1/2 cup of whole wheat flour and the rest white flour.) Add milk.
Mix well and roll out on floured surface to size to fit 9 x 13-inch baking pan in which you have butter or margarine.
Place dough in and turn over so both sides are coated.
Cut into thirds across the pan and then into 6 to 8 strips.
Bake in a 450° oven approximately 18 minutes.
I have sprinkled poppy seed or sesame seed into the margarine before putting the dough into the pan.

I have also added 1/2 cup grated Cheddar cheese and 1/2 teaspoon garlic powder to the dough before baking and sprinkled the top with Parmesan cheese and dry Italian (Good Seasons) dressing mix when I take out of oven for Garlic Butter Dips.

title: mexican soup
directions: Fill soup pan with water.
Dice potatoes, onions, garlic, bell pepper and carrots and add to water.
Add tomato sauce.
Cook for 40 minutes.
Add Jack cheese to top; sprinkle cilantro on top (optional).
Serve with flour tortillas.

title: pumpkin pie(delicious any time)
directions: Soften cream cheese in microwave on High 15 to 20 seconds.
Mix cream cheese, milk and Equal (or sugar) in large bowl with whisk until smooth.
Gently stir in whipped topping.
Spread on bottom of crust.
Pour 1 cup milk into bowl.
Add pudding mix.
Beat with wire whisk until well blended, 1 to 2 minutes.
(Mixture will be thick.)
Stir in pumpkin and spices with whisk; mix well.
Spread over cream cheese layer.
Refrigerate at least 3 hours.
Garnish with chopped nuts and a dollop of whipped topping if desired.

title: hot cheese dip
directions: Brown hamburger and sausage; drain.
Cube cheese.
Add tomatoes and hot sauce.
Put all ingredients into crock-pot and simmer on low heat.

title: chicken-bacon spread on dip
directions: Do ahead.
Combine all ingredients but apples.	Refrigerate until serving time.

title: temptation(janssons fristelse)
directions: Cut anchovy fillets into small pieces.
Peel potatoes and cut into julienne strips.
Slice onions and saute in small amount of butter.
Butter a 9 x 13 x 2-inch baking dish and put potatoes, anchovy and onions in layers, ending with potatoes.
Pour half and half over and sprinkle with bread crumbs.
Bake at 375° for about 50 minutes or until potatoes are done.
Serves 4.

title: banana split pie
directions: Mix first three ingredients together and press into a 13 x 9-inch pan.
Mix next three ingredients and pour over crumbs. Slice 5 bananas.
Sprinkle with lemon juice and spread over mixture in pan.
Pour drained crushed pineapple over all.
Top with Cool Whip.
Garnish with nuts and cherries.

title: bean bake
directions: Brown bacon.
Cook ground beef and onion.
Drain and rinse all beans except pork and beans.
Drain beef; return to skillet. Add reserved beans, undrained pork and beans, barbecue sauce and all except 1/4 cup of bacon to beef in skillet.
Mix well.
Spoon mixture into 9 x 13 baking dish.
Top with remaining bacon.
Bake 45 minutes at 350°.

title: white - almond trash
directions: Melt almond bark according to package directions.
Mix rest of ingredients together.
Pour almond bark over mixture and toss gently.
Spread on cookie sheet to cool.
Serve.

title: greg's fruit tart
directions: Mix flour, oleo and sugar well and bake until brown at 400° in a 9 x 13-inch pan.

title: fudge ribbon cake
directions: Combine 2 tablespoons butter with cream cheese, 1/4 cup sugar and cornstarch.
Add 1 egg, 2 tablespoons milk and 1/2 teaspoon vanilla.
Beat at high speed until smooth and creamy.
Set aside.

title: fresh apple cake(like mamma's)
directions: Combine apples and 2 cups sugar; let stand 30 minutes.
Add flour, salt and soda; beat for 1 minute on medium speed.
Add eggs, oil and vanilla; beat for 3 minutes on medium speed.
Pour into greased and floured 9 x 13-inch baking pan.
Bake at 350° for 45 minutes to 1 hour.
Combine brown sugar, milk and margarine; cook for 2 1/2 minutes.
Pour over hot cake.

title: oyster cracker snacks
directions: Mix together first four ingredients.
Pour over crackers. Stir well.
Bake 1 hour at 250°, stirring every 15 minutes. Cool.
Store in airtight containers.

title: holiday cheese ball
directions: Allow all cheeses to stay out in room temperature for 3 hours. Mix together cream cheese, Bleu cheese, onion and Worcestershire sauce.
Put Cheddar through a grater and add to cheese mixture. Roll in walnuts.
Serve with crackers.

title: ala mode
directions: Cut up several brownies in bite sized pieces.
Put in parfait glasses, layer of brownies and layer of ice cream.
Repeat and top with whipped cream.

title: sweet and sour partridge
directions: Mix flour, salt and pepper.
Coat partridge with flour mixture. Heat oil and butter in a large skillet on medium-high heat.
Add partridge pieces and "stir-fry" just until pinkness is gone, about 5 minutes.
Stir in sweet and sour sauce.
Serve with rice.

title: cup of dirt
directions: Crush cookies in resealable plastic bag with rolling pin or in food processor

container. Pour cold milk into a large bowl. Add pudding mix. Beat with wire whisk for 2 minutes or until well blended. Let stand 5 minutes. Gently stir in whipped topping and 1/2 of the crushed wafers.

title: carrot bread
directions: Sift together the flour, sugar, salt, baking powder, baking soda and cinnamon.
Add carrot, oil, eggs and nuts.
Bake at 350° for 1 hour.

title: mashed potato doughnuts
directions: In mixing bowl, combine sugar, salt, nutmeg, vanilla and butter.
Add potatoes, mix well.
Add eggs and milk, mix well. Stir in flour and baking powder.
Chill thoroughly.
On a lightly floured board, roll out dough to 1/2 inch thickness. Cut with doughnut cutter.

title: country sausage gravy
directions: Crumble sausage into a large frypan.
Cook over medium heat. Add onion.
Cook and stir until transparent.
Drain; discard all but 2 tablespoons drippings.
Stir in flour.
Cook over medium heat about 6 minutes or until mixture bubbles and turns brown. Stir in milk.
Add seasonings.
Cook, stirring until thickened. Delicious over biscuits.

title: stay-crisp cabbage salad
directions: Shred cabbage fine with sharp knife; mix with carrots, green pepper and onion.
Sprinkle with 1/2 cup cold water; chill. Soften gelatin in 1/4 cup cold water; set aside.
Mix sugar, vinegar, celery seed, salt and pepper in saucepan.
Bring to boil. Stir in softened gelatin.
Cool in refrigerator until slightly thickened; beat well.
Beat in oil.
After vegetables are drained well, pour oil and vinegar mixture over vegetables.
Keeps well several days in refrigerator.

title: banana bread
directions: Cream butter, shortening and sugar.
Add eggs.
Beat mixture. Add flour and soda and blend.
Add sour milk; add mashed bananas and mix thoroughly.
Grease and flour bread pan.
Bake at 350° for 1 hour.

title: quick chili
directions: Mix pinto beans and refried beans into a pot and warm slowly. Brown ground beef.
When beef is browned, add garlic and medium chopped onion.
Saute beef and vegetables about 2 minutes.
Add chili mix as directed on packages.
Mix chili meat to beans and let simmer 30 minutes.
Good served with cheese and crackers.

title: richard's favorite casserole
directions: Grease a large roaster lightly.
Shred cabbage and put in roaster.
Brown hamburger and onion; salt and pepper.
Drain and add to cabbage.
Stir in dry rice.
Add tomato soup and 1 can of water.
Cover and bake at 350° for about an hour.
Better than cabbage rolls.
Easier too!

title: scalloped potatoes
directions: Place a layer of potatoes in a large, greased casserole.
Top with a layer of onion slices and shredded cheese; repeat.
Mix milk and soup in a saucepan; heat well.
Pour over potatoes, onion and cheese.
Dot with butter.
Bake at 375° for 1 hour.

title: cabbage soup
directions: Cut cabbage, celery and onion into bite size pieces.
Put all ingredients into 5-quart Dutch oven.
Simmer 1 to 1 1/2 hours, until vegetables are tender.

title: quick cinnamon rolls
directions: Sift flour, baking powder and salt.
Blend shortening in and add milk.
Mix well.
Turn on floured board and roll as for making biscuits, trying to make dough oblong shaped.

title: pecan wafers
directions: Combine all ingredients and make dough.
Drop by spoonfuls on an ungreased cookie sheet.
Bake at 375° until edges are brown.

title: chicken enchilada casserole
directions: Fun to do with a large group.
Each person can bring an ingredient.

title: old timers pork rib and oyster jambalaya
directions: Brown ribs.
Add onions, bell peppers and celery.
Add one cup water.
Cover and cook on slow heat until ribs are tender (about 1 1/2 hours).
Add small amount of water, but keep sauce thick.
Add oysters and liquid; cook ten minutes.
Add shallots, parsley and rice.
Mix thoroughly.

title: molasses gingerbread
directions: Mix all ingredients together.
Mix well.
Bake like cookies on a cookie sheet at 350° until done.

title: chicken or turkey casserole
directions: Cook macaroni and drain.
Cook celery in chicken broth for 5 minutes (or use a chicken flavored bouillon cube plus 3/4 cup water). Combine macaroni, celery broth, celery soup, chicken, parsley and salt, if needed.
Pour in greased 2 quart casserole. Sprinkle with grated bread crumbs; dot with butter
Bake at 350° for 30-40 minutes

title: christmas tree coffee cake
directions: Dissolve yeast in warm water.
Let stand 5 minutes.
Combine next 7 ingredients in heavy saucepan.
Cook over medium heat, stirring constantly until cheese melts.
Cool to 105° to 115°.
Add eggs; beat 1 minute on medium speed of mixer.
Stir in yeast mixture, pineapple and enough flour to make a soft dough.
Turn dough out onto floured surface and knead until smooth and elastic (about 8 to 10 minutes).
Place in well-greased bowl, turning to grease top.
Cover and let rise in warm place (85°), free from drafts 1 hour or until doubled in bulk.

title: artichoke-rice salad
directions: Cook rice as directed on package, omitting butter.
Cool in large bowl.
Add green onions, green pepper and olives.
Drain artichoke hearts, reserving marinade; cut them in halves.
Combine artichoke marinade with curry powder and mayonnaise.
Add artichoke hearts to rice salad; toss with the dressing.
Chill.

title: oriental pork chops
directions: Combine egg, soy sauce, sherry, ginger and garlic.
Dip pork chops in egg mixture, then in bread crumbs.
Bake at 350° for 30 minutes.
Turn and bake 20 minutes longer.

title: raspberry punch
directions: Mix all ingredients well.
Serve in punch bowl.

title: pound cake
directions: Cream the butter and 2 cups of sugar together.
Add eggs. Combine dry ingredients together and add alternately with the sour cream to the batter, beginning and ending with dry ingredients. Mix just until the ingredients are blended together.
Add the vanilla.
Pour batter into 2 loaf pans.
Mix 1/4 cup sugar with the cinnamon and sprinkle over the batter.
Bake in a 350° oven for 50 to 60 minutes.
Cool thoroughly.
It is best served the next day.

title: brownies
directions: Sift flour, then sift with sugar, salt and cocoa.
Put into large bowl.
Add oil, eggs and vanilla.
Beat at medium speed for 4 minutes.
Bake in a 13 x 9-inch pan for about 1/2 hour, or until done, at 350°.
Do not overbake.

title: lemon lush
directions: Melt butter and add flour and sugar.
Press in a 9 x 13-inch pan.
Bake at 350° for 20 minutes.
Let cool.

title: pumpkin muffins
directions: Combine sugar, pumpkin and margarine.
Blend in eggs.
Combine flour, baking powder, cinnamon, nutmeg and salt.
Add combined dry ingredients alternately with milk, mixing well after each addition.
Stir in raisins and nuts.

title: hash brown casserole
directions: In large mixing bowl mix all ingredients except margarine and cereal.
Mix well and pour into 10 x 13-inch baking dish.
Melt margarine and spread over top of mixture.
Bake at 350° for 45 minutes.

title: penny carrots
directions: Place cooked carrots, onion and pepper rings in large bowl. Mix together other ingredients and pour over carrot mixture. Marinate overnight.
Good alone or as topping for salad.

title: blueberry-banana bread
directions: Sift flour, baking powder, soda and salt. Cream oleo and sugar until light and fluffy. Beat eggs into sugar/oleo mixture. Add flour mixture and bananas alternately to oleo mixture. Coat blueberries with 2 tablespoons flour.
Carefully stir berries into batter. Spoon into well greased 9 x 5 x 3-inch pan. Bake at 350° for 50 minutes; cool slightly before removing from pan. Makes 1 loaf.

title: graham cracker cake
directions: Cream sugar and shortening.
Add well beaten egg yolks and vanilla.
Mix coconut, pecans, crackers and baking powder and add to sugar mixture alternately with milk.
Beat egg whites until stiff and fold in.
Bake at 375°
for 30 to 35 minutes.
Batter will be thin.

title: shepherd's pie
directions: Fry hamburg and onion.
Place in bottom of a greased 1 1/2-quart casserole.
Add peas, then corn.
Spread mashed potatoes over top.
Dot with butter.
Bake at 350° until golden brown, approximately 30 to 45 minutes.

title: watermelon ice cream
directions: Mix 2 tablespoons green food coloring into lime sherbet and set aside.
Mix 2 tablespoons red food coloring into raspberry sherbet with 2 cups chocolate chips and set aside.
Spray nonstick cooking spray into large plastic container.
Line plastic container with lime sherbet (to make the rhine).
Fill inside of plastic container with raspberry sherbet.
Re-freeze entire container for 12 to 24 hours.
For serving, take out of container and slice.
Instant watermelon.

title: sausage cheese dip
directions: Fry ground beef and sausage until it loses its pink color; drain. Add other ingredients and heat. Serve with or over tortilla chips.

title: white cupcakes
directions: Bake at 375° to 400° for 20 minutes.

title: crab delights fettuccine
directions: Cook fettuccine; drain.
Heat butter and garlic in skillet on medium until garlic is lightly browned.
Add half and half, crab and pepper.
Heat about 3 minutes or until mixture just begins to bubble, stirring occasionally.
Add Parmesan cheese; stir 1 minute. Remove from heat.
Serve over fettuccine.
Add additional Parmesan cheese, if desired.
Makes 4 (1 cup) servings.

title: baked hamburgers
directions: Mix and let stand 15 minutes.
Make into cakes and brown.

title: dijon pork
directions: Brown pork in skillet. Add onions and cook until softened. Add other ingredients and simmer for 20 minutes. Add 3 tablespoons water to flour and make a thin paste. Add to pan. Heat until gravy is thickened, stirring constantly. Serve over noodles. Serves 4.

title: peanut butter bars
directions: Mix ingredients and press into 2 (9 x 13-inch) greased pans. Bake at 300°
for 20 to 25 minutes.

title: hot turkey or chicken salad
directions: In a mixing bowl, combine the turkey or chicken with celery, almonds, salt, thyme and pepper. Stir in the mayo or salad dressing and blend well. Add cheese and toss, then transfer to a greased 2-quart baking dish. Top with crushed potato chips. Bake, uncovered, in 450° oven for 15 minutes until heated through.

title: mother-son chocolate fudge
directions: Line a 13 x 9 x 2-inch pan with foil; lightly butter foil. Combine sugar and milk in a 3-quart heavy pan.
Stir and cook over medium heat until mixture reaches a full rolling boil.
Reduce heat if necessary, but keep mixture boiling steadily for 6 minutes.
Stir as needed to prevent scorching.
Meanwhile, put chips, butter and vanilla in large bowl of electric mixer.
Pour the hot mixture into mixer bowl and beat at high speed until there is no butter on top.
To tell when candy is ready to pour, lift beaters and let a little candy drop off them.
If the drops do not sink into the candy, it is ready to pour.
Stir in walnuts.
Pour into pan; mark pieces while warm.
Let candy cool for several hours or overnight; until candy is firm before cutting.

title: strawberry icebox pie
directions: *Or 1 pint fresh strawberries.
Put sugar over sliced strawberries and let set at least 1 hour.

title: good egg custard
directions: Beat eggs until lemon-colored.
Add sugar to eggs and mix thoroughly.
Bring milk and margarine to a boil.
Add this mixture to egg mixture and beat vigorously.
Add vanilla and pour into unbaked pie shell.
Bake at 350° for 40 minutes or until firm.

title: cranberry punch
directions: Blend ice milk and cranberry juice until slushy.
Add ginger ale.

title: tropics dressing
directions: Mix well with hand mixer.

title: cornbread salad
directions: Take cooked, cooled cornbread; crumble into a 9 x 12-inch bowl.
Layer tomatoes, pepper, onion, lettuce and bacon.

title: banana nut bread
directions: Mix ingredients and bake in oven at 350°.

title: peanut butter pizza
directions: Cream margarine, sugar, peanut butter, egg and vanilla.
Sift together dry ingredients and add to mixture.
Mix well.
Spread on greased and floured pizza pan as you would pizza dough.
Sprinkle chocolate or butterscotch chips or both.
Sprinkle small marshmallows on chips.
Bake at 325° for 10 to 15 minutes.

title: milkless, eggless, butterless cake
directions: Boil together first 6 ingredients for 3 minutes.
Cool thoroughly.
Add remaining ingredients.
Bake in 9-inch square pan at 350° for 35 minutes.

title: waffle fry nachos
directions: Bake fries according to package directions.
Transfer to a 10 inch ovenproof skillet.
Top with the bacon, onions, olives, tomatoes, salsa and cheeses.
Return to the oven for 5 minutes or until cheese is melted.
Serve with sour cream.
Serves 6 to 8 people.

title: hamburger casserole
directions: Lightly brown hamburger meat in skillet; drain.
Butter a 9 x 13-inch casserole dish.
Pour in the browned hamburger meat and spread.
Add sliced potatoes.
Add salt and pepper over potatoes. Add sliced carrots.
Add onions.
Mix celery soup and milk; mix good and pour over all of this.
Top with cheese slices.
Cover and bake for about 1 hour at 350°.
Uncover; bake 15 minutes more.

title: olivia's summer salad
directions: In a flat casserole dish, place 1 layer of crushed Melba toast, 1 layer of sliced homegrown tomatoes, 1 layer of thinly sliced onions and 1 layer of sliced peeled cucumbers.
Salt and pepper each layer.
Spoon homemade mayonnaise on cucumber layer. Make as many layers as you need, sprinkling crushed Melba toast over final layer of mayonnaise.
Cover and keep in fridge for 24 hours before serving.
Stir before placing on table.

title: pumpkin roll
directions: Beat sugar, pumpkin and egg together for 3 minutes.
Sift dry ingredients together.
Combine wet and dry ingredients and mix well.
Grease jelly roll pan and line with waxed paper.
Spread batter evenly in pan and bake at 375° for 13 to 15 minutes until edges brown slightly and cake springs back to touch.
Cool 1 minute in pan.
Turn cake over onto tea towel sprinkled with confectioners sugar, peel off waxed paper.
Roll cake lengthwise in tea towel like a jelly roll and cool 1 hour.

title: shoe peg corn casserole
directions: Mix first 8 ingredients.
Put in 9 x 13-inch casserole.
Melt margarine and mix with crushed cracker crumbs.
Sprinkle on top. Bake 45 minutes at 350°.

title: black-eyed pea salad
directions: Mix together and chill.

title: easy chicken noodle soup
directions: In large saucepan, stir together chicken broth, chicken, frozen peas and carrots, onion and pepper.
Bring to boil.
Stir in uncooked noodles.
Reduce heat.
Cover and simmer about 10 minutes or until noodles are tender.

title: toasted almond party spread
directions: Mix all ingredients, except almonds.
Place almonds on top. Bake at 350° for 15 minutes in preheated oven.
Serve hot with whole wheat or sesame seed crackers.

title: roger's chocolate cheesecake
directions: Form crust by blending cookie crumbs, 3 tablespoon melted butter, 1 ounce chocolate chips and 1/2 cup pecans.
Press into bottom and sides of a greased 10-inch spring-form pan.
Bake for 10 minutes

title: pistachio chocolate chip nut cake
directions: Mix all ingredients except nuts and chocolate bits.
Beat 2 minutes with mixer.
Fold in nuts and chocolate bits.
Pour into a large well-greased Bundt pan.
Bake at 350° for 45 minutes.
Cool 10 minutes and turn out on rack.
Sprinkle with powdered sugar.

title: dumplings
directions: Sift together first 3 ingredients into a bowl. Cut shortening in with pastry blender until crumbly. Pour in milk. Add egg. Mix only until flour is dampened; dough should be lumpy. Drop by spoonfuls on top of boiling stew meat. Cover tightly and steam 12 minutes without removing cover. Makes 6 large dumplings.

title: yogurt substitution
directions: Blend yogurt and cheese as base for dips; season with garlic and onion.
Use plain yogurt instead of milk or cream in mashed potatoes or pasta dishes.
Use vanilla yogurt instead of milk with instant pudding mixes for calcium-rich, creamy dessert.
Replace the sour cream in many cakes, muffins and quick breads with plain or vanilla yogurt.

Add 1 teaspoon baking soda to dry ingredients (in addition to other leavening ingredients called for in recipe). Blend 1 teaspoon Dijon style mustard with 1 cup plain yogurt and salt, pepper and/or herbs, to taste, to replace mayo in tuna or chicken salad.

title: oatmeal cookies
directions: Mix ingredients well.
Bake on greased cookie sheet at 350°.

title: pecan chews
directions: Beat egg whites until stiff.
Add brown sugar, vanilla and salt.
Fold in pecans.
Spray cookie sheet with Pam.
Bake in 350° oven for 8 to 10 minutes.

title: lemon cake
directions: Mix ingredients together.
Spread into a 13 x 9 x 2-inch pan (greased).
Mix will be crumbly.

title: chocolate sheet cake
directions: In saucepan, put oleo, Crisco, cocoa and water.
Bring to a rapid boil and pour over flour, sugar and stir well.
Add buttermilk, eggs, soda, vanilla and cinnamon.
Mix and pour into a greased pan size 16 x 11.
Bake at 400° for 20 minutes.

title: maple-pecan pralines
directions: Combine
sugar,
milk,
syrup,
margarine
and
cream of tartar in
a Dutch oven;
heat to boiling, stirring constantly. Stir in pecan pieces; cook over medium heat, stirring occasionally,
until
mixture
reaches
soft ball stage (236°). Remove from heat,
stir in flavoring.
Beat with a wooden spoon 5 to 8 minutes or
until
the mixture is creamy and begins to thicken. Working
rapidly,
drop
by
rounded
tablespoonfuls onto waxed paper; let cool.
Yields 2 dozen.

title: easy hamburger casserole
directions: Boil egg noodles in slightly salted water.
Brown ground chuck with chopped onion and bell pepper, using salt and pepper to season.

title: chocolate pie
directions: Mix well the sugar, cocoa and flour (or cornstarch).
Beat lightly the egg yolks; add 1/2 cup milk and beat lightly.
Add this and the 1 1/2 remaining cups milk to dry mixture and stir. Put on high burner until strikes a boil, stirring constantly, then turn burner to medium and continue stirring until it thickens.
(Make sure it is very thick.)
Boil about 1/2 minute. Remove from burner and add flavoring.
Let cool to warm.
Pour into ready-baked pie shell.
Top with meringue.

title: broccoli and rice casserole
directions: Prepare broccoli and rice according to package directions. Then mix together, adding Cheez Whiz and evaporated milk.
Place in 1-quart dish, sprinkle with paprika.
Bake at 350° for 30 minutes.

title: caroline marsh's six weeks muffins
directions: Mix all ingredients in large bowl.
Store, covered, in refrigerator.
When you take out each time for a batch of muffins, don't stir the mixture, just dip a spoonful out each time.
Last batch is better than the first!
Spoon batter into muffin pan cups coated with cooking spray.
Fill about 2/3 full.
Bake at 400° for 15 to 20 minutes.
Serve warm.

title: baked bean casserole
directions: Mix and bake 60 minutes at 350°. Yields 8 servings.

title: banana pudding
directions: Blend sugar and flour in medium bowl.
Separate eggs and set whites aside.
With a fork beat yolks and add to sugar.
Add vanilla.
Add milk in small amounts until all is blended in.
Cook in nonstick skillet on medium heat until thickened.
Remove from heat.
Put a layer of mix in bottom of 2-quart baking dish, add layer of vanilla wafers then layer of bananas.
Repeat until dish is almost full ending with layer of mix.
Add meringue and bake at 425° until meringue is brown.

title: persimmon cookies
directions: Combine one at a time and chill.
Drop by spoonfuls on baking sheet and into 350° oven for 12 to 15 minutes.

title: easy cheese cake
directions: Take cream cheese and sugar and mix with electric mixer until creamy.
Add sour cream and vanilla.
Blend in Cool Whip and mix well.
Let chill for at least 4 hours.

title: charleston chews
directions: Cream sugar and butter; add rest of ingredients.
Mix well. Pour into a greased 9 x 13-inch pan.
Cook at 350° for 45 minutes.

title: sweet cucumber pickles
directions: Mix cold water and salt.
Pour over sliced cucumbers; let stand 48 hours; drain and rinse.
Mix hot water and alum.
Pour over cucumbers and let stand 24 hours; drain and rinse.
Pack in sterile jars.
Tie spices and celery seed in bag; mix with vinegar and sugar; let simmer 30 minutes.
Pour over cucumbers and seal jars.

title: spaghetti and sauce
directions: In saucepan combine whole tomatoes, tomato sauce, crumble bay leaves.
Let simmer 15 minutes.
Brown beef; add onion, bell pepper and garlic.
Place cooked spaghetti on plate, top with ground beef, place sauce on top.
Serve with garlic or French bread, salad and fried chicken.

title: coconut crunch pie
directions: Beat egg whites at high speed of electric mixer until stiff. Add salt.
Gradually add sugar; fold in vanilla.
Stir in graham cracker crumbs, coconut and pecans.
Pour into a well buttered pie pan.
Bake at 350° for 20 minutes.
Serve with whipped cream or sliced bananas and whipped cream.

title: gooey butter cookies
directions: Mix first 3 ingredients and pat into 9 x 13-inch pan.

title: vanilla pudding filling and frosting
directions: Cook pudding, milk and cornstarch; cool.
Cream remaining ingredients.
Add to first mixture and beat with electric mixer until right to spread.

title: french cucumber pickles
directions: In a one gallon jar, slice cucumbers, onion and bell pepper. Add salt and let stand 1 hour.
Pour off liquid, but do not rinse. Mix vinegar, sugar and celery seed to dissolve (do not heat). Pour over cucumbers.
Pack tight, cover and refrigerate for 5 days.

title: stuffed peppers
directions: Boil peppers until not quite done.
Drain.
Stuff with hamburger, rice and seasoning mixed together.
Cook in oven 1 hour and 35 minutes.

title: microwave cookie treats
directions: Place one candy on top of each cookie.
Heat on High 30 seconds and they are ready for snacking.

title: banana pudding
directions: Mix pudding according to the directions on package.
Add sour cream and Cool Whip.
Mix on low speed until well blended.
Layer wafers, bananas and pudding in bowl.

title: mincemeat cake
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
Cream shortening and sugar.
Add corn syrup and eggs.
Sift flour (reserve a little to coat pecans and mincemeat) with spices and add alternately with buttermilk.
Stir in nuts and mincemeat.
Bake in a 10-inch tube pan 1 hour or until cake tests done.
Cool 10 minutes in the pan before turning out. Freeze if desired.
Thaw before serving.

title: navajo frybread
directions: Preheat lard to 200° or until it starts to smoke (I use cooking oil).
Mix all ingredients, except water, in medium size bowl.
Add water and knead until dough forms a ball.
Continue to add a little water, if necessary, to make a nice smooth texture, not sticky. (Let dough set at least 5 minutes.)
Puff off a piece of dough a little larger than a walnut.
Pat in hands to make it thin and flat.
Place slowly into preheated oil.
Turn when a bubble forms in the center or when the edges start to turn golden brown.
Brown the other side, remove to a paper towel.
You may eat the bread in the traditional Navajo way, by sprinkling with a little salt or spread with margarine and add cinnamon, sugar, honey, jam or powdered sugar; enjoy!

title: creamy hot chocolate mix
directions: Combine all ingredients and store in an airtight container. Use within 6 months.
Makes approximately 6 cups.
Add 3 to 4 tablespoons of mix to 1 cup of boiling water.

title: rice casserole
directions: Saute onion and rice in margarine until brown.
Put in 2 1/2-quart casserole dish with other ingredients.
Combine well. Cover and cook one hour at 350°.
Makes 6 to 8 servings.

title: moist pumpkin bread
directions: Cream shortening; gradually add sugar, beating well at medium speed.
Add eggs, one at a time.
Stir in pumpkin and water.
Mix well.
Combine flour, baking soda, salt, baking powder, cinnamon and cloves; mix well.
Add creamed mixture.
Fold in pecans.
Cook at 350° for 1 hour or until done.
Yields 2 loaves.

title: pudding cake
directions: Mix the first 4 ingredients and cook 15 minutes at 350°.
Let cool.
Mix cream cheese, Cool Whip and powdered sugar and add to first layer.
Mix pudding and milk and add to first and second layers.
Then top with Cool Whip.
Sprinkle with graham cracker crumbs.
Refrigerate.

title: hawaiian ham sandwiches
directions: Cut thins slices off tops of buns.
Hollow out bread in the center, leaving 1/4-inch thick shells;
set aside tops and discard hollowed-out bread (or save for another use).
Place buns on a baking sheet;
line the inside of each with Swiss cheese.
In a skillet, saute peppers and onions in oil for 3 minutes.
Add ham; cook for 3 minutes.
Add pineapple.
Remove from the heat;
drain. Spoon into buns.
Bake at 450°F. for 5 minutes.
Sprinkle with mozzarella cheese;
return to the oven until cheese melts, about 1 minute.
Replace tops of buns.
Serve immediately.

title: coffee cake
directions: Cream together sugars, margarine, cinnamon and salt.
Reserve 1 cup of this to be used as topping.
To remaining creamed mixture, add egg, milk, flour, baking soda and vanilla.
Mix well. Add nuts or raisins, as desired.
Pour batter into a greased and floured 9 x 13-inch pan.
Sprinkle reserved 1 cup creamed mixture on top of batter.
Bake at 350° for 35 to 45 minutes.

title: creamed carrots
directions: Filling; when read to serve, thicken with flour and milk.

title: stuffed mushrooms
directions: Wash mushrooms and remove stems.
Drain cups upside down on paper towels.
Brown sausage and onion, drain fat.
Mix remaining ingredients, add to meat, onion mixture.
Stuff caps, broil 3 to 5 minutes about 6 inches from heating unit.

title: cheese balls
directions: Mix together the cream cheese and Cheddar cheese.
Add all other ingredients.
May make one large ball or small individual balls.
Roll in chopped pecans.

title: devil's food cake
directions: Mix cocoa and water and then add soda and let stand.
Mix following ingredients and then add cocoa mixture.
Bake at 350° for 40 to 45 minutes.

title: bob's ol-fashion peanut brittle
directions: Lightly butter large cookie sheet and spread the peanuts 1/4 to 1-inch apart.

title: honey bear brownies
directions: Cream the butter and sugar in a small bowl.
Blend honey or syrup and vanilla. Add eggs, one at a time, beating well after each addition. Combine flour, cocoa and salt.
Gradually add to the creamed mixture. Stir in nuts.
Pour into greased 9-inch square pan. Bake at 350° for 25 to 30 minutes until brownies pull away from sides of pan.

title: chili rellenos casserole
directions: Brown hamburger and onion in skillet; drain.
Stir in salt and pepper; set aside.
Arrange half the green chilies in a greased 6 x 10-inch baking dish.
Sprinkle with cheese.
Top with meat, then remaining chilies.
Combine flour and 1/4 cup milk.
Blend until smooth.
Add eggs, 1 1/4 cups milk and hot sauce; mix well.
Pour over meat and chilies.
Bake 45 to 50 minutes at 350°.
Let stand 5 minutes before cutting to serve.

title: just great pork chops
directions: Put pork chops in baking dish.
Mix ingredients and pour over chops.
Bake at 350° for 2 hours.

title: holly bars
directions: Place first 8 ingredients in bowl of electric mixer.
Beat hard for 2 minutes.
Stir in oats, nuts, dates and fruit. Spread in well-greased 13 x 9-inch pan.
Bake at 350° for 30 to 35 minutes.
Frost and decorate if desired.

title: lemon poppy seed bread
directions: Combine all ingredients; beat for 4 minutes.
Grease and flour 2 loaf pans; fill 2/3 full.
Bake at 350° for 40 minutes.

title: macaroni and beef casserole
directions: About 45 minutes before serving: Preheat oven to 300°.
In a 10 inch skillet over high heat, cook first 5 ingredients until meat is browned, about 10 minutes.
Remove skillet from heat.

Spoon mixture into a 2 qt. casserole dish. Add uncooked macaroni, tomatoes with their liquid and remaining ingredients to casserole, stirring to break up tomatoes. Cover casserole, bake 35 minutes or until mixture is hot and macaroni is tender; stirring occasionally.

title: ham and cheese loaves
directions: Let bread dough thaw and rise according to package directions. On floured surface, roll out bread dough (1 loaf at a time); spread meat over loaf and top with grated cheese.
Roll loaf up and pinch seams together.
Bake in 375° oven until golden brown.
Best served hot.

title: lemon-broccoli chicken
directions: Cut 4 thin slices from lemon.
Set slices aside.
Squeeze 2 teaspoons juice from remaining lemon.
Set aside.

title: hello dolly's
directions: Cream together butter, sugar and vanilla.
Add chips, nuts and flour.

title: tiny corncakes
directions: Combine all dry ingredients in a large bowl.
Stir well.
Make a well in center of mixture.
Combine corn, milk and egg in a bowl.
Stir well.
Add to dry ingredients, stirring just enough to moisten.

title: sartain salad
directions: Mix all ingredients together in a large bowl and let set in refrigerator.

title: daiquiri punch
directions: Put 1 can limeade, 1 can rum and ice in a blender.
Blend on high speed for 1 1/2 minutes.
Pour into a punch bowl.
Repeat 4 times.
Designate a driver before serving.

title: sweet potato casserole
directions: Beat sweet potatoes with electric mixer until fluffy.
Add butter, orange juice and rind, eggs and sugar. Beat well.
Spoon potato mixture into 3-quart casserole. Cover with topping. Bake at 350° for 30 minutes.

title: blueberry cobbler
directions: Put one package of crescent rolls in the bottom of a greased baking dish. Mix cheese, sugar, milk and eggs together and spread on top of rolls. then put pie filling on top of cheese mixture. Put last package of crescent rolls on top of pie filling. Bake at 350° for 30 minutes.

title: apricot nectar cake
directions: Mix well and pour into greased and floured tube or Bundt cake pan.
Bake 1 hour at 325°.
Let cool 15 minutes; remove from pan.

title: mom's monday lunch potato soup
directions: In a 3-quart saucepan, cook bacon until crisp; remove to paper towels to drain. Saute onion in the drippings until tender. Add the potatoes and soup and stir until smooth. Gradually stir in milk. Cook over medium heat, stirring constantly. Stir in bacon, salt if desired, and pepper. Cook until heated through. Garnish with parsley. Yield: 3 to 4 servings.

title: poppy seed bread
directions: Mix all dry ingredients, then add oil, milk and eggs.
Bake at 350° for 45 minutes in loaf pan.

title: quick nut rolls
directions: Combine buttermilk with sugar, salt, soda, shortening, eggs, softened yeast and half the flour in bowl.
Beat 2 minutes real hard until smooth.
Stir in remaining flour to a soft dough.
Add more flour if needed until elastic.
Divide in three.
Roll out into oblong pieces.
Spread with filling.
Put milk around edges. Put on cookie sheet.
Let rise until double.
Beat eggs and milk and spread on top.
Sprinkle with sugar.
Bake at 400° for 30 minutes.

title: carrot bread with raisins and caraway seed
directions: Combine flour, caraway seed, salt, baking powder, baking soda, cinnamon, allspice, cloves, nutmeg, carrot and raisins.
Stir together butter and sugar.
Add egg; combine well.
Stir buttermilk and rind.
Add to flour mixture and stir until just combined. Divide batter between 2 buttered loaf pans.
Bake in a preheated 350° oven for 50 minutes to 1 hour, or until a skewer comes out clean.
Let loaves cool for 10 minutes before removing from pans. Freezes well.

title: oatmeal scotchies
directions: Preheat oven to 375°. In a small bowl, combine flour, baking soda, salt and cinnamon; set aside. In a large bowl, combine butter, sugar, brown sugar, eggs and vanilla. Beat until creamy. Gradually add flour mixture. Stir in oats and butterscotch morsels. Drop by level spoonfuls onto ungreased cookie sheet. Bake 7 to 8 minutes (9 to 10 minutes for crispy cookies). Yields 4 dozen.

title: spinach bread
directions: Melt oleo, add onions, cottage cheese, corn bread mix, spinach and salt.
Add eggs last.
Bake at 400° for 30 minutes.
Bake in dish or pan.
Put under broiler for a few minutes to brown top.

title: toll house pie
directions: Add the first 5 ingredients in order listed, beating well after adding each item.
Stir in chips and walnuts.
Pour into unbaked pie shell and bake for 1 hour at 325°.
May be served warm with ice cream.

title: apple crisp
directions: Pare apples; cut into bowl.
Add sugar and lemon juice to coat.
Spoon into 9-inch pan.
Combine flour and brown sugar; cut in butter.
Sprinkle over apples; pat down firmly.
Sprinkle cinnamon on top.
Bake at 350° for 45 minutes.

title: five can casserole
directions: Combine all ingredients, except bread crumbs, in 1-quart casserole.
Sprinkle bread crumbs on top.
Bake for 1 hour at 350°.
Yields 4 servings.

title: light and creamy pumpkin pie
directions: Combine pumpkin, milk, pie filling mix and pumpkin pie spice in small mixer bowl; beat at lowest speed of electric mixer until well blended, about 1 minute.
Fold in 2 1/2 cups of the whipped topping.
Spoon into crust.
Freeze until firm, about 4 hours. Top with remaining whipped cream.

title: ginger glazed spareribs
directions: Place ribs in 6-quart Dutch oven. Add water to cover. Cook 45 minutes
or until tender. Drain and set aside.
Combine sugar, cornstarch, salt, ginger and pepper in 2-quart saucepan. Stir in lemon juice, soy sauce and 1/4 cup water.
Cook until mixture begins to thicken, about 3 minutes.
Brush sauce on each side of ribs and broil in oven until golden brown or can brown on grill.

title: chocolate chip cookie cake
directions: Cream sugar, eggs, vanilla and margarine.
Add flour and salt, then soda/water.
Mix chocolate chips in.
Add chopped nuts, if desired.
Bake 20 minutes at 375° on greased pizza pan.

title: squash casserole
directions: Cook squash and onion in water until tender; drain.
Add egg. Mix salt, sugar, cheese and part of butter; cook until melted. Pour into baking dish; pour cracker crumbs over top and dot with butter.
Bake until butter is melted and browned.

title: hearty breakfast skillet
directions: Brown sausage in large nonstick skillet on medium heat; drain.
Add potatoes and tomatoes; cook 5 minutes or until potatoes are browned, stirring occasionally.
Top with Velveeta. Beat eggs and water with wire whisk; pour evenly over ingredients in skillet; cover.
Reduce heat to low.
Cook 10 to 12 minutes or until egg mixture is set in center and Velveeta is melted.
Let stand, uncovered, 5 minutes before cutting into wedges to serve. Makes 6 servings.

title: rice and meat dish
directions: Salt and pepper the meat.
Brown in a skillet.
Soak rice 30 minutes or longer.
Drain.
Put in oblong pan, 2-inches deep.
Put a little salt on the rice.
Lay brown meat on top of rice.
Cover with can of onion soup with a can of water.
Pour over rice and meat.
Put a little water in skillet over all.
Cover and bake at 350° for 60 minutes.

title: peanut butter rice krispies treats
directions: Bring sugar & syrup to full boil.
Take off stove and add peanut butter, pour over rice krispies and stir well.
Put in buttered 9 x 13 pan.
Variation:
Melt 1 1/2 c. chocolate chips in microwave and spread on top.

title: meatballs
directions: Mix all ingredients in large bowl until firm.
Roll into 2-inch balls; place on cookie sheet.
Bake for 30 to 45 minutes at 400°.
Serve with your favorite homemade sauce or it's great for meatball sandwiches.

title: baked chicken
directions: Wash chicken breasts and pat dry.
Coat with butter and place in a greased casserole.
Dice garlic cloves and arrange around chicken.
Chop shallots and layer over chicken.
Pour chicken broth over and sprinkle with white pepper.
Cover and bake at 350° for 1 hour and 15 minutes.

title: oatmeal cookies
directions: Cream first three ingredients until light and fluffy. Stir in milk.
Sift dry ingredients and stir in mix.
Add raisins and oats.
Bake at 400° for 12 minutes.

title: mike's sausage casserole
directions: Peel skin from sausage. Start preparing rice. Slice sausage into 1/4-inch slices. Place in 9 x 13 Pyrex dish and microwave for 5 minutes. Turn after 2 1/2 minutes. Heat beans while fixing rice. When rice is ready, mix all ingredients except cheese and pour in dish. Place dish in oven and broil for 5 minutes. Remove and top with cheese. Return to oven, browning cheese to taste. Remove and serve.

title: chili
directions: Mince garlic and onion.
Heat oil in a large saucepan and add onions and garlic.
Saute the mixture about 10 minutes.
Chop meat to medium coarseness.
Add it to the pan and brown it for 10 minutes.
Pour the juice from the tomatoes into the pan.
Coarsely chop the tomatoes.
Add them to the pan with all the remaining ingredients.
Simmer the chili, uncovered, for 1 hour.
Correct the seasoning and water if the chili becomes too thick.

title: jello pie
directions: Beat 2 eggs thoroughly.
Add sugar and pineapple juice.
Heat until it starts boiling.
Remove from fire and add lemon jello. Set aside to cool.
Whip 1 can milk which has been chilled.
Fold into cooled jello mixture.
Pour into baked pie shells.
Makes 2 pies.

title: appalachian mountain rice pudding
directions: Combine rice, milk and honey.
Add eggs; mix well.
Stir in raisins.
Pour into greased baking dish.
Sprinkle with cinnamon. Bake at 350° about an hour.
Serve with whipped cream.

title: easy fish, chicken or steak marinade
directions: Combine all ingredients except meat in small bowl. Mix well. Pour over meat and marinate 4-24 hours in refrigerator. Grill meat according to liking, approximately 10 minutes for each inch of thickness.

title: popcorn krispies
directions: Melt
together
the butter, caramels, vanilla and Eagle Brand milk.
Cut
the marshmallows in half.
Dip the marshmallows in the
caramel
mixture and then roll in Rice Krispies. Put on wire rack or waxed paper.

title: king crab au gratin
directions: Pour into well-greased 1 1/2-quart casserole dish.
Top with bread crumbs.
Bake at 400° for 10 to 15 minutes.
Serves 6.

title: mexican rice
directions: Combine the tomato, onion and garlic in a blender.
Puree until smooth.
In a medium saucepan, with lid, heat the oil over medium-high heat. Add the rice and fry, stirring frequently, until opaque and golden.
Pour in the tomato puree, salt, cumin, white pepper and cinnamon and continue cooking, stirring frequently, until most of the liquid is absorbed.
Pour in the chicken broth. Bring to a boil, reduce to a simmer and cover.
Cook 25 minutes or until the liquid is absorbed.
Let sit with the cover on 10 minutes longer. Fluff and serve.

title: easy lemon pie
directions: Beat egg yolks until smooth.
Add milk and mix well until blended.
Add lemon juice and again stir until mixture is smooth and starts to thicken.
Pour into pie shell.
Beat egg whites until stiff, adding sugar to taste and beating until whites stand in peaks.
Spread over pie.
Cook in oven for 5 to 10 minutes at 250°, or until the egg whites have browned.
Let cook, chill and serve.

title: vidalia onion dip
directions: Slice onions thin.
Soak in sugar, vinegar and water for 2 to 4 hours.
Drain well.
Toss with mayonnaise and celery salt. Serve with saltines.
Refrigerate leftovers.

title: stuffed mushrooms
directions: Fry chopped up bacon, onion, mushroom stems, green pepper and seasonings until tender.
Remove from heat and cool.
Add softened cream cheese.
Fill clean mushroom caps with filling.
Then dip tops into bread crumbs.
Place in a buttered pan; add 1/4 cup water.
Bake at 375° for 15 to 25 minutes.

title: strawberry delight
directions: Fix the Dream Whip as directions say.
Add powdered sugar and cream cheese.
Mix well and pour into graham cracker crust.
Let set 2 hours in refrigerator.

title: beet pickles
directions: Drain liquid from beets into saucepan and add vinegar, sugar, and spices. Heat to a boil and add beet slices. Reheat to boiling and remove to quart jar for cooling.

title: milk chocolate fondue
directions: In fondue pot or medium saucepan, combine chocolate chips and evaporated milk.
Cook over low heat until chocolate is melted, stirring occasionally.
Stir in vanilla.
Serve with angel food cake, fresh fruit or pretzels.

title: vegetable cheese casserole
directions: Make white sauce, using the oleo, flour and milk.
Add the cheese and stir until melted.
In a casserole dish place the green beans, corn, carrots and pimentos.
Pour cheese sauce over vegetables.
Stir lightly.
Cover with buttered bread crumbs, if desired.
Bake at 350° until browned, hot and bubbly (about 45 minutes).
Serves 12.

title: lemon delight
directions: Mix all together.
Press into a 9 x 13-inch pan.
Bake at 350° for 10 minutes.
Cool.

title: chicken fricassee
directions: In pan, heat oil over medium heat. Add chicken, a few pieces at a time. Brown well on both sides. Remove chicken and pour off excess fat.
Add onions and mushrooms.
Stirring frequently, cook 5 minutes or until tender. Add broth, salt and pepper. Return chicken to pot. Bring to a boil. Reduce heat and simmer 20 to 30 minutes.
Remove chicken and keep warm.

title: butternut squash pie
directions: Combine all ingredients in mixer until smooth.
Pour into unbaked 9-inch pastry shell and bake at 300° for 1 hour.

title: raspberry and cream cheese coffee cake
directions: Spray bottom and sides of a 9 or 10-inch spring-form pan with nonstick cooking spray.
In a large bowl, combine flour and 1/2 cup sugar.
Cut in margarine until mixture resembles coarse crumbs. Measure and set aside 1 cup of these crumbs.
To remaining crumb mixture, add baking powder, baking soda, salt, sour cream, 1 1/2 teaspoons vanilla, almond extract and 2 egg whites; blend well. Spread batter over bottom and up sides of pan.
Batter should be about 1/4-inch thick on sides.

title: lasagne
directions: Brown hamburger, onion and salt.
Drain off grease.
Add rest of ingredients and simmer for 45 minutes.
Layer in 9 x 13-inch pan:

title: chicken marsala
directions: Dredge chicken in flour with salt and pepper.
Shake in bag. Sprinkle on oregano and squeeze lemon juice over chicken.
When browned on both sides, add lemon, wine or sherry.
Cover.
If breasts are flattened, cook for about 10 minutes to make sure they are done, 30 minutes for regular breasts.
Add mushrooms and almonds last 5 minutes.
Serve over rice.

title: swirl cobbler
directions: Heat oven to 350 degrees.
Melt the margarine in a 13x9x2 inch baking dish.
Heat sugar and water in a saucepan (can use part juice if you have it) until sugar melts.
Cut shortening into flour until particles are like fine crumbs.
Add milk, and stir with a fork only until dough leaves side of bowl.
Turn out onto lightly floured board; knead 2 or 3 times.
Roll dough out into a large rectangle about 1/4 inch thick.
Sprinkle cinnamon over fruit; then sprinkle fruit evenly over dough.
Roll up like a jelly roll and pinch edges together.
Cut into 1/2 inch slices. Place in the pan with melted margarine.
Pour sugar syrup carefully around rolls.
Bake for 45 minutes.

title: corn pudding
directions: Beat eggs slightly.
Add milk, sugar and salt.
Combine corn with other ingredients.
Add to the milk mixture and mix well. Pour into a buttered casserole and bake at 325° for 1 hour.

title: graham cracker cookies
directions: Place butter, margarine and sugar in small saucepan and boil 3 minutes.
Stir occasionally.
Line a jelly roll pan with crackers. Add pecans to hot mixture and spoon over graham crackers.
Bake 12 minutes at 350°.
Remove from pan before they cool and cut graham crackers with a knife along lines to separate.
Makes 80 cookies.

title: 12 bean soup
directions: Wash beans.
Add beans and ham to water in large kettle.
Add onions, carrots, celery and seasonings.
Simmer 3 hours, covered. Given to me by a Swiss friend.

title: coconut surprise
directions: Mix together and pat into a 9 x 13-inch pan.
Bake for 20 minutes at 300°.
Let cool.

title: broccoli-cheese strata
directions: Oil 2-quart casserole.
Layer broccoli, bread, onion and half of cheeses.
Sprinkle remaining cheeses on top.
Whisk together eggs, buttermilk and seasonings.
Pour into casserole.
Bake for 40 minutes at 350°.
Serves 4.

title: texas sheet cake(a b-i-i-i-g brownie cake!)
directions: Preheat oven to 375°F (190°C).
Grease a 15 x 10-inch or larger baking pan.
Put Brownie Mix in a large bowl.
In a small saucepan, bring butter or margarine and water to a boil.
Add to Brownie Mix. Add sour cream, eggs and baking soda.
Blend well.
Pour into prepared pan.
Bake 20 to 25 minutes, until a toothpick inserted in center comes out clean.
Prepare Cocoa Icing.
Frost cake while still hot.
Makes one large cake.

title: shrimp casserole
directions: Cook rice until fluffy. Saute onion and chopped pepper in butter. Add soup, lemon juice, pepper, salt and garlic powder. Mix well and add to rice. Add shrimp and parsley. Mix well and place in greased baking dish. Sprinkle cheese on top. Bake at 350° for 30 to 40 minutes. Serves 8 to 10.

title: wonderful choc-bars
directions: Layer all ingredients in an 8 x 8-inch square pan or double recipe in a 9 x 13-inch pan.
Layer ingredients in order.
Bake for 40 minutes at 350°.

title: marinated vegetables
directions: Drain vegetables.
Combine ingredients and toss lightly.

title: 7-up cake
directions: Beat ingredients, except 7-Up.
Add it last and beat well. Bake about 40 minutes in oblong pan at 350°.

title: cheese ball
directions: Mix all together with hands and shape into ball. Roll in chili powder and paprika.

title: salmon and crabmeat au gratin
directions: Mix flour, milk, butter and seasoning.
Cover bottom of buttered baking dish with a thin layer of this sauce.
Add alternate layers of crab, salmon and sauce until dish is full.
Dot with butter; sprinkle with cheese and bake at 500° for 15 minutes.

title: crabmeat dip
directions: Beat last 4 ingredients until fluffy.
Fold in crabmeat and chill overnight, if possible.
Makes one cup.

title: mother's butter beans
directions: Cook the butter beans in boiling, salted water until tender, taking care that they do not overcook and get mushy.
Add margarine to the liquid in the saucepan; be generous with the pepper.
In a small cup, add the flour and just enough water to stir into a smooth paste.
Stir flour mixture into the butter bean liquid; mix well.
Heat and stir to slightly thicken.
Serve hot. Serves 4 to 6.

title: blueberry pie
directions: Slice bananas in bottom of baked pie crust. Add pie filling. Top with Cool Whip.
Chill.

title: chicken casserole
directions: Bake chicken for 45 minutes at 350°.
Prepare noodles as directed.
Trim florets off broccoli and steam.
Combine noodles, chopped chicken, steamed broccoli and mushroom soup in a large casserole dish.
Add 1 soup can of water; mix.

title: spaghetti salad
directions: Cook
spaghetti.
Marinate in Italian dressing and Salad Supreme
overnight.
Add remaining ingredients and chill before serving.
Makes 12 servings.

title: flapper pie(makes 2 pies)
directions: Heat
4 cups milk.
Beat 4 egg yolks with a little cold milk, sugar,
cornstarch	and vanilla.
Use enough milk so it will
pour into hot milk.
Cook until thick.
Pour into graham wafer crusts made in 2 pie plates.

title: barbecue sauce
directions: Heat to warm.
Marinate meat overnight or brush on while cooking.

title: peanut butter fudge
directions: Blend sugar and milk in a frying pan, turn to high heat, stir continuously until mixture comes to a full boil.
Let mixture boil for 5 minutes.
Reduce heat to medium-low or low, stir in peanut butter, continue stirring continuously until mixture comes to a soft ball stage.

title: turkey scallopini
directions: Pound turkey to 1/8 inch thickness.
Flour lightly, shake off excess in skillet.
Melt 2 tablespoons margarine, oil and garlic. Brown meat on both sides until golden brown approximately 3 minutes.
Place meat in ovenproof casserole.
Add remaining margarine and mushrooms to skillet and saute until mushrooms lose their crispness.
Add to casserole.
Combine juice, broth and wine, stir and heat until mixture bubbles.
Pour over casserole.
Bake at 325° for 30 minutes.
Makes 4 servings.

title: vegetable dip
directions: Mix together and refrigerate.
Makes a large batch.
Cut in half and it still makes quite a bit.

title: zelma collin's bread pudding
directions: Beat eggs slightly.
Add milk, sugar, butter and salt.
Put bread crumbs in a greased baking dish.
Add cinnamon.
Pour egg mixture over bread.
Bake at 375° until done.

title: mostaccioli
directions: Saute onion and garlic in oil; set aside.
Cook meat until done.
Rinse off fat.
Add to onion mixture and add remaining ingredients, except noodles.
Cook to a boiling point, stirring frequently.
Reduce heat and simmer slowly about an hour until it thickens.
Cook noodles according to directions.
Mix sauce and noodles.
Serve with grated Romano or Parmesan cheese.

title: german chocolate bars
directions: Sprinkle nuts and coconut into greased 9 x 13-inch pan. Prepare cake mix as directed on box.
Pour over nuts and coconut. Blend cheese, sugar and margarine.
Spoon over top, staying 1-inch from sides.
Bake at 350° for 55 minutes.

title: bubbles
directions: Mix together and let the children make bubbles!

title: drop oatmeal cookies
directions: Combine ingredients.
Bring to a boil in a heavy boiler; cook 3 minutes.
Stir at all times.
Turn off heat.
Add 2 cups 1-minute oatmeal, 1 cup chopped nuts and 1 teaspoon vanilla.
Drop on waxed paper.

title: kielbasa jambalaya
directions: Combine all ingredients in a large skillet.
Cover.
Bring to a boil.
Reduce heat.
Simmer 20 minutes or until rice is cooked.

title: chocolate-toffee trifle
directions: In a clear glass bowl, layer chocolate cake, chocolate pudding, Cool Whip and Heath bar candies.
Add as many layers as your bowl allows.
Finish with Cool Whip and Heath bar candy. Chill until ready to serve.

title: speedy doughnuts
directions: In deep fat fryer or heavy saucepan, heat about 1 quart oil to 350°.
Separate dough into 10 biscuits.
Cut holes in center of biscuits.
Fry biscuits and holes in oil about 1 1/2 minutes on each side, or until golden brown.
Drain.
If desired, roll doughnuts and holes in sugar or cinnamon-sugar mixture or drizzle with glaze or icing.
Serve warm.
Makes 10 doughnuts.

title: lobster with scampi sauce
directions: Saute garlic and pepper in lemon juice until golden brown. Add water, parsley and lobster.
Simmer for approximately 10 minutes.
You may substitute shrimp or scallops for lobster meat.

title: apple pie mix
directions: Prepare canning jars and lids.
Pack apples in jars.
Mix other ingredients and cook until thick.
Pour over apples in jars. Seal and process for 20 minutes in hot water bath or for 10 minutes at 5 pounds pressure.

title: marango meatballs
directions: Mix ground beef, onions, bread, salt and pepper.
Form into meatballs; brown in butter.
Drain grease; scrape meat particles loose.
Place meatballs back in skillet.

title: simply delicious summer chicken
directions: Wash
and chop lettuce and set aside.
Brown chicken in small amount of butter.
Cover and let simmer until thoroughly cooked, turning every few minutes.
Drain on paper towels.
Wash fruit. Layer in a large bowl of lettuce the fruit and nuts.
Garnish with fresh cherries and rest of fruit on top.

title: garlic chicken(30 minute meal!)
directions: Use a shallow saute pan or skillet.
Brown the chicken tenders in the Wish-Bone dressing, adding the cooking wine as the browning begins.
Add the garlic and Italian herbs.
Toss in the mushroom slices and stir frequently as they brown.
A little splash or two more of the Italian dressing or wine may be needed to keep the mixture moist and coat the mushrooms nicely.
Serve on a heated platter.

title: lemon eagle brand pie
directions: Separate eggs and set egg whites aside.
Combine egg yolks with Eagle Brand milk.
Stir in lemon juice and grated lemon rind. Pour into prepared graham cracker crust.
Beat egg whites with sugar and cream of tartar and place on top of pie.
Bake 5 minutes at 450° or until brown.

title: yummy pork roast
directions: Place roast in cooker, after peeling sweet potatoes and apples, spread around roast, pour honey over all and bake at 425 degrees for 3 -4 hrs. or until roast is done.

title: lee ann almond bark candy
directions: Melt bark and mix peanut butter in melted almond bark.
Mix remaining ingredients.
Pour melted mixture over dry mixture. Shape into balls.
Refrigerate until set.

title: lobster with tomatoes, basil and gnocchi
directions: Combine the wine, water, sherry, lemon juice and 1 teaspoon salt in a large pot over medium-high heat and bring to a boil. Add the lobsters and steam until they turn light red, about 10 to 12 minutes.
Remove the lobsters from the pot and set aside to cool.
Strain and reserve the liquid.
Remove the lobster meat from the tails and claws and cut into 1/2-inch pieces.
Set aside.

title: savory beef stew
directions: Melt shortening in a 2-quart saucepan; brown meat.
Add 1/2 cup water, the bouillon cube, garlic, bay leaf, salt, allspice and lemon juice.
Heat to boiling, stirring occasionally.
Reduce heat.
Cover; simmer until meat is almost tender, about 1 to 1 1/2 hours.
Add onions, potatoes and carrots; heat to boiling.
Reduce heat; cover and simmer 10 to 20 minutes.
(Time varies by how firm you like your vegetables.)
Add peas; cook until tender, 6 to 10 minutes.

title: make-ahead beef balls
directions: Mix together.
Bake for 10 minutes or until done on cookie sheet in 400° oven.
Let cool for 10 minutes.
Put cookie sheet in deep freeze.
Leave for 15 minutes.
Pack in containers.
Thaw and serve with your favorite barbecue sauce.

title: zucchini pie
directions: Mix milk, cornstarch and eggs until slightly thickened, then add mashed squash.
Remove from heat and add flavoring and oleo. Bake pie shell and pour in baked shell.
Beat egg whites until stiff.
Put on pie and brown.

title: crab quiche
directions: Saute mushrooms and onion in margarine; drain.
Mix with crabmeat and place in bottom of partially baked pie shell. Combine cream, eggs, mayonnaise, pepper and nutmeg in bowl; beat until smooth.
Stir in cheese.
Pour this mixture into pie shell. Bake at 375° for 25 to 30 minutes.
Serves 6.

title: cheesy beef-and-rice casserole(light recipe)
directions: Preheat oven to 375 degrees. Cook first 3 ingredients in a large nonstick skillet over medium-high heat until meat is browned, stirring to crumble. Add water and next 6 ingredients (water through chiles); bring to a boil. Cover, reduce heat, and simmer 10 minutes. Uncover and simmer an additional 2 minutes. Remove from heat; set aside. Combine the rice, sour cream, sliced green onions and milk in a bowl. Spoon rice mixture into a 9-inch baking dish. Top with beef mixture; sprinkle with cheese. Bake for 10 minutes or until thoroughly heated. Let stand 5 minutes before serving.

title: blackberry pie
directions: Preheat oven to 425°.
In large bowl, combine first 6 ingredients; let stand.

Roll out half of pastry and line 9-inch pie plate as directed in Steps 1 through 3 of pastry recipe. Spoon filling evenly into crust; dot with butter or margarine. Prepare top crust as directed in Step 4 of pastry recipe; make a decorative edge.
Bake 50 minutes or until golden brown.
Makes 6 servings.

title: cherokee goulash
directions: Brown crumbled sausage.
Cook rice.
Drain sausage.
Add rice and kidney beans to sausage.
Heat until beans are warm.
Season with salt and pepper to taste.
Top with soy sauce to taste.

title: peanut butter pie
directions: Cream together cream cheese, powdered sugar and peanut butter. Add Cool Whip.
Put in a graham crust and refrigerate.
Optional: Chip a candy bar on top.

title: salad dressing chocolate cake
directions: Beat ingredients for 2 minutes.
Bake at 350° for 30 minutes. Use two pans.

title: bean sprout and spinach salad
directions: Pour boiling water over spinach in colander; rinse immediately with cold water.
Drain thoroughly and place in medium serving bowl.
Repeat procedure with bean sprouts and place in same bowl. Combine sugar, vinegar, soy sauce and sesame seed; pour over vegetables and toss to combine.
Cover and refrigerate at least 1 hour before serving.

title: garlic sauce (salsa de aglio)
directions: Mash
garlic
to
a
paste with the salt.
Beat the egg yolk and
add
to
the
garlic; mix well.
Add the olive oil a little at
a
time to the garlic and egg yolk mixture.
Mix in the
lemon juice and oregano.
(If desired, whisk in an electric blender.)

title: lemon bars
