directions: Mix well 2 cups plain flour, confectioners sugar and softened margarine.
Spread in a 9 x 13-inch pan.
Bake at 350° for 15 minutes.
Mix together the eggs, sugar, 4 tablespoons plain flour, lemon juice and baking powder.
Pour over first layer.
Bake for 25 to 30 minutes at 325°.
When cool, sprinkle powdered sugar over top, then cut into bars or squares.

title: pumpkin roll
directions: Beat eggs at high speed for 1 minute.
Gradually add sugar. Stir in pumpkin and lemon juice; set aside.
Stir together flour, baking powder, cinnamon and salt.
Fold into pumpkin mix.
Put wax paper on large cookie sheet.
Pour batter on top with nuts.
Bake at 375° for 15 minutes.
Turn onto towel (not terry cloth). Sprinkle with powdered sugar and roll with towel and set aside to cool (about 1 hour).

title: favorite deviled eggs
directions: In a bowl, combine the first 7 ingredients until creamy. Shape into 1-inch balls.
Roll in cheese.
Cover and refrigerate until serving. Serves about 2 dozen.

title: verna's lettuce salad
directions: Layer lettuce, celery, green pepper, onion and grease in 9 x 13-inch dish.
Spread mayonnaise on top, sprinkle sugar over mayonnaise.
Sprinkle bacon over top.
Wrap in foil and refrigerate overnight.

title: pork chops and potato bake
directions: Brown chops in a small amount of oil. Combine chicken gravy, potatoes and sliced onion. Pour into 9 or 8-inch square baking dish. Top with browned chops. Season with salt and pepper. Cover with foil and bake at 375° for 1 hour or until potatoes are tender. Remove foil and bake 10 minutes longer.

title: pole beans with tomatoes
directions: Wash and snap pole beans into bite size pieces; put into large saucepan and cover with water.
Add onion and bacon; cut into 1-inch pieces.
Cover and cook on medium heat for 1 hour. Uncover; add chopped tomatoes, salt and pepper.
Continue cooking on medium heat, uncovered, until water is nearly gone.

title: hamburgers and cheeseburgers
directions: Cook until medium
or
well.
On a plain or toasted bun place the cooked
hamburger.
Can
be served with French fried potatoes, ketchup, mustard, lettuce, tomatoes, barbecue sauce.

title: chicken piccata
directions: Slice each breast in half lengthwise, butterfly style into 8 thin, flat pieces.
Dip pieces in flour to coat lightly.
In skillet, melt butter.
Saute chicken until browned on both sides. Add lemon juice and broth to pan and cook 3 to 4 minutes, turning chicken frequently in sauce until cooked through.
Garnish with parsley.
Great served with pasta.

title: southern meat loaf
directions: Preheat oven to 350°. In a large bowl, combine all ingredients. Shape into a loaf and put in a meat loaf baking dish. Bake 1 hour or until done.

title: greek spinach pie
directions: Thaw filo dough.
Cut Feta cheese into 1/2-inch chunks.
In separate bowl, beat eggs.
Mix with Feta cheese.
Set aside.

title: rice peggy jane
directions: Saute bacon and onion.
Put all ingredients in baking dish. Bake at 350° for 1 hour.

title: shrimp dip
directions: In medium-sized mixing bowl, mix the lemon juice and cream cheese together.
Stir in shrimp and green onions. Add mayonnaise. Stir in hot sauce, Worcestershire and salt.
Put mixture into serving dish and chill.
Best if made several hours or one day ahead.
Serve with crackers.
Makes a lot, easily enough for 10 to 15 guests.

title: chicken-broccoli casserole
directions: Cook and debone chicken.
Line casserole dish with cooked broccoli.
Lay chicken over broccoli.
Mix and heat until blended the soup, mayonnaise, lemon juice and curry powder.
Pour over chicken.
Sprinkle with Cheddar cheese. Mix crackers or cornflakes with one tablespoon margarine and spread over cheese.
Bake 30 minutes at 350°, covered.
Uncover and bake 10 minutes longer.

title: rocky road dream bars
directions: Heat oven to 350°.
Grease 13 x 9-inch pan.
In large bowl, combine base ingredients (cake mix and margarine).
Mix at highest speed until crumbly.
Reserve 1 1/4 cups crumbs for topping.
Press remaining crumbs mixture into prepared pan.

title: oatmeal candy
directions: Boil milk for 3 minutes.
Then add all the rest and drop on wax paper.

title: marinated bean salad
directions: Rinse and drain beans and peas.
Add celery, parsley, onions and green and black olives.
In a small bowl, whisk together the rest of the ingredients.
Pour over bean mixture.
Cover and refrigerate overnight.
Makes 8 servings.

title: beef and spinach lasagna
directions: Heat oven to 375°.
In a large nonstick skillet, brown beef over medium heat 8 to 10 minutes. Pour off drippings.
Add salt, spaghetti sauce, tomatoes and red pepper.
Set aside.

title: braised short ribs with vegetables
directions: Trim excess fat from ribs.
Place ribs, about half at a time, fat side down in heated Dutch oven.
Brown on all sides.
Repeat until all ribs are browned.
Remove ribs and all but 2 tablespoons drippings from Dutch oven.
Add whole and chopped onions; saute for 10 minutes, stirring occasionally.
Remove whole onions; set aside. Add beef broth, 1 cup water, Worcestershire sauce, peppercorns, bay leaf, garlic, marjoram and ribs.
Bring to a boil.
Reduce flame. Simmer, covered, 1 1/2 hours.
Scrub potatoes.
Cut in 1-inch strips.
Add carrots and whole onions along with potatoes to Dutch oven.
Simmer, covered, 1 more hour or until ribs and vegetables are tender.
Place ribs and vegetables on heated platter.
Combine flour and remaining 1/4 cup water.
Mix well.
Stir into pan juices.
Bring to a boil, stirring constantly.
Reduce flame and simmer for 2 to 3 minutes.
Strain.
Pour over ribs and vegetables. Serve with Horseradish Cream if desired.

title: green bean casserole
directions: Drain string beans; arrange in a 13 x 9-inch baking dish. Combine skim milk, mushroom soup, garlic cheese and 1/2 of jalapeno cheese.
Heat until all is melted, then spread evenly over string beans.
Dot the top with remaining cheese (optional). Bake at 350° until cheese sauce thickens (45 minutes to 1 hour).

title: yellow punch
directions: Mix well lemon jello and boiling water; add sugar, pineapple juice, orange juice, lemonade, apricot nectar and 1 gallon water. Mix all ingredients well.
Chill and serve.

title: oven rice casserole
directions: Chop or slice onion in casserole dish.
Add consomme, rice and slice in margarine.
Stir.
Place in oven at 350° for 1 hour. Stir after 20 minutes. This is a great side dish for chicken, beef or pork.

title: pecan pie
directions: Slightly beat eggs.
Add sugar and vanilla and mix well.
Add butter and stir.
Add syrup and beat until thickens.
Stir in nuts.
Pour into unbaked 9-inch pie shell.
Bake at 350° for 15 minutes.
Reduce heat to 300° and cook 35 minutes.
Serves 8.

title: trifle
directions: Select a bowl (glass is fun).
Put some stale cake on bottom; halve ladyfingers or cake up the sides.
(Ladyfingers relax nicely with lashing of sherry.)
Lace all these with sherry.
Layer with sliced fruits repeatedly, and alternate with custard layers, occasional cake-slice layers, fruits, fruits and fruits, lashes of sherry, dollops of currant jelly, sprinkles of nuts, etc.
If it's a glass bowl, turn some vivid colors eyeward.
Internally, please yourself by the arrangements only you will see, and only once.
Top with whipped cream and fruit/nut reminders.
Never forget the sherry.

title: tea room chicken salad
directions: Combine all ingredients and mix well. Refrigerate.

title: chicken or turkey dressing
directions: Mix cornbread and bread crumbs (or stuffing mix) with broth. Add remaining ingredients; mix well. Pour into greased 9 x 13-inch baking dish. Bake at 350° for 30 minutes, until light brown. Makes 10 to 12 servings.

title: chicken in a biscuit
directions: Mix chicken, lemon pepper and cream cheese.
Roll out biscuits and fill with chicken, fold and pinch edges to seal.
Dip in butter and place in baking dish.
Mix soup and milk and pour over biscuits.
Bake at 350° for 20 to 25 minutes until golden.

title: stuffed pork chops
directions: Place pork chops on bottom of baking pan (9 x 13-inch).

title: fresh (soft pear) cake
directions: Sift
dry
ingredients.
Combine eggs, salad oil, sugar and vanilla; mix well. Add sifted ingredients and blend.
Add pears, pecans, raisins and cherries.
Mix.
Bake in a 10-inch Bundt (greased
and
floured)
pan
for
1 1/4 to 1 1/2 hours, until toothpick comes out clean at 325°.
Remove from pan and let cool. Now all you need is coffee and company.

title: baked beans
directions: Brown ground beef.
Add bell pepper and onion.
Add ketchup, Worcestershire and brown sugar.
Put beans in crock-pot on high. When beef mixture simmers, add all to crock-pot.
Mix well.
When it starts to boil, set on low for 3 to 4 hours!

title: pasta and tomato
directions: Brown ground beef.
Cook shells.
Add onion and spaghetti sauce to ground beef.
Simmer.
Mix cooked shells with sour cream.

title: ox yoke rhubarb custard pie
directions: Preheat oven to 375°.
Combine first 5 ingredients in a large bowl.
Sprinkle flour evenly over bottom of pie shell.
Pour rhubarb mixture into shell.
Bake in lower third of oven until set, about 1 hour.

title: shrimp dip
directions: Mix all ingredients in blender for several minutes. Refrigerate immediately.
Store overnight to bring out flavor of shrimp.

title: bubble solution
directions: Combine all ingredients and pour into a plastic bottle.
To blow bubbles use straws, pipe cleaners formed into loops, spoons with holes in them or other items you can think of.
(Do not drink!)

title: latin souffle
directions: Trim crust from bread and butter one side.
Arrange in a 9 x 13-inch baking dish, butter side down, making a shell.
Sprinkle the grated cheeses in the shell.
Mix the milk and eggs well.
Add the rest of the ingredients to the egg mixture and pour over the cheese shell.
Cover and refrigerate overnight.
Bake in a 325° oven for 50 minutes.
Let stand for 10 minutes before serving. (Delicious with ham.)

title: cream cheese tarts
directions: Note:
Need paper liners for muffin tin.

title: steak and pepper rice skillet
directions: Brown beef in oil.
Stir
in
onions, rice, beef, broth, water and soy sauce.
Bring to a boil.
Reduce heat;
cover and cook over low heat until
almost
all liquid is absorbed (about 25 minutes).
Stir in green pepper and heat.

title: oatmeal cookies
directions: Put shortening, vanilla and sugar in bowl and mix until light and fluffy.
Add eggs and milk and beat hard for 1 minute.
Mix in flour mixture, one-third at a time.
When all flour is added, drop by teaspoon 2-inches apart on greased cookie sheet.
Bake at 350° for 12 minutes or until light brown.
Remove from pan at once.

title: beef and cabbage soup
directions: Brown meat in large heavy pot.
Drain fat.
Combine all other ingredients with meat.
Bring to a boil, reduce heat.
Simmer until done.

title: barbecued spareribs
directions: Brush spareribs with liquid smoke several hours before cooking.
Brown spareribs under broiler.
Season with salt and pepper.
While ribs are browning prepare sauce of remaining ingredients.
Simmer for a few minutes.
Arrange ribs in shallow baking pan.
Pour sauce over ribs and baste with it during baking period.
Bake at 325° for 1 1/2 hours.
Cover for first half hour.

title: apple butter
directions: Mix all together.
Boil for 30 minutes and put in hot jars and seal.

title: mexican egg scramble(microwave)
directions: Microwave bacon on rack or paper towels 45 seconds per slice. Place butter, onion and green pepper in bowl and microwave 2 1/2 minutes on High.
Beat eggs with water and garlic powder; microwave 5 minutes on Roast or Medium-high.
Add bacon, chilies, olives and pimentos.
Mix with cheese or place cheese on top. Cover and allow to melt.
Serve with guacamole and chips and refried beans for an easy nutritious brunch.

title: peanut butter frosting
directions: Cream the butter, peanut butter and vanilla together until butter is softened.
Gradually add the confectioners sugar, beating well after each addition.
Beat in the egg yolk.
Beat in enough of the milk until frosting is of spreading consistency.

title: beef and potato nacho casserole
directions: Brown ground beef and 1/2 cup onion in skillet; drain excess fat.
Stir in taco seasoning, water and tomato sauce.
Bring to a boil; simmer 1 minute.
Spread meat mixture into a greased 9 x 13-inch baking pan.
Top with chilies, beans and potatoes.

title: apple pie cake
directions: Cream the sugar and shortening together.
Beat in the eggs. Sift together the flour, salt, soda, cinnamon and nutmeg.
Add flour and then fold in the apples and nuts.
Bake in greased Pyrex 9-inch pan at 350° for 35 to 40 minutes. Serve with whipped cream or ice cream.

title: meat pie
directions: Brown ground beef.
Add the can of cream of mushroom soup and sour cream.
After mixing, add the onion.
Let crescent rolls get room temperature.
Spread crescent rolls on cookie sheet (1 can). Then take meat mixture and make layer.
Cover the layer with lemon pepper, shredded cheese and the second can of crescent rolls. Bake at 375° until brown.

title: brussels sprouts
directions: Thaw Brussels sprouts.
Slice each in half.
Saute onion and garlic in olive oil.
Add sprouts.
Cook and turn until tender. Place in dish and sprinkle with Parmesan cheese.

title: beef noodle casserole
directions: Marinate beef in Worcestershire sauce and soy sauce.
Let set for 1 hour.
Drain marinade and save.
Put the meat in a large pan on stove.
Add garlic powder, thyme, paprika, salt and pepper. Sprinkle flour and vegetable oil over meat.
Cook on high for 10 minutes.
Then add onions, cream of mushroom soup, cream of celery soup and water.
Mix, then pour over meat.
Add peas.
Add uncooked noodles.
Add the marinade you saved.
Cook 15 to 20 minutes.

title: baked corn
directions: Cook the corn (or if using canned, not necessary).
Beat the eggs, milk, seasonings and 2 tablespoons butter.
Mix well.
Pour into greased 1 1/2-quart baking dish.
Mix crumbs with butter and sprinkle over corn mixture.
Bake at 350° for 40 minutes or until mixture is set.

title: turkey tetrazzini
directions: Preheat oven to 400°.
Cook spaghetti per package directions. Make cream sauce.
Blend margarine and flour over medium heat. Add broth and cook, stirring until smooth and thick.
Add milk, sherry and salt and pepper to taste.
Drain spaghetti.
Combine sauce, turkey and spaghetti; pour into two 2-quart greased casseroles.
Top with Parmesan.
Bake for 20 minutes.
Freezes well.

title: potato salad
directions: Mix together everything and put paprika on top if you have any.

title: seafood soup
directions: Heat and serve.
Serves 4 to 6.

title: apple salad
directions: Cook pineapple, sugar and cream cheese. Boil 2 to 3 minutes. Add Jell-O. Pour in oblong dish. Fold in apples, nuts and Cool Whip. Refrigerate before serving.

title: sausage casserole
directions: Mix all ingredients.
Bake covered in a greased 2-quart casserole at 325° for 1 hour.
Stir after 30 minutes.
Serve with a salad and garlic bread.

title: coconut pecan frosting
directions: Combine sugar, milk, egg yolks, Crisco and vanilla.
Cook and stir over medium heat to boiling (takes about 12 minutes).
Remove from heat; add coconut and pecans.
Beat until frosting thickens. Cool 15 minutes.
Frosts two 8 or 9-inch layers or 13 x 9-inch cake.

title: buttermilk-herb chicken
directions: Combine buttermilk with next 7 ingredients in a 9 x 13-inch dish.
Add chicken breasts and turn to coat with marinade.
Cover and refrigerate overnight.
Drain (discard marinade).
Combine bread crumbs and Parmesan cheese.
Dredge chicken in bread crumb mixture, coating all over.
Place in 9 x 13-inch dish coated with cooking spray.
Drizzle with margarine.
Bake at 350° for 35 to 40 minutes or until chicken is no longer pink when cut in thickest part.
Serves 4.

title: easy zucchini casserole
directions: Dice 3 cups of zucchini and set aside.
In a large bowl, mix all of the other ingredients.
Stir zucchini into mixture and pour in a greased 9-inch Pyrex dish.
Bake at 350° for 50 to 60 minutes.

title: barbecue meat loaf
directions: Combine first 6 ingredients; add 1/2 cup tomato sauce and stir well.
Shape into a 12 x 7-inch loaf; place on a lightly greased rack of a broiler pan.
Combine remaining tomato sauce and remaining ingredients in a saucepan; stir well.
Bring to a boil over medium heat.
Reduce heat; simmer about 10 minutes, stirring occasionally.
Set aside.
Bake meat loaf at 350° for 1 1/2 hours, basting with the barbecue sauce the last 30 minutes of baking.
Serve with remaining sauce.

title: apple fritters
directions: Mix first 5 ingredients.
Drop by spoonfuls.
Fry in deep fat. Dust with powdered sugar.

title: rice pudding
directions: Beat eggs well.
Add one cup of milk and then stir eggs and milk together.
Add sugar and beat.
Heat rice in one cup of milk. Mix all ingredients together and pour in baking dish.
Put butter slices on top of mixture.
Bake at 400° for 40 minutes or until brown.

title: sugarless pecan pie
directions: Heat Karo to boiling point.
Break eggs into medium bowl and beat slightly.
Add butter, vanilla and spices.
Pour hot syrup (Karo) over egg mixture and beat with fork until butter has melted.
Pour into unbaked pie shell.
Add pecans.
Bake at 350° until knife inserted in filling comes out clean, about 40 minutes.

title: shortbread cookies
directions: Mix flour and sugar together. Mix butter in mixture. Add vanilla. Form into small balls and place on cookie sheet a few inches apart. With fork, take and press the top of cookies, making a crisscross pattern. Bake at 375° for 10 to 15 minutes until brown. Cool on wire rack.

title: puppy dog tails(cookies)
directions: Roll into tails and bake at 350° for 20 minutes after mixing together.
When cool, roll in powdered sugar.

title: a to z bread
directions: Sift dry ingredients; set aside.
Beat eggs in a large bowl; add oil and sugar, cream well.

title: salmon patties
directions: Mix meal and flour.
Add all other ingredients to salmon, then add meal, flour mixture.
Roll out in patties.
Fry in oil until brown.

title: tapioca pudding
directions: Put tapioca, cornstarch and 5 tablespoons sugar in saucepan and mix.
Add yolks to milk and then to the dry ingredients.
Beat egg whites and 4 tablespoons sugar; set aside.
Cook 8 minutes until boiling; add 1 teaspoon vanilla.
Pour into whipped egg whites. Fold in until mixed.

title: pumpkin cake
directions: Combine all ingredients and beat well.
Bake in 350° oven in a 9 x 13-inch pan for 20 to 30 minutes.

title: crunchy chicken breasts
directions: Place chicken breast pieces between 2 pieces of wax paper on a cutting board.
Pound out with a meat mallet on both sides to tenderize.
Dip in seasoned flour.
In a small bowl, beat egg and milk together.
Place crushed cereal on clean sheet of wax paper. Dip chicken pieces in beaten egg and milk.
Roll in crushed cereal to coat.
Heat oil in skillet and saute until golden brown on both sides.
Drain on paper towels and serve.
Serves 4.

title: pumpkin bread
directions: Sift flour, salt, soda and spices only once. Combine pumpkin, salad oil, applesauce and sugar.
Add flour mixture alternately with eggs.
Mix well.
Add raisins and nuts.
Bake at 350° about 1 hour.
Makes 2 loaves.

title: mexican rice
directions: Fill plate with rice.
Crumple handful of tortilla chips. Place cheese over top.
Cover with beans.
Microwave until cheese melts.
Cover with salsa.
Season to taste.
I use red pepper, Tabasco and soy sauce.

title: cranberry sauce salad
directions: Mix pineapple juice with jello and water; heat to dissolve jello.
Remove and stir in lemon juice, nutmeg and cranberry sauce.
Cool until thickened slightly.
Add sour cream and mix. Fold in pineapple and nuts.
Let set for 6 to 8 hours.

title: mashed potatoes
directions: Whip together and pour into flat baking dishes. Garnish with Parmesan cheese and paprika.
Heat through and serve.
Can be frozen and served later. Good with ham.

title: cider loaf
directions: Cream sugar and shortening. Add milk, eggs and vanilla.
Blend alternately with mixed dry ingredients and cider.
Mix in apples and nuts.
Grease and flour large bread pan.
Sprinkle with topping of 1/2 teaspoon cinnamon and 2 teaspoons sugar.
Bake at 350° for 1 hour and 15 minutes.

title: steamed rice
directions: Put 1 cup of long grain rice and 1 cup of tap water in the bowl.
Gently rub rice between fingers, then drain rice through the strainer.
Put rice and strainer back in the bowl, another cup of water and rub again.
Repeat this process until the water in the bowl is clear (about 3 times).
Now, dump the rice out of the strainer into the bowl and add 1 cup of water.
Put bowl into the steamer.
Turn heat to medium-high under the steamer.
When steam starts to develop, cover and steam rice for 20 minutes at the medium-high setting.
Turn heat to low and steam 10 minutes more. Cooked rice will be tightly packed, so fluff with a wet chopstick or fork.

title: skillet cookies
directions: Cook in heavy pan until thick (first four ingredients).
Add vanilla, Rice Krispies and chopped nuts.
Let cool.
Roll in small balls and roll in coconut.

title: tree house chocolate pudding
directions: Put cocoa and sugar into saucepan.
Mix until well blended. Add milk to cocoa mixture.
Stir until dry ingredients are dissolved.
Cook over medium heat, stirring constantly until mixture starts to boil.
Boil for 1 minute.
Remove from heat. Cover the pan and let cool or serve warm.
After pudding has cooled to room temperature, it must be refrigerated.
Makes 4 servings.

title: macaroni casserole
directions: Gradually add macaroni and salt to rapidly boiling water so that water continues to boil.
Cook, uncovered, stirring occasionally until tender.
Drain in colander.
Return macaroni to cooking pot.
Mix in soup, ham and green beans.
Cook and stir until mixture is hot.
Dine on half and freeze remainder.

title: broccoli cheese soup
directions: Melt butter in frypan.
Add onions, carrots, potatoes, celery, broccoli and green peppers; saute until tender.
Then add broth. Gradually add milk to flour, then combine with broth and vegetables in a large pot.
Bring to a boil and let thicken for 5 to 10 minutes.
Add Cheez Whiz and salt and pepper to taste. Reduce heat and simmer for another 10 minutes.
Makes 8 generous servings.

title: patience cake
directions: Bake cake as directed on box in 2 large pans.
When completely cool, slice layers in half, making 4 layers.
Mix frosting in large container.
Ice cake and refrigerate for 3 days.

title: hickory nut cake
directions: Cream sugar and butter.
Sift dry ingredients; add alternately with milk.
Add nuts with dry ingredients.
Last fold in egg whites and vanilla.
Bake at 350° for 25 minutes.

title: miniature drumsticks
directions: Cut off wing tips and discard; cut remainder in half.
Blend flour, cheese, m.s.g., salt, paprika and oregano.
Add Tabasco to buttermilk.
Dip "drumsticks" in buttermilk mixture.
Shake to remove excess.
Roll in dry ingredients.
Cook about 5 minutes in deep oil heated to 365°.

title: applesauce cookies
directions: Cream shortening and sugar together.
Combine dry ingredients together, all except the soda.
In separate bowl, add applesauce and the soda.
Stir, letting applesauce foam.
Add creamed mixture and applesauce together.
Mix while adding egg and vanilla, then add dry ingredients, beating until moist.
Stir in chocolate chips and drop by teaspoon onto ungreased cookie sheet.
Bake at 375° for 15 to 20 minutes.

title: blueberry pie(a favorite of ben longwood)
directions: Heat oven to 425°.
Prepare pastry.
Mix sugar, flour and cinnamon.
Stir in blueberries.
Turn into pastry-lined pie plate; sprinkle with lemon juice.
Dot with margarine.
Cover with top crust that has slits cut in it; seal and flute.
Cover edge with 2 to 3-inch strip of aluminum foil to prevent excessive browning; remove foil during last 15 minutes of baking.
Bake until crust is brown and juice begins to bubble through slits in crust, 35 to 45 minutes.
Makes 6 servings, 550 calories per serving.

title: pumpkin bread
directions: In a medium bowl, combine dry ingredients; set aside.
In a large bowl, blend pumpkin, oil, water and eggs.
Gradually add dry ingredients until well blended.
Stir in peanut butter chips and nuts.
Put batter into 3 greased and floured loaf pans.
Bake at 350° for approximately 1 hour or until toothpick comes out clean. Cool loaves in pan 10 minutes.
Take out and cool completely on racks.

title: make ahead macaroni
directions: Combine all ingredients.
Pour into 13 x 9-inch baking dish. Cover and refrigerate overnight.
Bake uncovered for 1 hour at 350°.
Serves 6 to 8.

title: german oven pancake
directions: Preheat oven to 450°.
Beat eggs until foamy.
Add milk and beat again until well blended.
Add flour and salt and beat until smooth.
Put the butter into a deep, glass pie pan or 10-inch skillet (ovenproof).
Place in oven for 5 minutes or until butter melts.

title: sweet potato fritters
directions: Spread potatoes and onions on clean dish towel.
Roll up, twisting towel to extract moisture.
In bowl, whisk eggs, flour, salt and pepper until smooth.
In large nonstick skillet, heat 1/4 cup oil over medium high heat.
Add vegetables to batter and mix. Spoon 1 tablespoon mixture into skillet.
With back of spoon, flatten slightly.
Fry 4 minutes.
Turn and fry 2 to 4 more minutes.
Drain on paper towels.
Keep warm while frying remaining fritters adding more oil if necessary.
Makes 6 servings. Nutrient information per serving: Calories 157, Carbohydrates 23 g., Cholesterol 106 mgs., Protein 5 g., Fat 5 g., Sodium 217 mg.

title: party rye appetizers
directions: Brown meats.
Drain off excess fat.
Stir in melted Velveeta cheese and spread on rye slices.
Bake at 350° for 10 minutes. (Appetizers may be frozen before baking and heated in a 350° oven for 15 minutes before serving.) Yields 48.

title: chocolate pudding dessert
directions: First Layer:
Mix the butter, flour and sugar.
Press into bottom of greased 9 x 13-inch pan. Bake at 325° for 15 minutes or until light brown. Cool.

title: peanut butter chews
directions: In a 2-quart pan, melt chocolate chips and peanut butter over low heat, stirring occasionally, for 4 to 5 minutes.
In a 3-quart bowl, pour peanut butter mixture over the corn flakes, marshmallows and raisins, stirring until all flakes are coated. Press into a 13 x 9-inch buttered pan.
Cool completely in refrigerator; cut into bars.
Makes 3 dozen.

title: vegetable medley
directions: Combine vegetables in saucepan in small amount of water and steam 6 to 7 minutes; drain.
Combine vegetables, soup, half of cheese, sour cream, pepper, pimento and half of onions.
Pour into a buttered casserole.
Bake, covered, at 350° for 30 minutes.
Top with remaining cheese and onions.
Bake, uncovered, 5 minutes longer.
Serves 6.

title: mallow granola bars
directions: Melt butter in large pan.
Add marshmallows and stir.
Turn burner off before marshmallows are completely melted.
(This keeps bars softer.)
Add granola and stir.
Pour into greased loaf pan and press down with wax paper.
Sprinkle chocolate chips on top and press.
I like to use warm granola so the marshmallows are easier to work with.
Cut when cooled.

title: peanut patties
directions: Stir together and boil for 5 minutes.
Remove from heat and add 1 cup of powdered sugar and couple teaspoons of red food coloring.
Pour in pan over foil or in foil cupcake cups.

title: yellow dream cake
directions: Mix cake mix, oil, oranges and eggs.
Bake, in 3 pans that have been greased and floured, at 350° for 35 minutes.
Cool.

title: shiver shakes
directions: Combine all ingredients in a blender. Process until well-blended. Sprinkle with crushed mints and serve in tall glasses with a candy cane.

title: paper bag apple pie
directions: Mix together 1/2 cup sugar, three tablespoons flour and the cinnamon.
Sprinkle evenly over thinly sliced apples; set aside.

title: stephanie's cake
directions: Prepare cake mix according to package directions in a 9 x 13-inch pan, except replace 1 cup of water (called for in recipe) with 1/2 cup water and 1/2 cup strained pineapple juice.
While cake is baking, mix vanilla pudding with milk.
Blend in cream cheese.
Fold in 3/4 container of Cool Whip.
Spread on cooled cake.
Top with strained pineapple and shredded coconut.

title: blueberry dessert
directions: Whip Dream Whip according to package directions.
Mix cream cheese with sugar until well blended.
Add Dream Whip; beat until well mixed.
Pour into pie shells (can use either crumb or baked shells with pecans pressed into them); chill.
Top with can of blueberry pie filling to which you add juice of 1 lemon.
Makes 2 (9-inch) pies or can be made in 9 x 13-inch pan.

title: fresh apple cake
directions: Mix sugar, shortening and egg whites together.	Add dry ingredients and milk and blend together.
Add apples and nuts; mix.
Spray
x
13-inch	pan with Baker's Joy.
Pour batter into pan.
Bake 1 hour at 350°.

title: glaze for ham
directions: Mix together and spread on ham for last 30 to 45 minutes of baking time.
Bake ham at 350° for approximately 15 minutes per pound or follow wrapping directions for precooked ham.

title: cheesecake
directions: Combine above ingredients.
Pat into bottom of 9 x 13-inch pan.

title: german potato salad
directions: On medium heat, fry bacon until crisp; set aside.
Drain off all but 3 to 4 tablespoons of grease; save rest.
Fry onion in bacon grease until transparent.
You may need to add a little more grease.
Add potato cubes, salt and pepper.
Fry potatoes, stirring often to keep from sticking.
When just about done, mix cornstarch, chicken broth, parsley and vinegar.
Add to potatoes and stir together well.
Cover and simmer for 5 to 10 more minutes.
Mix in bacon.
Serve hot.

title: library paste
directions: Mix ingredients, except oil of cloves, together in a pan and cook over low flame, stirring constantly, until thick.
Remove from fire and add oil of cloves.
This prevents spoilage and gives the paste a nice odor.
Pour into jars.
The recipe makes one pint.
If made as directed, the paste will keep several months.

title: spiced pumpkin cake in coffee cans
directions: Beat eggs.
Mix all dry ingredients together and gradually add to bowl with eggs.
Beat slowly.
When batter is smooth, add the pumpkin, oil, water, walnuts, raisins and coconut; beat until everything is well blended.
Grease four 1-pound coffee cans with oil and dust with flour.
Fill cans up 3/4 full.
All cans are baked at one time.
Bake at 350° for 1 hour.
Test with a long tester in center to be sure it is done.
Cool on wire rack.
Take out of cans; wrap in clear wrap.
Can be frozen until needed.

title: lemon bars
directions: Press first 3 ingredients into a 9 x 13-inch pan.
Bake at 350° for 20 minutes.
Mix remaining ingredients.
Spread over hot crust.
Bake 20 to 25 minutes longer.
Cut while hot.
When cool, sprinkle 2 teaspoons powdered sugar over top.

title: classic dip
directions: Beat all ingredients in small mixing bowl at medium speed until well blended.
Refrigerate.
Serve with vegetable dippers or as a baked potato topper.
Makes 2 cups.

title: watergate salad
directions: Combine all ingredients.
Refrigerate until ready to serve.

title: molasses sugar cookies
directions: Cream oil and sugar.
Add molasses and egg.
Beat well. Add dry ingredients.
Chill well, approximately 2 hours.
Roll in balls, then in
sugar.
Bake at 375° for 8 to 10 minutes on greased cookie sheet.

title: pecan pie
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
Beat eggs just until blended.
Add sugar, salt and corn syrup.
Add cooled melted butter and vanilla. Mix to blend well.
Spread nuts in bottom of pie shell.
Pour in filling.
Bake for 50 to 60 minutes.
Makes two 10-inch pies.

title: three bean baked beans
directions: Saute onions and garlic.
Do not brown. Mix all other ingredients.
Pour into 2 or 3-quart baking dish. Stir a time or two during baking. Bake 1 to 1 1/4 hours at 350°.
Freezes nicely.

title: pork chops and sauerkraut
directions: Wash
and rinse sauerkraut and place in casserole.
Put onion in
center
and
add
juniper
berries and peppercorns. Distribute applesauce over the top.
Pour wine over all, then add
a
little water to just about cover.
Simmer slowly (covered),
about
hours.
Place
browned
chops among the sauerkraut and bake in 325° to 350° oven for about 1 hour.

title: real italian spaghetti sauce
directions: Brown sausage; drain well. Add each following ingredient, stirring after each addition. Add 1 teaspoon pepper; simmer for about 5 hours.

title: impossible pumpkin pie
directions: Mix all ingredients in blender on medium speed.
Pour into 10-inch greased pie plate.
Bake at 350° for 45 to 50 minutes or until a knife blade comes out clean. Makes its own crust.

title: southern casserole pie
directions: Coat stew meat in flour and seasoning.
Saute meat in skillet until brown.
Combine meat and vegetables in dish.
Add enough water to cover. Bake, covered, at 350° for 1 1/2 hours or until tender.
Uncover.

title: pie crust
directions: Sift the flour and salt into pie pan.
Bring water and shortening to boil and pour slowly over the flour and salt mixture. Mix with large spoon, then pat out using spoon and hands, do not roll.
Flute edge.
Fill with your favorite filling.
For a cooked shell, prick and place in 350° oven until golden brown.
Cool and fill.

title: pork chop casserole
directions: Season pork chops, dust with flour and quickly brown in hot oil.
Place in a casserole dish in the order listed.
Cover.
Bake at 350° for about 1 hour.
Delicious!!
Easy!!

title: tea cakes
directions: Mix all ingredients thoroughly.
Using a tablespoon, place as many on cookie sheet as possible.
Bake at 375° until lightly brown.
Makes about 3 dozen.

title: french cherry pie
directions: Cream confectioners sugar and cream cheese in bowl until soft. In separate bowl, whip cream with vanilla and confectioners sugar to taste.
Combine contents of both bowls and pour into cooled pie crust.
Cover with cherry or your choice pie filling and refrigerate until ready to serve.

title: spaghetti salad
directions: Boil and drain spaghetti.
Cut cleaned vegetables in small pieces.
Toss in a large bowl.
Add spaghetti and Salad Supreme to taste.
Add Italian salad dressing, about 1 cup, a little at a time.
You may need more dressing according to size of vegetables.

title: quail casserole
directions: Brown quail in stick of margarine; remove quail.
Brown onion and pepper.
Add soup, milk and wine.
Put quail and sauce in casserole dish.
Salt and pepper.
Bake at 325° for 1 hour.

title: the banana bread of kings(fat-free)
directions: Measure bran, banana, applesauce and sugar in a large bowl. Add the water and stir.
Sift flour; add flour to banana mixture, stirring only until combined.
Pour into bread pan and place in oven.
Bake at 350° for 40 to 45 minutes.

title: zucchini cake
directions: Mix, milk, marshmallows, and orange juice with graham cracker crumbs and other ingredients.
Mix with hands, until crumbs are moist.
Makes one large Fruitcake by pressing mixture into a waxed paper lined angel food cake pan.
If mixture becomes too crumbly to shape easily, add a few drops of milk.
Cover Fruitcake tightly. Chill 2 days before serving.
Makes 1 (4 1/2 lb.) cake.

title: chicken vegetable saute
directions: Wash and dry the chicken.
Heat margarine in heavy skillet that has a lid.
Add garlic and chicken.
Saute slowly over very low heat until browned and chicken is cooked almost all the way through, about 20 minutes.
Add potatoes and green onions to the pan with chicken.
Place chicken pieces on top of the potatoes. Cover and saute 5 minutes.
Add peas, mushrooms and chicken broth.

title: 24 hour vegetable salad
directions: Mix onion, bell pepper, celery, corn, peas and pimento.
Boil sugar, apple cider vinegar and oil.
Pour oil mixture over vegetables.
Let stand 24 hours at room temperature before serving.

title: toad-in-the-hole(british)
directions: Sift flour and salt into a bowl.
Beat to a smooth batter with egg, half the milk and melted butter.
Stir in remaining milk.
